п»ї{"_id":"SVH1DJRN00000001","name":"Act 1 Гўв‚¬вЂќ Restore the Flame (Director Journal)","pages":[{"_id":"RTFPAGE000000018","name":"Beat 1 Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Konungs-ferГѓВ° (The KingГўв‚¬в„ўs Call)","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 1\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eDuration:\u003c/strong\u003e Г‚ВЅ session\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eLocations:\u003c/strong\u003e The PCs\u0027 home towns\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Roleplay introduction, table-round character moments\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eTone:\u003c/strong\u003e Grim duty, communal desperation, old law invoked in new crisis\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1a3a; color:#c8c8e8; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4a4ac8;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVP Status Гўв‚¬вЂќ Entering This Beat\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cstrong\u003eTotal VP (max):\u003c/strong\u003e 0 | \u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 | \u003cstrong\u003eVP into Level:\u003c/strong\u003e 0\u003cbr\u003e\u003cem style=\"font-size:0.9em;\"\u003eCampaign start - heroes begin at Level 1.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1a3a; color:#c8c8e8; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4a4ac8;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVP Status Гўв‚¬вЂќ Entering This Beat\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cstrong\u003eTotal VP (max):\u003c/strong\u003e 0 | \u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 | \u003cstrong\u003eVP into Level:\u003c/strong\u003e 0\u003cbr\u003e\u003cem style=\"font-size:0.9em;\"\u003eCampaign start - heroes begin at Level 1.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2\u003eOverview\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBefore the campaignГўв‚¬в„ўs main machinery begins, the ancient call goes out under \u003cstrong\u003eHigh King HaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs Danelaw\u003c/strong\u003e: a \u003cstrong\u003eKonungs-ferГѓВ°\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќa kingГўв‚¬в„ўs-journey duty, invoked in desperation. The last time this law was used was three generations ago, during the Second Barrow-War. Its invocation now tells every jarl in Svellheim that the king is out of options.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe call reaches multiple towns (the PCs\u0027 homes) through riders, skalds, stamped notices, or lantern signals. Each community chooses (or pressures) a local hero to answer. The chosen are told to make for \u003cstrong\u003eHrafnborg\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќbecause contracts, rations, and authority still exist there.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis beat establishes:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSvellheim is freezing. The world is ending slowly.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs are not chosen for gloryГўв‚¬вЂќthey are chosen because someone had to go.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe law still has weight, even when everything else is failing.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eThe Call\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eRun this as a quick table-round introduction. Each player describes:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHow the Konungs-ferГѓВ° reached their characterГўв‚¬в„ўs town\u003c/strong\u003e (rider, skald, lantern signal, sealed letter with the raven-seal).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHow their community \"volunteered\" them\u003c/strong\u003e (Thing vote, hearth-oath called in, a debt owed, a Quiet WardenГўв‚¬в„ўs quiet suggestion, a parentГўв‚¬в„ўs sacrifice).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat they packed\u003c/strong\u003e (one personal item that matters to themГўв‚¬вЂќthis becomes a character hook later).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe call is formal, ancient, and heavy with law:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"\u003cem\u003eBy the Danelaw of High King Harald, bearer of the Cold Iron Crown, a Konungs-ferГѓВ° is proclaimed. Let each settlement of loyal standing send forth one champion to Hrafnborg, there to serve the realmГўв‚¬в„ўs need in this time of shadow and frost.\u003c/em\u003e\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe words are old. The desperation is new.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eRunning the Selection\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLet the table roleplay \u003cstrong\u003ewhy\u003c/strong\u003e each hero was chosen. Give each player 2Гўв‚¬вЂњ3 minutes to set their scene.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePrompts for the local jarl or hall-leader:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"YouГўв‚¬в„ўre too good to waste here. Go make my name bigger.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"If you die in the fjords, I wonГўв‚¬в„ўt have to feed you.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"You owe me for the winter I saved you from. This is the price.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"They asked for a warrior. IГўв‚¬в„ўm sending a problem.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"YouГўв‚¬в„ўre the only one who can speak to strangers without starting a blood-feud.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"The Warden said your name. I donГўв‚¬в„ўt argue with the Wardens.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eWhat the PCs Know\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Fimbulwinter is three years old and getting worse.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe dead are risingГўв‚¬вЂќnot everywhere, but more often, and closer to towns.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHrafnborg is the largest settlement still standing. The king is there. Rations are there. Law is there.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eA Konungs-ferГѓВ° is a serious thing. Refusing it stains a familyГўв‚¬в„ўs name for a generation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eWhat the PCs DonГўв‚¬в„ўt Know\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhy the Konungs-ferГѓВ° was really called.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThat the Ever-Embers are dying.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThat the Ember-Keepers are dead.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThat they are being chosen specifically because they are \u003cstrong\u003eunknown\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќoutsiders the king can trust because no one in his court has had time to compromise them.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eGM Notes\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ Pacing and Tone\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis beat should feel like the beginning of a journey no one wants to make. The PCs are not heroes yetГўв‚¬вЂќthey are burdens their communities can afford to lose, debts that needed paying, or good people in bad circumstances who couldnГўв‚¬в„ўt say no.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDo not rush this.\u003c/strong\u003e The emotional foundation of the campaign is laid here. When the PCs look back on this moment from Beat 9, standing outside a besieged Hrafnborg, the contrast should hit like a hammer.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf a player struggles with the \"why me?\" prompt, offer one: \"Your communityГўв‚¬в„ўs healer says the dead whisper your bloodlineГўв‚¬в„ўs name. Better you go than they come here.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ Connecting to Character Options\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf your players chose Svellheim-specific ancestries, cultures, or careers during character creation, tie the Konungs-ferГѓВ° to those choices:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHearthborn:\u003c/strong\u003e The local Ever-Ember flickered when the call arrived. The elders took it as a sign.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFrostblood:\u003c/strong\u003e The community doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt trust what you are. Sending you away solves two problems.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eKin of the Deep:\u003c/strong\u003e Something stirred in the old mine. The foreman says you know too much to stay.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWarden-touched:\u003c/strong\u003e A Quiet Warden visited your door at dawn. \"The dead are choosing sides. Time you did too.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#2a6a2a;\"\u003eBeat 1 Гўв‚¬вЂќ Victory Point Summary\u003c/h4\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eNo VP-earning encounters this beat. Total: 0 VP.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#2a6a2a;\"\u003eBeat 1 Гўв‚¬вЂќ Victory Point Summary\u003c/h4\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eNo VP-earning encounters this beat. Total: 0 VP.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eTransition to Beat 2\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOnce each player has described their departure, compress time:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou leave behind the only warmth youГўв‚¬в„ўve ever known. The roads are badГўв‚¬вЂќworse than last year, worse than the year before. The mile-markers are buried. The lanterns are dark. But the direction is clear: south toward the coast, toward Hrafnborg.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou are not the only one on the road.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs begin to encounter each other on the Lantern Road. Proceed to \u003cstrong\u003eBeat 2: The Road to Hrafnborg\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","markdown":null},"src":null,"system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"sort":10,"flags":{},"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"exportSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"draw-steel","systemVersion":"0.10.0","createdTime":0,"modifiedTime":0,"lastModifiedBy":null}},{"_id":"RTFPAGE000000019","name":"Beat 2 Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Road to Hrafnborg","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 1\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eDuration:\u003c/strong\u003e Г‚ВЅГўв‚¬вЂњ1 session\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eLocations:\u003c/strong\u003e The Lantern Road, a wayside inn (optional), a graveyard ruin outside Hrafnborg\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Travel montage (Easy), social introduction, combat encounter\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eTone:\u003c/strong\u003e Cold fellowship, growing dread, first blood\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1a3a; color:#c8c8e8; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4a4ac8;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVP Status Гўв‚¬вЂќ Entering This Beat\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cstrong\u003eTotal VP (max):\u003c/strong\u003e 0 | \u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 | \u003cstrong\u003eVP into Level:\u003c/strong\u003e 0\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1a3a; color:#c8c8e8; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4a4ac8;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVP Status Гўв‚¬вЂќ Entering This Beat\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cstrong\u003eTotal VP (max):\u003c/strong\u003e 0 | \u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 | \u003cstrong\u003eVP into Level:\u003c/strong\u003e 0\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2\u003eOverview\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs travel to Hrafnborg along the failing Lantern Road. On the way, they meet each otherГўв‚¬вЂќstrangers bound by the same grim duty. They share a road, a fire, and their suspicions.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOn the last night, just outside HrafnborgГўв‚¬в„ўs outer walls, the party passes an old church ruin with a frozen graveyard. The dead rise. This is the PCs\u0027 first combat encounter and their first proof that the crisis is real.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis beat establishes:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs as a group (from suspicion to necessity).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTravel in Svellheim is dangerous and expensive.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe dead are rising, and they \u003cstrong\u003eremember\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 1: The Road\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Montage Test | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Easy | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on success / 0 VP on failure\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Montage Test | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Easy | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on success / 0 VP on failure\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eRun the journey as a short \u003cstrong\u003eMontage Test\u003c/strong\u003e (Easy difficulty, 2Гўв‚¬вЂњ3 days of travel).\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eParty Size Adjustment (4 heroes):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDifficulty\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eSuccess Limit\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eFailure Limit\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEasy (adjusted)\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e4\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e4\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eSample Tests\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eChallenge\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCharacteristic\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDescription\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eNavigate the Lantern Road\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eReason\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eStay on failing roads, read buried markers, avoid dead-end detours.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eEndure the cold\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eMight\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eResist frostbite, carry gear through snowdrifts, ford frozen streams.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eFind shelter at night\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eIntuition\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eLocate wind-breaks, abandoned crofts, or natural shelters.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAvoid trouble on the road\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAgility\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eSlip past bandit camps, desperate refugees, or rival groups.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eMontage Outcomes\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTotal Success:\u003c/strong\u003e Arrive rested and supplied. No Heat loss. Earn 1 Victory.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePartial Success:\u003c/strong\u003e Arrive tired. Lose 1 dayГўв‚¬в„ўs rations (Heat) or one piece of minor equipment is damaged (Weight).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTotal Failure:\u003c/strong\u003e Arrive exhausted and rattled. One PC has a \u003cstrong\u003econdition\u003c/strong\u003e (frostbitten or exhausted). Lose 2 days\u0027 rations. Director gains 2 additional Malice for the graveyard encounter.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 2: Meeting on the Road\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eDuring the montage, the PCs encounter each other. Let them introduce themselves \u003cstrong\u003ein character\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eStart with suspicion, necessity, and shared hardship. Maybe they camp together. Maybe they share a fire at a roadside waystation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eConversation starters:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"You answering the Konungs-ferГѓВ° too? You poor bastard.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"IГўв‚¬в„ўve got half a fire. YouГўв‚¬в„ўve got half a fire. Together thatГўв‚¬в„ўs almost warm.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"Where are you from? Гўв‚¬В¦Never heard of it. Probably still standing, then.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eOptional: The Burnt Peat (Tavern Introduction)\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you want a classic \"you all meet in a tavern\" opener, place a waystation inn halfway to Hrafnborg.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eName:\u003c/strong\u003e The Burnt Peat\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWarmth costs extra.\u003c/strong\u003e (1 iron-token for a seat near the fire.)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe locals are wary\u003c/strong\u003e of anyone answering the Konungs-ferГѓВ°. (\"You poor bastards. The kingГўв‚¬в„ўs scraping the barrel now.\")\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe PCs can share a table, a fire, and their reasons for coming.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis gives you a social scene before the violence. ItГўв‚¬в„ўs also a chance to introduce minor color NPCs (a Lantern Road courier, an Ashwright peat-seller, a Quiet Warden who says nothing but watches the PCs with unsettling calm).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 3: The Graveyard (Combat Encounter)\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Combat | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on victory\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Combat | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on victory\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOn the second or third night, just outside HrafnborgГўв‚¬в„ўs outer walls, the party passes an old church ruin. The structure is half-collapsed. The graveyard is frozen, the headstones cracked and leaning.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe ruin looms against the grey skyГўв‚¬вЂќstone ribs of a long-dead faith. The graveyard sprawls around it: tilted stones, frozen earth, and something \u003cstrong\u003ewrong\u003c/strong\u003e in the air.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe cold here is different. It doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt just chill your skin. It \u003cstrong\u003epulls\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThen you hear it: the scrape of bone on frozen ground.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eEncounter: Draugr Ambush\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate (Level 1 PCs)\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eEncounter Value:\u003c/strong\u003e Tune to party size (3 heroes ГўвЂ°Л† EV 12Гўв‚¬вЂњ16)\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEnemies:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e3Гўв‚¬вЂњ4 \u003cstrong\u003eDraugr Thralls\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 1 Minions)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e1 \u003cstrong\u003eBarrow-Warden\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 2 Standard)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTerrain:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFrozen ground (difficult terrain in patches)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCracked headstones (cover, 1 square high)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eRuined church walls (partial shelter, 2 squares wide, line-of-sight blocker)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLighting:\u003c/strong\u003e Dim (torches/lanterns required; attacks without a light source have a bane)\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eSpecial Rule: The Dead Remember the Law\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhen a draugr is reduced to 0 HP, it whispers a name or an accusation before crumbling. This is narrative color, but it foreshadows later revelations:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"You broke guest-rightГўв‚¬В¦\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"The Ember died because of youГўв‚¬В¦\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"KaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs name is ashГўв‚¬В¦\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"The wolf waits beneath the rootГўв‚¬В¦\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLet the PCs react. Do not explain these whispers. They are seeds planted for Beats 7, 8, and 9.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eStat Blocks\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eUse the following entities from the Svellheim Entities module:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e@UUID[Actor.zUjpuZAf682D5Vov]{Draugr Thrall} (Level 1 Minion)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e@UUID[Actor.6fPQPowgpjUR9ipq]{Barrow-Warden} (Level 2 Standard) Гўв‚¬вЂќ Carries a @UUID[Item.SVH0FrostBlade01]{Frost-Etched Barrow-Blade}\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eAftermath\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAfter the fight:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLet the PCs search the bodies. They find a \u003cstrong\u003e@UUID[Item.SVH0BurialCoin01]{Ember-Keeper\u0027s Burial Coin}\u003c/strong\u003e stamped with the ember-mark (a seven-pointed flame). If any PC recognizes it (medium Reason test), they know itГўв‚¬в„ўs an Ember-KeeperГўв‚¬в„ўs tokenГўв‚¬вЂќold, worn, and shouldnГўв‚¬в„ўt be in a common graveyard.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOne PC might be touched by the Barrow-WardenГўв‚¬в„ўs accusation. (\"You will fail them, tooГўв‚¬В¦\") This is narrative, not mechanicalГўв‚¬вЂќbut let it land.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs can see HrafnborgГўв‚¬в„ўs walls in the distance. Lights. Smoke. Bells.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГўЕЎвЂќГЇВёВЏ Loot\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e@UUID[Item.SVH0BurialCoin01]{Ember-Keeper\u0027s Burial Coin} \u0026mdash; Found on the Barrow-Warden\u0026rsquo;s body. A medium Reason test identifies it as an Ember-Keeper\u0026rsquo;s token.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e@UUID[Item.SVH0FrostBlade01]{Frost-Etched Barrow-Blade} \u0026mdash; Taken from the Barrow-Warden. The runes are Old NorrГ…вЂњnt and reference \u0026ldquo;the law of the grave.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe last draugr crumbles to frost and ash. For a moment, the only sound is your breathing and the wind through the ruinГўв‚¬в„ўs ribs.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThen, from the south, you hear bells. Hrafnborg.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYouГўв‚¬в„ўve arrived.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#2a6a2a;\"\u003eBeat 2 Гўв‚¬вЂќ Victory Point Summary\u003c/h4\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:8px 0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#c0e0c0;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eEvent\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eDifficulty\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eVP Award\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 1: Lantern Road Montage\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eEasy\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e1 VP on success\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 3: Draugr Ambush\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eModerate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e1 VP on victory\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#98cc98;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eBeat Total (Mandatory)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eup to 2 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#2a6a2a;\"\u003eBeat 2 Гўв‚¬вЂќ Victory Point Summary\u003c/h4\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:8px 0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#c0e0c0;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eEvent\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eDifficulty\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eVP Award\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 1: Lantern Road Montage\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eEasy\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e1 VP on success\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 3: Draugr Ambush\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eModerate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e1 VP on victory\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#98cc98;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eBeat Total (Mandatory)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eup to 2 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eTransition to Beat 3\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs approach HrafnborgГўв‚¬в„ўs outer gates. They are processed by Chainwarden clerksГўв‚¬вЂќnames taken, debts recorded, Konungs-ferГѓВ° papers stamped. They are directed to modest quarters in a fortified hall. Fed. Told to wait.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe waiting feels wrong. Proceed to \u003cstrong\u003eBeat 3: The Quiet Summons\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","markdown":null},"src":null,"system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"sort":20,"flags":{},"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"exportSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"draw-steel","systemVersion":"0.10.0","createdTime":0,"modifiedTime":0,"lastModifiedBy":null}},{"_id":"RTFPAGE000000020","name":"Beat 3 Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Quiet Summons","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 1\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eDuration:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 session\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eLocation:\u003c/strong\u003e Hrafnborg Гўв‚¬вЂќ the KingГўв‚¬в„ўs quarters\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eKey NPCs:\u003c/strong\u003e High King Harald, Gragnir (Ash-Walker), Dreyfus (the hound)\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Roleplay, lore delivery, mission briefing\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eTone:\u003c/strong\u003e Paranoia, secrecy, the weight of impossible choices\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1a3a; color:#c8c8e8; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4a4ac8;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVP Status Гўв‚¬вЂќ Entering This Beat\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cstrong\u003eTotal VP (max):\u003c/strong\u003e 2 | \u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 | \u003cstrong\u003eVP into Level:\u003c/strong\u003e 2\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1a3a; color:#c8c8e8; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4a4ac8;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVP Status Гўв‚¬вЂќ Entering This Beat\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cstrong\u003eTotal VP (max):\u003c/strong\u003e 2 | \u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 | \u003cstrong\u003eVP into Level:\u003c/strong\u003e 2\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2\u003eOverview\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs have arrived in Hrafnborg after the graveyard fight. They expect processing, maybe assignments, perhaps even rest. Instead, they are kept in polite custody all day. Late in the evening, High King Harald arrives personallyГўв‚¬вЂќno heralds, no guardsГўв‚¬вЂќand leads them to his private sitting room.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eInside, with only a grey hound as witness, Harald reveals the truth: the Ever-Embers are dying, the Keepers are murdered, and SvellheimГўв‚¬в„ўs warmth is failing.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eGragnir appears from the shadows with the first step: find Lew Tosferd in Stairwatch, who can find Kaelen. The session ends with the PCs accepting the mission and Dreyfus having heard every word.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 1: Polite Custody\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs are ushered into a modest but warm chamber in one of HrafnborgГўв‚¬в„ўs fortified halls. Guards bring foodГўв‚¬вЂќsalt pork, hard bread, watered aleГўв‚¬вЂќand stoke the brazier. They are told to rest. To wait. That the King will \"receive them soon.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHours pass. Morning becomes afternoon. Afternoon becomes dusk.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: Building Tension\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis waiting period is meant to feel \u003cstrong\u003ewrong\u003c/strong\u003e. Let the players describe what their characters do. Some may try to leaveГўв‚¬вЂќpolitely discourage them with guards who are unfailingly courteous but immovable.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"The KingГўв‚¬в„ўs orders, friend. For your safety.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLet tests (easy Reason or Intuition test) or passive observations reveal:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe guards change every two hours. TheyГўв‚¬в„ўre professional, wary, and wonГўв‚¬в„ўt answer questions.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNo one else is being treated this way. Other Konungs-ferГѓВ° arrivals are processed through the Chainwardens\u0027 ledgers and released into the city.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs can hear distant alarm bells twice during the dayГўв‚¬вЂќbrief, then silenced. (These are wall attacks the King will mention later.)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePacing tip:\u003c/strong\u003e If the players get restless, compress time. \"Another hour passes. Then another. The light outside turns grey, then dark. And thenГўв‚¬вЂќthe door opens.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 2: The King Comes\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe door opens quietly. No fanfare. No herald.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA man steps insideГўв‚¬вЂќbroad-shouldered, greying at the temples, wearing a simple wool tunic under a fur-lined cloak. His eyes are sunken, and his hands bear fresh ink stains. Behind him, the hallway is empty.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Come,\" he says, voice low. \"And speak softly.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt wait for questions. He turns and walks.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis is \u003cstrong\u003eHigh King Harald\u003c/strong\u003e. PCs who grew up in SvellheimГўв‚¬в„ўs towns will recognize him from coins, carvings, or stories. He looks older than his reputation. Tired.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLet the PCs follow or hesitate. If they ask questions aloud, Harald puts a finger to his lips and gestures: \u003cem\u003efollow\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Walk\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHarald leads them through cold stone corridors. PCs with sharp eyes (easy Reason or Intuition test) notice:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNo other guards in this section.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe torches are spaced farther apart than usual.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe route avoids the main halls.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhen they reach the KingГўв‚¬в„ўs private door, there are \u003cstrong\u003eno guards\u003c/strong\u003e. This is unusual. In Hrafnborg, even minor nobles post at least one huscarl.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHarald unlocks the door himself, ushers the PCs inside, and locks it behind them.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 3: The Sitting Room\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe room is warmГўв‚¬вЂќperhaps the warmest youГўв‚¬в„ўve felt since the graveyard. A low fire burns in a stone hearth. Furs cover the floor. A table holds a map weighted with cold daggers. Shelves line the walls: scrolls, wax tablets, a childГўв‚¬в„ўs wooden sword.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe room is empty. No advisors. No guards. No servants.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOn the floor near the fire, a large grey hound raises its head. Its eyes are pale, almost silver. It watches you without blinking.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHarald closes the door and leans against it. For a moment, he just breathes.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe hound is \u003cstrong\u003eDreyfus\u003c/strong\u003e. Let the PCs react. If they try to speak to the dog, it does not respondГўв‚¬вЂќbut it \u003cstrong\u003ewatches\u003c/strong\u003e. If anyone uses magic, makes an oath aloud, or speaks a true name, DreyfusГўв‚¬в„ўs ears perk.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#3a1a1a; color:#e0d0c0; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #cc3333;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#ff6666;\"\u003eГўЕЎВ  GM Secret: Dreyfus the Listener\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDreyfus is a shape-walkerГўв‚¬вЂќNГѓВ­ГѓВ°hГѓВ¶ggrГўв‚¬в„ўs eyes and ears in the mortal world. He is Wyrd-bound by guest-right and cannot harm anyone in this room, but he can \u003cstrong\u003ehear\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003eremember\u003c/strong\u003e, and \u003cstrong\u003ereport\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFor now, let him be an unnerving presence. Do not reveal anything yet. The PCs should feel that the dog is strange, but attribute it to an old animalГўв‚¬в„ўs quirks.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTells (for observant players, hard Intuition test):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDreyfus never blinks.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHe watches mouths more than hands.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHe does not eat from the bowl by the hearth (itГўв‚¬в„ўs been full for days).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhen Harald speaks the word \"Kaelen,\" the houndГўв‚¬в„ўs ears flattenГўв‚¬вЂќnot in fear, but in \u003cstrong\u003eattention\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 4: HaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs Confession\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOnce the PCs are settled (or at least silent), Harald speaks. Use this as a framework, not a scriptГўв‚¬вЂќlet the players interrupt, question, or react.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"The Ever-Ember spoke,\" Harald begins, his voice flat. \"Three weeks ago. It spoke to the Keepers and said the Ever-Embers across Svellheim are dying. That it is tired. That it can no longer hold the boundaries between the living and the dead.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe moves to the table, touches the map. \"It promised answers. Promised to explain, after it rested, how we might rekindle the flames. I brought the council together. We prepared. We waited.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe closes his eyes. \"The night before the meeting, the Keepers were slain. All sevenГўв‚¬вЂќevery one of the Ember-Keepers in Svellheim. In their beds. No signs of struggle. No witnesses. There are no Keepers left alive.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHis jaw tightens. \"And the next morning, the dead came for our walls.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLet the PCs process. Then Harald continues:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe attacks have escalated: skeletons, ghosts, barrow-wights, all striking the walls at different points.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEvery defensive plan the council makes is \u003cstrong\u003eanticipated\u003c/strong\u003e. The attacks avoid the traps, circumvent the patrols.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHarald suspects a traitorГўв‚¬вЂќor a leakГўв‚¬вЂќwithin his own command structure.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHe cannot trust his own court. He cannot trust his own shadows.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eLore: The Ever-Embers and Their Keepers\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Ever-Embers\u003c/strong\u003e are sanctioned hearth-flames that burn in major settlements across Svellheim. They are not merely firesГўв‚¬вЂќthey are \u003cstrong\u003eanchors\u003c/strong\u003e, points where YggdrasilГўв‚¬в„ўs warmth-flow stabilizes. In folklore, they \"keep the dead in their graves\" and \"hold back the long dark.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Ember-Keepers\u003c/strong\u003e (civic office) are chosen every ten years in a sacred rite:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eChildren of age (13) are paraded past the Ever-Ember during the winter solstice.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe flame itself \u003cstrong\u003echooses\u003c/strong\u003e seven by spitting a coal-ember onto their foreheads, leaving a permanent mark (a scar that glows faintly in darkness).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe chosen seven serve for ten years, then are replaced.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDuties:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMaintain the flameГўв‚¬в„ўs ring enclosure\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eManage fuel and ward-lines\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eRaise wind-breaks to protect the flame from storms\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSpeak\u003c/strong\u003e to the flame on the cityГўв‚¬в„ўs behalf (a rite performed in silence, with offerings of ash and memory)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe murders are not just politicalГўв‚¬вЂќthey are \u003cstrong\u003eexistential\u003c/strong\u003e. Without Keepers, the Ever-Ember cannot be safely questioned, fed, or calmed. And if the Ever-Ember dies, the dead will flood the city.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 5: The Secret Mission\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAfter the PCs absorb the crisis, Harald delivers the mission.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"I called the Konungs-ferГѓВ° for a reason,\" Harald says, looking each of you in the eye. \"Not for warriors. Not for a war band. I needed people I could trust who no one would suspect. People who owe loyalty to their \u003cstrong\u003ehomes\u003c/strong\u003e, not to my council.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe straightens. \"I need you to find Kaelen. She was one of the seven Keepers. In her second year, she leftГўв‚¬вЂќabandoned her vows, her mark, everything. No one knows why. No one knows where she went.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Find her. Bring her back. If anyone can speak to the Ever-Ember now, itГўв‚¬в„ўs her.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLet the PCs ask questions. Harald answers honestly (remember: \u003cstrong\u003eHarald does not lie\u003c/strong\u003e):\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhy Kaelen?\u003c/strong\u003e She was the youngest Keeper ever chosen (age 13, the minimum). She served faithfully for a year, then vanished. Harald believes guilt or fear drove her awayГўв‚¬вЂќbut also believes she still carries the ember-mark and the knowledge required to speak to the flame.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat happened to her?\u003c/strong\u003e No one knows. She left no message. Some think she fled to the Interior Belt. Some think sheГўв‚¬в„ўs dead.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhy us?\u003c/strong\u003e \"Because no one is watching you. Because youГўв‚¬в„ўre not on any ledger. Because I canГўв‚¬в„ўt trust my own shadows anymore.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat about the attacks?\u003c/strong\u003e \"I have soldiers. I have walls. I can holdГўв‚¬вЂќfor a while. What I donГўв‚¬в„ўt have is a Keeper.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat if she wonГўв‚¬в„ўt come?\u003c/strong\u003e HaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs jaw tightens. \"Convince her. SvellheimГўв‚¬в„ўs warmth depends on it.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 6: The Interruption Гўв‚¬вЂќ Gragnir\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eJust as the PCs agree (or object), the shadows move.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"He tells you \u003cstrong\u003esome\u003c/strong\u003e of the truth.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe voice comes from the corner, low and rough as ash scraped from stone. A figure steps into the firelightГўв‚¬вЂќtall, lean, wrapped in smoke-grey furs. His fingers are black with soot. The smell of burning peat follows him.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs hand goes to his hip (no sword), then drops. \"Gragnir.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe manГўв‚¬вЂќGragnirГўв‚¬вЂќnods to the King, then looks at you. \"The King wants Kaelen. Good. YouГўв‚¬в„ўll need her. But the King doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt know \u003cstrong\u003ewhere\u003c/strong\u003e she is. I do. Or ratherГўв‚¬вЂќI know who does.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eGragnir explains:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThere is a man named \u003cstrong\u003eLlewyellen Tosferd\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќ\"everyone calls him Lew.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLew has a gift: he can find things that are \u003cstrong\u003elost\u003c/strong\u003e. Through old contracts, favors, and a network of informants that spans the Interior BeltГўв‚¬вЂќand through other means he wonГўв‚¬в„ўt discuss.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLew is currently in \u003cstrong\u003eStairwatch\u003c/strong\u003e, a waystation town just beyond MidgardГўв‚¬в„ўs Shield, near the TitanГўв‚¬в„ўs Stair pass.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eItГўв‚¬в„ўs a hard trekГўв‚¬вЂќten days through cold, bandit country, and failing routes (~200 miles across the Coastal Belt and MidgardГўв‚¬в„ўs Shield)Гўв‚¬вЂќand the party must travel \u003cstrong\u003ein secret\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHarald looks grim but doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt contradict Gragnir. Instead, he asks: \"WhatГўв‚¬в„ўs the price?\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eGragnir smiles, ash crinkling at the corners of his mouth. \"For you? Nothing, Highness. For them?\" He looks at the PCs. \"Lew will name his price when you find him. He always does.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: GragnirГўв‚¬в„ўs Manner\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGragnir is not hostile, but he is not comforting either. He speaks like someone who has seen this crisis coming for years and is tired of being ignored.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs press him:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\"How did you get in here?\"\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \"The same way the cold gets in. Through the cracks.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\"Why donГўв‚¬в„ўt YOU find Kaelen?\"\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \"Because sheГўв‚¬в„ўll run from me. She wonГўв‚¬в„ўt run from strangers. Not at first.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\"What arenГўв‚¬в„ўt you telling us?\"\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \"Everything I canГўв‚¬в„ўt prove yet. When I can, youГўв‚¬в„ўll wish I hadnГўв‚¬в„ўt.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\"Who are you?\"\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \"A man who talks to trees. The trees are dying. That should concern you.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 7: The Kicker\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAs the meeting concludes, Gragnir fades back into the shadows (literally or metaphoricallyГўв‚¬вЂќyour choice). Harald gives the PCs what aid he can:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTravel papers\u003c/strong\u003e (forged as \"merchants\u0027 retinue\" to avoid Chainwarden scrutiny)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSupplies:\u003c/strong\u003e 3 days\u0027 cold-weather rations, 2 lantern-oil flasks, 1 @UUID[Item.SVH0CipherPack01]{KingГўв‚¬в„ўs Cipher Packet} (to be used only in dire need)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eA warning:\u003c/strong\u003e \"Trust no one in my name. If someone quotes my orders, assume theyГўв‚¬в„ўre lying or compromised.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAs you turn to leave, the grey houndГўв‚¬вЂќDreyfusГўв‚¬вЂќrises and pads silently to the door. He sits. He watches. And for just a moment, youГўв‚¬в„ўd swear the hound \u003cstrong\u003esmiles\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#3a1a1a; color:#e0d0c0; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #cc3333;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#ff6666;\"\u003eГўЕЎВ  GM Secret: The Leak Is Set\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDreyfus has heard everything. The mission. The names. The destination. He will remain at HaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs sideГўв‚¬вЂќlistening to every war council, every messenger, every whispered orderГўв‚¬вЂќand relay intelligence through Wyrd-channels: root-whispers carried along YggdrasilГўв‚¬в„ўs dying root-lines. While agents of Grafvitnir may act on this intelligence, Dreyfus serves the deeper entropy.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis is the engine that drives the Grafvitnir Pressure Check for the rest of Act 1. The PCs donГўв‚¬в„ўt know theyГўв‚¬в„ўve been compromisedГўв‚¬вЂќbut you do.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eNarrative consequences for later beats:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs agentsГўв‚¬вЂќPale Maw cultists, corrupted officials, Wyrd-touched creaturesГўв‚¬вЂќknow the PCs\u0027 mission and destination.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDreyfus staying with Harald means the spy has \u003cstrong\u003eongoing\u003c/strong\u003e access: every update Harald receives about the PCs\u0027 progress flows straight to the enemy.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs will not learn the source until Beat 8, when Gragnir reveals the truth.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eOutcomes\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBy the end of this beat, the PCs should have:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eUnderstood the existential crisis: Ever-Embers dying, Keepers dead, dead rising.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAccepted the mission: find Kaelen and bring her back.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMet Harald (desperate, honest, out of options) and Gragnir (cryptic, blunt, urgent).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLearned the next step: find Lew Tosferd in Stairwatch.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFelt the weight of secrecy and paranoia.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBeen unknowingly compromisedГўв‚¬вЂќDreyfus heard every word and remains at HaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs side, feeding intelligence to GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs network.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#2a6a2a;\"\u003eBeat 3 Гўв‚¬вЂќ Victory Point Summary\u003c/h4\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eNo VP-earning encounters this beat. Total: 0 VP.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#2a6a2a;\"\u003eBeat 3 Гўв‚¬вЂќ Victory Point Summary\u003c/h4\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eNo VP-earning encounters this beat. Total: 0 VP.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eTransition to Beat 4\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs must leave Hrafnborg before dawn, using the forged papers to pass the Chainwardens\u0027 outer checkpoints. Harald cannot help them leaveГўв‚¬вЂќhis involvement must remain invisible.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eProceed to \u003cstrong\u003eBeat 4: The Road to Stairwatch\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","markdown":null},"src":null,"system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"sort":30,"flags":{},"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"exportSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"draw-steel","systemVersion":"0.10.0","createdTime":0,"modifiedTime":0,"lastModifiedBy":null}},{"_id":"RTFPAGE000000021","name":"Beat 4 Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Road to Stairwatch","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 1\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eDuration:\u003c/strong\u003e 1Гўв‚¬вЂњ2 sessions\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eLocation:\u003c/strong\u003e Hrafnborg (departure) ГўвЂ вЂ™ Lantern Road ГўвЂ вЂ™ Frostfen Marshes ГўвЂ вЂ™ MidgardГўв‚¬в„ўs Shield ГўвЂ вЂ™ TitanГўв‚¬в„ўs Stair ГўвЂ вЂ™ Stairwatch\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eKey NPCs:\u003c/strong\u003e Warden-Sergeant Eirik Greyhand (Greypass), Bryn Ketilsdottir (Hollow Waystation)\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Two Hard Montage Tests, combat encounter, negotiation encounter, narrative interludes\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eTone:\u003c/strong\u003e Isolation, hardship, dwindling warmth, the road is the enemy\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1a3a; color:#c8c8e8; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4a4ac8;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVP Status Гўв‚¬вЂќ Entering This Beat\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cstrong\u003eTotal VP (max):\u003c/strong\u003e 2 | \u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 | \u003cstrong\u003eVP into Level:\u003c/strong\u003e 2\u003cbr\u003e\u003cem style=\"font-size:0.9em;\"\u003eBeats 4a (Coastal Road) and 4b (Mountain Road) play in sequence - both contribute VP.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1a3a; color:#c8c8e8; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4a4ac8;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVP Status Гўв‚¬вЂќ Entering This Beat\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cstrong\u003eTotal VP (max):\u003c/strong\u003e 2 | \u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 | \u003cstrong\u003eVP into Level:\u003c/strong\u003e 2\u003cbr\u003e\u003cem style=\"font-size:0.9em;\"\u003eBeats 4a (Coastal Road) and 4b (Mountain Road) play in sequence - both contribute VP.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2\u003eOverview\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs slip out of Hrafnborg before dawn with forged papers and the KingГўв‚¬в„ўs supplies. Ahead: \u003cstrong\u003etwo hundred miles\u003c/strong\u003e of failing roads, frozen marshland, Chainwarden checkpoints, mountain passes, and Fimbulwinter stormsГўв‚¬вЂќall while maintaining the secrecy of their mission.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis is a long, dangerous journey. Travel rates vary with terrain: 24 miles/day on maintained roads, 18 miles/day through hindered ground (marshes, foothills), and 12 miles/day in severe mountain passesГўв‚¬вЂќaveraging ~20 miles/day across the full route. The trek takes \u003cstrong\u003e8Гўв‚¬вЂњ10 days\u003c/strong\u003e. The beat is divided into two montage tests separated by encounters, building a rhythm of endurance, danger, and discovery. By the time the PCs reach Stairwatch, they should feel every mile.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 1: The Departure\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eSГѓВіlmГѓВЎnuГѓВ°ur 6th. Dawn.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou leave Hrafnborg before dawn, slipping through the Chainwardens\u0027 outer checkpoints with forged merchants\u0027 papers and the taste of salt pork still on your tongues. The Lantern Road stretches north into a world of grey ice and stunted pines.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe KingГўв‚¬в„ўs instructions are clear: reach Stairwatch. Find Lew Tosferd. Trust no one.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe cold doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt care about instructions.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAs the PCs pass through the outer checkpoint:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Chainwarden on duty is half-asleep and waves them through with barely a glance. (This changes if the party dawdled or made noise in the KingГўв‚¬в„ўs halls.)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe road beyond the walls is immediately different: the stones are cracked, weeds push through ice, and the mile-markers are buried or missing.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe sound of the city fades within minutes. The only sounds are wind, their own breathing, and the crunch of frost under boots.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: Leaving Hrafnborg\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAs the PCs pass through the outer checkpoint, note that Dreyfus is \u003cstrong\u003enot\u003c/strong\u003e hereГўв‚¬вЂќhe is back in HaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs chambers. But every detail of the PCs\u0027 mission, destination, and route was spoken aloud in HaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs sitting room while the hound listened.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWithin hours of the PCs\u0027 departure, that intelligence begins flowing through GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs Wyrd-channels to agents in the field. The PCs donГўв‚¬в„ўt know this yet.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 2: Journey Context\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBefore beginning the first montage test, set the scene with a full description of the route:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eJourney:\u003c/strong\u003e Hrafnborg ГўвЂ вЂ™ Lantern Road north ГўвЂ вЂ™ Frostfen Marshes ГўвЂ вЂ™ MidgardГўв‚¬в„ўs Shield foothills ГўвЂ вЂ™ Chainwarden Toll at Greypass ГўвЂ вЂ™ Mountain Road ГўвЂ вЂ™ TitanГўв‚¬в„ўs Stair ГўвЂ вЂ™ Stairwatch descent\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eDistance:\u003c/strong\u003e ~200 miles\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eDuration:\u003c/strong\u003e ~8Гўв‚¬вЂњ10 days through Fimbulwinter terrain\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eCalendar:\u003c/strong\u003e Departure SГѓВіlmГѓВЎnuГѓВ°ur 6th; estimated arrival SГѓВіlmГѓВЎnuГѓВ°ur 15thГўв‚¬вЂњ16th\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eTerrain:\u003c/strong\u003e Coastal Belt (frozen farmland) ГўвЂ вЂ™ Marshlands ГўвЂ вЂ™ Interior Belt boundary (MidgardГўв‚¬в„ўs Shield range)\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Route\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDays 1Гўв‚¬вЂњ2 Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Lantern Road:\u003c/strong\u003e Once a well-maintained highway connecting Hrafnborg to the interior towns. Now itГўв‚¬в„ўs a ruin: mile-markers buried, road-signs stolen for firewood, sections impassable with snow or debris. Chainwarden patrols tax travellers in Heat (fuel rations) or Word (travel permits). The land is flat, frozen farmlandГўв‚¬вЂќopen sky, cutting wind, and the Ever-EmberГўв‚¬в„ўs warmth fading with every mile.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDay 3 Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Frostfen Marshes:\u003c/strong\u003e Where the Lantern Road crosses the old fenlands, the terrain turns treacherous. The marshes havenГўв‚¬в„ўt frozen solidГўв‚¬вЂќthe ice is thin in patches, the reeds hide pockets of black water, and the footcauseway is half-collapsed. The road narrows to a single crumbling path through frozen bog. Something about the Frostfen feels \u003cstrong\u003ewrong\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќthe cold here is different, wetter, heavier, as if the land itself is exhaling.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDays 4Гўв‚¬вЂњ5 Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Refugee Road:\u003c/strong\u003e Beyond the Frostfen, the Lantern Road meets the HerdwegГўв‚¬вЂќthe old drovers\u0027 highway running east from the Interior Belt. The intersection is choked with refugees fleeing south toward Hrafnborg. Families, merchants, whole villages on the move. The PCs are heading \u003cstrong\u003enorth\u003c/strong\u003e when everyone else is heading \u003cstrong\u003esouth\u003c/strong\u003e. Questions will be asked.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDays 5Гўв‚¬вЂњ6 Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Chainwarden Toll at Greypass:\u003c/strong\u003e Where the road enters the foothills of MidgardГўв‚¬в„ўs Shield, a fortified checkpoint controls passage. The Toll was built to manage trade; now it manages panic. Chainwardens in cold-bitten armour inspect papers, confiscate contraband, and demand tariffs that grow steeper every month. This is a negotiation encounter.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDays 6Гўв‚¬вЂњ8 Гўв‚¬вЂќ MidgardГўв‚¬в„ўs Shield Foothills:\u003c/strong\u003e Rocky, wind-scoured ground. The treeline thins. Abandoned crofts and shepherds\u0027 shelters dot the landscapeГўв‚¬вЂќsome still have walls, none have roofs. The weather turns from \"miserable\" to \"lethal.\" The road climbs steadily. The air thins. Storm-fronts roll in without warning.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDays 8Гўв‚¬вЂњ9 Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Mountain Road:\u003c/strong\u003e The ancient road that climbs into the TitanГўв‚¬в„ўs Stair proper. Built by giants, if the stories are trueГўв‚¬вЂќthe flagstones are enormous, cracked but enduring. Avalanche debris, rockfalls, and ice-slick switchbacks make the ascent exhausting. A partially collapsed stone bridge spans a gorge halfway up.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDay 10 Гўв‚¬вЂќ TitanГўв‚¬в„ўs Stair \u0026amp; Descent:\u003c/strong\u003e The final push: a narrow ice-choked switchback pass through the highest point of MidgardГўв‚¬в„ўs Shield. The wind is a physical force. The descent on the far side is steep but windlessГўв‚¬вЂќa blessed reliefГўв‚¬вЂќand StairwatchГўв‚¬в„ўs lights are visible from the top.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eWhat the PCs Notice\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAs they travel, seed these observations:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Ever-EmberГўв‚¬в„ўs warmth faded \u003cstrong\u003efast\u003c/strong\u003e once they left HrafnborgГўв‚¬в„ўs radius. The cold deepens with every mile.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eRoadside shrines to Yggdrasil appear every few milesГўв‚¬вЂќsmall cairns with hollow centres where flame-offerings should sit. Every single one is extinguished. Some have been for weeks.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWildlife is wrong: no birds, no hares, no foxes. The only tracks are old. Something has driven everything south or underground.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe people they pass on the road donГўв‚¬в„ўt make eye contact. They walk fast, heads down, clutching whatever they can carry. No one stops to talk.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe sky doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt change colour. Dawn and dusk are the same shade of iron-grey. Only the lightГўв‚¬в„ўs intensity tells you what time it is.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAt one point, they pass a farmstead. No smoke from the chimney. The door is open. Snow has drifted inside. (If they investigate: the family left in haste. Food is still on the tableГўв‚¬вЂќfrozen solid.)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 3: Montage Test 1 Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Coastal Road\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Montage Test (Coastal Road) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 VP on success, 1 VP partial, 0 VP failure\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Montage Test (Coastal Road) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 VP on success, 1 VP partial, 0 VP failure\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCovers Days 1Гўв‚¬вЂњ4: Hrafnborg ГўвЂ вЂ™ Lantern Road ГўвЂ вЂ™ Frostfen Marshes ГўвЂ вЂ™ Refugee Road junction.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eParty Size Adjustment (4 heroes):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDifficulty\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eSuccess Limit\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eFailure Limit\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHard (adjusted)\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e6\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e2\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRounds:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 montage test rounds (each hero acts once per round; 8 total individual tests).\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRules Reminder:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEach hero uses a \u003cstrong\u003edifferent skill\u003c/strong\u003e for each test (no repeating skills across the montage).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSkills grant +2 to the test (not an edge). Edges and banes apply as normal.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf a hero has a clever non-test action (using an item, ability, or resource), it can earn automatic successes at your discretion.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eA hero can \u003cstrong\u003eassist\u003c/strong\u003e another heroГўв‚¬в„ўs test instead of making their own. The assisting hero must use a different skill than the lead. Roll a power roll: tier 1 = bane on leadГўв‚¬в„ўs test; tier 2 = edge; tier 3 = double edge.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eRound 1 Sample Tests\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eChallenge\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCharacteristic\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDescription\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eNavigate the failing Lantern Road\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eReason\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eRead buried markers, recall old maps, plot detours around collapsed sections. The road splits and rejoinsГўв‚¬вЂќchoosing the wrong fork adds hours.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eEndure the cold and ration supplies\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eMight\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eResist frostbite, carry gear through snowdrifts, ford frozen streams. The supplies must last ten days, not three.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAvoid or deceive early Chainwarden patrols\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePresence\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eA roving patrol stops the party. Talk past them with the forged papers; deflect suspicion about heading north when everyone else goes south.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eScout for safe passage through the Frostfen\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eIntuition\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe marsh-ice is unreliable. Find the old causeway stonesГўв‚¬вЂќburied under frost but still solidГўв‚¬вЂќor risk falling through into black water.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eNavigate the Frostfen at night\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAgility\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe party must cross the worst section of marsh after dark (the ice is harder at night). Balance on ice-slick causeway stones, leap frozen tussocks, avoid thin spots.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eRead weather signs to avoid a squall\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eIntuition\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eA Fimbulwinter squall can drop visibility to armГўв‚¬в„ўs length in minutes. Reading the cloud-patterns and wind-shift gives the party time to shelter before it hits.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eRound 1 Interlude: The Extinguished Shrine\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBy the roadside, a cairn of stacked stones stands waist-high. Its centre is hollowГўв‚¬вЂќa bowl-shaped depression where a flame should burn. The ash is cold. Dead wildflowers, frost-brittle, lie scattered around the base. Someone left offerings. No one came to tend the fire.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe cairnГўв‚¬в„ўs keystone is carved with a single runic word. It reads: \u003cem\u003eRemember.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA moment for the PCs to reflect on what the Ever-Embers mean. If anyone makes an offering (even just a breath warmed into their hands and placed in the basin), the cairnГўв‚¬в„ўs keystone warmsГўв‚¬вЂќjust for a momentГўв‚¬вЂќthen goes cold again. Yggdrasil is listening, but too weak to answer.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eRound 2 Sample Tests\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eChallenge\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCharacteristic\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDescription\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eFind shelter in the Frostfen margins\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eReason\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe flat marshland offers no natural shelter. Locate an old peat-cutterГўв‚¬в„ўs hut, an overturned barge, or a reed-bank thick enough to break the wind.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCross the Herdweg junction without attention\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePresence / Agility\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe junction is crowded with refugee columns. The PCs need to cross \u003cstrong\u003ethrough\u003c/strong\u003e the flow heading north without drawing questions. Why are young, healthy travellers heading \u003cstrong\u003etoward\u003c/strong\u003e the danger?\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eResist marsh-sickness\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eMight\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe FrostfenГўв‚¬в„ўs air carries something foulГўв‚¬вЂќnot disease, exactly, but a heaviness in the lungs. A character who fails wakes the next morning with a rattling cough and bloodshot eyes. (ГўЛ†вЂ™1 to Might tests until a rest.)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAvoid refugee columns\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePresence / Agility\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eFamilies fleeing south toward Hrafnborg clog the road. The PCs need to avoid drawing attention. Questions about their directionГўв‚¬вЂќheading \u003cstrong\u003enorth\u003c/strong\u003e when everyone else flees \u003cstrong\u003esouth\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќwill raise suspicion.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCalm a panicked pack-mule\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePresence\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe mule balks at a frozen corpse on the road and threatens to bolt with half the supplies.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eKeep morale up at camp\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePresence\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe landscape is crushing. Four days of grey-white emptiness and freezing wind. The PCs need to keep each other from despair. Stories, songs, small comforts.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eRound 2 Interlude: The Drowned Village\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Lantern Road crosses what was once a shallow lakeГўв‚¬вЂќyou can tell by the reed-stumps and the change in ground texture. At the lakeГўв‚¬в„ўs centre, barely visible through frost-haze, rooftops jut from the ice. A village, flooded and frozen.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe ice is clear enough to see through in places. Below: a market square, complete with stalls and carts. A temple spire, its bell still visible. Streets and doorways andГўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eMovement. Something shifts below the ice. Not a fish. Something with \u003cstrong\u003ehands\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs should \u003cstrong\u003enot\u003c/strong\u003e investigate. If they do: the ice creaks ominously, and whatever is below tracks their movement across the surface. A easy Reason test identifies this as a draugr nestГўв‚¬вЂќthe village died and the residents didnГўв‚¬в„ўt leave. Breaking the ice would release dozens of them.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs are wise enough to move on, they gain useful information: the dead are \u003cstrong\u003eeverywhere\u003c/strong\u003e, not just in obvious battlefields and barrows. The Frostfen is a cemetery that doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt know itГўв‚¬в„ўs dead.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eMontage 1 Outcomes\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003ch4 style=\"color:#66ff66;\"\u003eTotal Success (5+ successes before failure limit)\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe party crosses the Frostfen and reaches the Herdweg junction intact.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEarn \u003cstrong\u003e2 Victories\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSupplies are holding. Morale is manageable.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDreyfusГўв‚¬в„ўs intelligence from Hrafnborg hasnГўв‚¬в„ўt reached field agents yetГўв‚¬вЂќdelay the first Grafvitnir Pressure Check by one scene.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch4 style=\"color:#ffff66;\"\u003ePartial Success (failure limit hit, but 2+ more successes than failures)\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eArrive at the Herdweg junction, but at cost. Choose one:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHeat cost:\u003c/strong\u003e Lost a day navigating the Frostfen. One dayГўв‚¬в„ўs rations consumed for no progress. (ГўЛ†вЂ™1 dayГўв‚¬в„ўs supplies.)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHealth cost:\u003c/strong\u003e Marsh-sickness. One PC has a persistent cough (ГўЛ†вЂ™1 to Might tests until a respite in a warm building).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRemedy available:\u003c/strong\u003e PCs who forage successfully in the marshes (medium Intuition test) discover marsh-root \u0026mdash; the raw ingredient for @UUID[Item.SVH0MarshPoult01]{Frostfen Marsh-Root Poultice}. An herbalist PC can prepare one during a rest.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWord cost:\u003c/strong\u003e A refugee recognised the KingГўв‚¬в„ўs seal on the forged papers and spread the word. The PCs\u0027 cover is thinner. (+1 to future Grafvitnir Pressure Checks.)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEarn \u003cstrong\u003e1 Victory\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch4 style=\"color:#ff6666;\"\u003eTotal Failure\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe party still reaches the junction, but arrives \u003cstrong\u003ecompromised\u003c/strong\u003e:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLose 2 days\u0027 rations \u003cstrong\u003eand\u003c/strong\u003e one PC has marsh-sickness.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs agents know exactly where the party is. The next Pressure Check triggers automatically at 5+.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNo Victories earned. Director gains 3 Malice for the next encounter.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch3\u003eMontage 1 Failure Encounter: Chainwarden Patrol (Optional)\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Combat (Optional - triggered on montage failure) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on victory\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Combat (Optional - triggered on montage failure) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on victory\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eThis encounter triggers on a Total Failure or at the Director\u0027s discretion after a Partial Success. A Chainwarden patrol has been tipped off by Ashwright informants or Pale Maw agents. They are waiting at a narrow bottleneck on the Herdweg approachГўв‚¬вЂќa stone bridge over a frozen ravine.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe road narrows ahead. A stone bridge spans a frozen creek bedГўв‚¬вЂќold stone, JГѓВ¶tunfolk work, still solid after centuries. On the far side, five figures in grey cloaks wait in a loose line. Chain links glint on their tabards. The lead figure raises a gauntleted hand.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eГўв‚¬Е“Halt. Toll authority, road inspection. Papers.Гўв‚¬Вќ\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe tone is wrong. This isn\u0027t bored routine. They were waiting for you.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat\u0027s really happening:\u003c/strong\u003e Warden-Captain Halvard received a raven from Ashwright\u0027s network with a description of the party. He\u0027s been told to detain themГўв‚¬вЂќalive, if possible, but he has latitude. Halvard is a pragmatist who has been bribed, not a zealot. If the fight goes badly, he\u0027ll try to retreat.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eNegotiation possible:\u003c/strong\u003e If the PCs try to talk their way out (medium Presence test), they can avoid combatГўв‚¬вЂќbut only if they haven\u0027t already antagonised the Chainwardens at the toll. If they dealt with Eirik\u0027s toll peacefully, they get an edge on this test.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eEncounter Setup\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEncounter Difficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate (EV 21 for 4 heroes)\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eHard Variant:\u003c/strong\u003e Add Warden-Captain Halvard (EV 33 total)\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eStandard Composition:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e1 Chainwarden Enforcer (Platoon Defender)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e1 Chainwarden Artillerist (Platoon Artillery)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e2 Chainwarden Militia (Horde Brute)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e4 Chainwarden Guards (Minion Brute)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHard Composition:\u003c/strong\u003e Add Warden-Captain Halvard (Leader)\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTerrain:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eStone Bridge:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 squares wide, 6 squares long. Railings provide half cover.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFrozen Ravine:\u003c/strong\u003e 3 squares deep. Falling deals 10 damage. Climbing out requires a easy Might test.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTree Line:\u003c/strong\u003e The artillerist starts in the trees 10 squares back from the bridge, providing three-quarters cover.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTactics:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe Enforcer holds the bridge chokepoint, taunting the first PC across.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe Artillerist fires from the tree line, exploiting their range and cover-ignoring shots.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe Militia flank around the ravine edges to hit squishier targets.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe Guards swarm whoever crosses the bridge.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eIf Halvard is present, he uses \u003cstrong\u003eWarden\u0027s Warrant\u003c/strong\u003e to mark the most dangerous PC, then sweeps with \u003cstrong\u003eChain-Flail Sweep\u003c/strong\u003e when the party clusters.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eHuman Malice Features\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThese Chainwardens use the \u003cstrong\u003eHuman\u003c/strong\u003e keyword and share the following Malice features:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAlchemical Device\u003c/strong\u003e (3 Malice, Maneuver): \u003cem\u003eArea, Magic, Ranged\u003c/em\u003e | 3 cube within 10 | Each enemy and object in the area. Deals 4/6/9 corruption damage; slowed (save ends) / slowed (save ends) / restrained (save ends). CanГўв‚¬в„ўt be used by a minion.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eExploit Opening\u003c/strong\u003e (5 Malice, Triggered): Trigger: A ChainwardenГўв‚¬в„ўs turn starts. Each Chainwarden acting this turn gains an edge on abilities until the end of their turn, or has a double edge on any ability that targets an enemy affected by a condition.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eStaying Power\u003c/strong\u003e (7 Malice, Triggered): Trigger: A ChainwardenГўв‚¬в„ўs turn starts. Each non-minion Chainwarden in the encounter regains Stamina equal to 5 ГѓвЂ” their level.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eChainwarden Guard\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eChainwarden Guard\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHuman, Humanoid, Chainwarden\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eLevel 1 Minion Brute\u003c/strong\u003e | \u003cstrong\u003eEV 3 for four minions\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSize:\u003c/strong\u003e 1M | \u003cstrong\u003eSpeed:\u003c/strong\u003e 5 | \u003cstrong\u003eStamina:\u003c/strong\u003e 5 | \u003cstrong\u003eStability:\u003c/strong\u003e 0 | \u003cstrong\u003eFree Strike:\u003c/strong\u003e 2\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eImmunity:\u003c/strong\u003e corruption 1, psychic 1\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eWith Captain:\u003c/strong\u003e +2 bonus to speed.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMight\u003c/strong\u003e +2, \u003cstrong\u003eAgility\u003c/strong\u003e +0, \u003cstrong\u003eReason\u003c/strong\u003e +0, \u003cstrong\u003eIntuition\u003c/strong\u003e +0, \u003cstrong\u003ePresence\u003c/strong\u003e +0\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHalberd\u003c/strong\u003e ГўвЂ”вЂ  2d10 + 2 Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003eSignature Ability, Main action\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eMelee, Strike, Weapon\u003c/em\u003e | Melee 2 | One creature or object per minion\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eГўвЂ°В¤11: 2 damage\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e12Гўв‚¬вЂњ16: 4 damage\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e17+: 5 damage\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eEffect: If the guard is flanked, they can make a free strike against a different target adjacent to them.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSupernatural Insight\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ The guard ignores concealment if it\u0027s granted by a supernatural effect.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eChainwarden Militia\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eChainwarden Militia\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHuman, Humanoid, Chainwarden\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eLevel 1 Horde Brute\u003c/strong\u003e | \u003cstrong\u003eEV 3\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSize:\u003c/strong\u003e 1M | \u003cstrong\u003eSpeed:\u003c/strong\u003e 5 | \u003cstrong\u003eStamina:\u003c/strong\u003e 20 | \u003cstrong\u003eStability:\u003c/strong\u003e 0 | \u003cstrong\u003eFree Strike:\u003c/strong\u003e 2\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eImmunity:\u003c/strong\u003e corruption 1, psychic 1\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMight\u003c/strong\u003e +2, \u003cstrong\u003eAgility\u003c/strong\u003e +0, \u003cstrong\u003eReason\u003c/strong\u003e +0, \u003cstrong\u003eIntuition\u003c/strong\u003e +0, \u003cstrong\u003ePresence\u003c/strong\u003e ГўЛ†вЂ™1\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBillhook\u003c/strong\u003e ГўвЂ”вЂ  2d10 + 2 Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003eSignature Ability, Main action\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eMelee, Strike, Weapon\u003c/em\u003e | Melee 2 | One creature or object\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eГўвЂ°В¤11: 3 damage\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e12Гўв‚¬вЂњ16: 5 damage; push 1 square\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e17+: 7 damage; m\u0026lt;2] prone\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWarden\u0027s Resolve\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003e1 Malice, Maneuver\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nEffect: The militia and each ally adjacent to them gain +2 to stability until end of round.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSupernatural Insight\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ The militia ignores concealment if it\u0027s granted by a supernatural effect.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eChainwarden Artillerist\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eChainwarden Artillerist\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHuman, Humanoid, Chainwarden\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eLevel 1 Platoon Artillery\u003c/strong\u003e | \u003cstrong\u003eEV 6\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSize:\u003c/strong\u003e 1M | \u003cstrong\u003eSpeed:\u003c/strong\u003e 5 | \u003cstrong\u003eStamina:\u003c/strong\u003e 20 | \u003cstrong\u003eStability:\u003c/strong\u003e 0 | \u003cstrong\u003eFree Strike:\u003c/strong\u003e 4\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eImmunity:\u003c/strong\u003e corruption 1, psychic 1\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMight\u003c/strong\u003e +0, \u003cstrong\u003eAgility\u003c/strong\u003e +2, \u003cstrong\u003eReason\u003c/strong\u003e +1, \u003cstrong\u003eIntuition\u003c/strong\u003e +1, \u003cstrong\u003ePresence\u003c/strong\u003e +0\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eArbalest\u003c/strong\u003e ГўвЂ”вЂ  2d10 + 2 Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003eSignature Ability, Main action\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eRanged, Strike, Weapon\u003c/em\u003e | Ranged 15 | One creature or object\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eГўвЂ°В¤11: 6 damage\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e12Гўв‚¬вЂњ16: 9 damage\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e17+: 12 damage\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eEffect: This ability ignores cover and concealment.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e3 Malice: This ability targets one additional creature or object.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAlchemical Bolt\u003c/strong\u003e ГўвЂ”вЂ  2d10 + 2 Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003e3 Malice, Main action\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eArea, Magic, Ranged\u003c/em\u003e | 3 cube within 10 | Each creature in the area\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eГўвЂ°В¤11: 4 damage; slowed (EoT)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e12Гўв‚¬вЂњ16: 6 damage; slowed (save ends)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e17+: 8 damage; restrained (save ends)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eEffect: The area becomes difficult terrain until the end of the encounter.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCovering Fire\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003eTriggered action\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eRanged\u003c/em\u003e | Ranged 15 | One enemy (the triggering enemy)\u003cbr\u003e\nTrigger: An enemy within distance willingly moves.\u003cbr\u003e\nEffect: At any point during the movement, the artillerist makes a free strike against the target.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSupernatural Insight\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ The artillerist ignores concealment if it\u0027s granted by a supernatural effect.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eChainwarden Enforcer\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eChainwarden Enforcer\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHuman, Humanoid, Chainwarden\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eLevel 1 Platoon Defender\u003c/strong\u003e | \u003cstrong\u003eEV 6\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSize:\u003c/strong\u003e 1M | \u003cstrong\u003eSpeed:\u003c/strong\u003e 5 | \u003cstrong\u003eStamina:\u003c/strong\u003e 40 | \u003cstrong\u003eStability:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 | \u003cstrong\u003eFree Strike:\u003c/strong\u003e 4\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eImmunity:\u003c/strong\u003e corruption 1, psychic 1\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMight\u003c/strong\u003e +2, \u003cstrong\u003eAgility\u003c/strong\u003e +0, \u003cstrong\u003eReason\u003c/strong\u003e +1, \u003cstrong\u003eIntuition\u003c/strong\u003e +0, \u003cstrong\u003ePresence\u003c/strong\u003e +0\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eChain-Mace\u003c/strong\u003e ГўвЂ”вЂ  2d10 + 2 Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003eSignature Ability, Main action\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eMelee, Strike, Weapon\u003c/em\u003e | Melee 1 | One creature or object\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eГўвЂ°В¤11: 5 damage\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e12Гўв‚¬вЂњ16: 8 damage\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e17+: 11 damage; m\u0026lt;2] target has double bane on next power roll\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eEffect: Target is taunted (EoT).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eStand Fast\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ Whenever an adjacent creature the enforcer has taunted deals damage to a creature other than the enforcer, the enforcer can make a free strike against them.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOverwhelm\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ An enemy who starts their turn adjacent to the enforcer can\u0027t shift.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSupernatural Insight\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ The enforcer ignores concealment if it\u0027s granted by a supernatural effect.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eWarden-Captain Halvard (Hard Variant)\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eWarden-Captain Halvard\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHuman, Humanoid, Chainwarden\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eLevel 1 Leader\u003c/strong\u003e | \u003cstrong\u003eEV 12\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSize:\u003c/strong\u003e 1M | \u003cstrong\u003eSpeed:\u003c/strong\u003e 5 | \u003cstrong\u003eStamina:\u003c/strong\u003e 80 | \u003cstrong\u003eStability:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 | \u003cstrong\u003eFree Strike:\u003c/strong\u003e 4\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eImmunity:\u003c/strong\u003e corruption 2, psychic 2\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMight\u003c/strong\u003e +3, \u003cstrong\u003eAgility\u003c/strong\u003e +2, \u003cstrong\u003eReason\u003c/strong\u003e +2, \u003cstrong\u003eIntuition\u003c/strong\u003e +0, \u003cstrong\u003ePresence\u003c/strong\u003e +2\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eChain-Flail Sweep\u003c/strong\u003e ГўвЂ”вЂ  2d10 + 3 Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003eSignature Ability, Main action\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eArea, Weapon\u003c/em\u003e | 1 burst | Each enemy in the area\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eГўвЂ°В¤11: 3 damage; m\u0026lt;1] slowed (save ends)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e12Гўв‚¬вЂњ16: 6 damage; m\u0026lt;2] slowed (save ends)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e17+: 8 damage; m\u0026lt;3] slowed (save ends)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eEffect: One ally within 10 squares can make a free strike.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e1 Malice: One ally within 10 squares can use their signature ability instead.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWarden\u0027s Warrant\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003eManeuver\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eRanged\u003c/em\u003e | Ranged 10 | One enemy\u003cbr\u003e\nEffect: The target is marked until the start of the captain\u0027s next turn. The captain and each of their allies gain an edge on abilities used against targets marked by the captain.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eShield Wall\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003eTriggered action\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eMelee\u003c/em\u003e | Melee 1 | Self or one ally\u003cbr\u003e\nTrigger: A creature makes a strike against the captain or an ally adjacent to them.\u003cbr\u003e\nEffect: The damage is halved.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEnd Effect\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ At the end of each of their turns, the captain can take 5 damage to end one effect on them that can be ended by a saving throw. This damage can\u0027t be reduced in any way.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSupernatural Insight\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ The captain ignores concealment if it\u0027s granted by a supernatural effect.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eForm Up!\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003eVillain Action 1\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nEffect: The captain shifts up to their speed. During or after this movement, they can use Chain-Flail Sweep twice.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDisperse!\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003eVillain Action 2\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eArea, Magic\u003c/em\u003e | 5 burst | Each enemy in the area\u003cbr\u003e\nEffect: The captain slides each target up to 5 squares.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBy Authority of the Chain!\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003eVillain Action 3\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nEffect: Each ally within 10 squares can move up to their speed and make a free strike.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003ePatrol Aftermath\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs \u003cstrong\u003ewin\u003c/strong\u003e the fight:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSearch the bodies: Halvard (if present) carries a sealed letter from Гўв‚¬Е“V.A.Гўв‚¬Вќ (Voss Ashwright) describing the party and offering 50 gold for their detention. This is a key intelligence findГўв‚¬вЂќevidence that the Chainwardens have been compromised.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe guards carry Chain-Warden road tokensГўв‚¬вЂќuseful for bluffing through future checkpoints.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eEarn \u003cstrong\u003e1 Victory\u003c/strong\u003e for defeating the patrol.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs \u003cstrong\u003enegotiate\u003c/strong\u003e past the patrol:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHalvard lets them through but sends a rider ahead. +1 to future Grafvitnir Pressure Checks.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eNo Victory earned, but no resources spent.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs \u003cstrong\u003eflee\u003c/strong\u003e:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThey must take a 1-day detour through rough terrain. Lose 1 day\u0027s rations.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe patrol reports their position. +2 to the next Grafvitnir Pressure Check.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 4: Point of Interest Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Hollow Waystation\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBetween the first montage and the Chainwarden Toll, the party encounters this location. It can serve as a rest stop or a trap.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe road widens at a stone-built waystationГўв‚¬вЂќone of the old Embertender rest-houses that once dotted the major routes. The roof is intact. The walls are solid. Smoke rises from the chimney.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSomeone is inside.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eInside: \u003cstrong\u003eBryn Ketilsdottir\u003c/strong\u003e, a former Embertender who abandoned her post when her settlementГўв‚¬в„ўs Ever-Ember went out. SheГўв‚¬в„ўs been living in the waystation for three weeks, burning furniture for warmth, rationing a dwindling supply of dried fish.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBryn is not hostile, but she is deeply ashamed. She failed her oath. The Ember she tended flickered and died in the nightГўв‚¬вЂќno attack, no catastrophe, it justГўв‚¬В¦Гўв‚¬вЂ№ stopped. She couldnГўв‚¬в„ўt bear to face her community.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs offer compassion: Bryn shares what she knows. The Ever-Embers are going out \u003cstrong\u003ewithout external cause\u003c/strong\u003e. Three more have failed since hersГўв‚¬вЂќshe heard the news from refugees on the road. \"ItГўв‚¬в„ўs not the cold killing them,\" she says. \"ItГўв‚¬в„ўs something underneath. The ground is sick.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs push her for information (easy Presence test): Bryn describes the night her Ember died. \"I heard a sound. Not from outsideГўв‚¬вЂќfrom \u003cstrong\u003ebelow\u003c/strong\u003e. Like something exhaling. The flame bent toward the floor and went out. The stone was warm for an hour afterward, as if the fire had sunk into the earth.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs share food: Bryn is overwhelmed. She insists on giving them her last useful possessionГўв‚¬вЂќa \u003cstrong\u003eChainwarden toll-token\u003c/strong\u003e (worth one free passage through a checkpoint, saving Heat or Word at the Greypass Toll).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs help Bryn secure the waystation (or if they show genuine kindness), she also offers a battered iron lantern from the waystation\u0026rsquo;s stores: the @UUID[Item.SVH00WayLantrn01]{Hollow Waystation Lantern}. \u0026ldquo;It was the Embertender\u0026rsquo;s before mine. The flame won\u0026rsquo;t die in the wind. Take it \u0026mdash; I don\u0026rsquo;t deserve to carry their light.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: Bryn\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBryn is not a quest-giver. She is a \u003cstrong\u003ewindow into the world\u003c/strong\u003e. Her story illustrates what Fimbulwinter does to ordinary peopleГўв‚¬вЂќit breaks them not through violence, but through grinding, inexorable failure. If the PCs are kind to her, they earn a toll-token and a contact who may reappear in Act 2 (she can reach Hrafnborg and serve the King). If they ignore her, sheГўв‚¬в„ўs just another ghost on the road.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 5: Negotiation Encounter Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Chainwarden Toll at Greypass\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Negotiation | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on success\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Negotiation | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on success\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eApproximately SГѓВіlmГѓВЎnuГѓВ°ur 10th. Day 5 of the journey.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eContext\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhere the Lantern Road enters the foothills of MidgardГўв‚¬в„ўs Shield, the Chainwardens maintain a fortified toll crossing called \u003cstrong\u003eGreypass\u003c/strong\u003e. It controls the only maintained road through the lower mountains. The toll was built to manage trade caravans; now it manages desperation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe road narrows between two bluffs of dark stone. A wall of stacked timber and iron bars blocks the pathГўв‚¬вЂќnot a military fortification, but close enough. A gate. A guardhouse. A flag bearing the Chainwarden sigil: a broken chain, re-forged.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eTwo wardens stand at the gate, wrapped in furs over mail. One holds a ledger. The other holds a spear.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Papers,\" says the one with the ledger. It is not a request.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Encounter\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis is a \u003cstrong\u003eModerate Negotiation\u003c/strong\u003e with the toll commander, \u003cstrong\u003eWarden-Sergeant Eirik Greyhand\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eInterest\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePatience\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e2\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e3\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMotivations:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEirik wants order.\u003c/strong\u003e He is not corruptГўв‚¬вЂќhe is \u003cstrong\u003eexhausted\u003c/strong\u003e. The toll is underfunded, understaffed, and overwhelmed. He wants travellers to follow procedure so he can maintain the fiction that the system works.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEirik wants supplies.\u003c/strong\u003e The toll garrison hasnГўв‚¬в„ўt received a resupply in weeks. Heat (fuel, rations) is more valuable to him than coin.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEirik wants to go home.\u003c/strong\u003e He has a family in Hrafnborg. He hasnГўв‚¬в„ўt heard from them in a month. Any newsГўв‚¬вЂќeven bad newsГўв‚¬вЂќis worth something.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat the PCs Want:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePassage through the toll without their cover being blown.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIdeally, intelligence about the road ahead (mountain conditions, bandit activity, undead sightings).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf they have BrynГўв‚¬в„ўs toll-token, they can present it for automatic free passage for one person. The rest must still negotiate.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eNegotiation Beats\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eArgument\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eEffect\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePresent the forged papers (Presence)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eEirik inspects them. TheyГўв‚¬в„ўre good forgeries. Tier 2+: heГўв‚¬в„ўs satisfied. Tier 1: he notices the seal is slightly wrongГўв‚¬вЂќ\"This isnГўв‚¬в„ўt the standard merchant cipher. Where did you get these?\" (+1 Interest, as he becomes suspicious but also curious.)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eOffer rations or fuel (Heat currency)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThis speaks directly to EirikГўв‚¬в„ўs need. Tier 2+: earns 2 Interest immediately. Eirik waves them through and offers road intelligence as thanks.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eShare news of Hrafnborg (Presence)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eTell Eirik the city still stands, the Ever-Ember still burns, and the King is active. Tier 2+: EirikГўв‚¬в„ўs shoulders drop with relief. +1 Interest. He becomes notably friendlier.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eBluff a military connection (Presence)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eClaim to be on Chainwarden business. Tier 3 only: Eirik buys it and provides an escort for the next 5 miles. Tier 1Гўв‚¬вЂњ2: Eirik knows every Warden in the district. He doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt know \u003cstrong\u003eyou\u003c/strong\u003e. ГўЛ†вЂ™1 Patience.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThreaten or intimidate (Might)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCatastrophic. Eirik has 8 wardens and a fortified position. ГўЛ†вЂ™2 Patience. If Patience hits 0 through threats, the PCs are detained and must escape (adding a day to the journey and burning their cover).\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePresent BrynГўв‚¬в„ўs toll-token\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAutomatic: one party member passes free. Eirik recognises the token and asks after Bryn. If the PCs mention sheГўв‚¬в„ўs alive and where she is, he is visibly relievedГўв‚¬вЂќ\"She was a good Tender. We all wondered.\"\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eOutcomes\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eInterest Achieved:\u003c/strong\u003e The PCs pass freely. Eirik provides road intelligence:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"The mountain road is passable but ugly. Two rockfalls in the last weekГўв‚¬вЂќyouГўв‚¬в„ўll need to detour around the second one, near Kross-stead. And watch the gorge bridgeГўв‚¬вЂќthe western footing has shifted. ItГўв‚¬в„ўll hold, probably, but donГўв‚¬в„ўt linger on it.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe pauses. \"ThereГўв‚¬в„ўs alsoГўв‚¬В¦Гўв‚¬вЂ№ something else. The patrols up in the high country have been finding tracks. Big ones. Not bear, not wolf. Something that walks on two legs but drags something behind it. We donГўв‚¬в„ўt go looking. IГўв‚¬в„ўd suggest you donГўв‚¬в„ўt either.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs impressed Eirik during the negotiation (Tier 2+ result), he also offers a confiscated weapon from his evidence locker: the @UUID[Item.SVH00ChainDagr01]{ChainwardenГўв‚¬в„ўs Confiscated Dagger}. Гўв‚¬Е“YouГўв‚¬в„ўll need this more than my paperwork does.Гўв‚¬Вќ\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePatience Exhausted:\u003c/strong\u003e The PCs are treated with suspicion. Choose one:\n\u003cstrong\u003e TheyГўв‚¬в„ўre forced to surrender 2 days\u0027 rations as \"toll payment\" (Heat cost).\n\u003c/strong\u003e Their descriptions are logged in the ledger. GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs network may access this. (+1 to all future Grafvitnir Pressure Checks.)\n** TheyГўв‚¬в„ўre delayed half a day while paperwork is \"processed\" (Time cost).\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 1b: Interlude Гўв‚¬вЂќ The GlГѓВіГѓВ°fariГўв‚¬в„ўs Caravan\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003ePlace this scene immediately after the Greypass negotiation, before the party continues up the mountain road.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eContext\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIn a sheltered hollow just past the checkpoint, a caravan has made camp Гўв‚¬вЂќ five or six wagons in a careful circle, each one patched and reinforced with the wear of many seasons. The canvas is a patchwork of repairs. Between the wagons, people move with the quiet efficiency of a group that has done this a thousand times.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe caravan was also delayed by the Chainwardens. Where the party negotiated their way through, the caravanГўв‚¬в„ўs master has been in a quieter, longer standoff. Now that the checkpoint is behind them both, the caravan master notices the party and raises a hand in greeting.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis is \u003cstrong\u003eSГѓВ¶ldГѓВ­s GlГѓВіГѓВ°fari\u003c/strong\u003e. See SГѓВ¶ldГѓВ­s GlГѓВіГѓВ°fari: The GlГѓВіГѓВ°fariГўв‚¬в„ўs Arc for her full character document.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eA tall woman with copper-brown hair in a practical braid stands by a small fire, tending it with the attention of someone who takes fire personally. Her coat is a patchwork of repairs Гўв‚¬вЂќ each patch from a different settlement, different season. Around her neck, on a cord close to her chest, hangs a sealed clay pot. Even from here you can see the faint glow of something inside Гўв‚¬вЂќ not flame, exactly, but the suggestion of flame. The suggestion of something that has been burning for a very, very long time.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eShe looks at you Гўв‚¬вЂќ your gear, your pace, your injuries, the way you carry yourselves Гўв‚¬вЂќ and something in her expression says she has already learned more from looking than most people learn from asking.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"You got past Eirik?\" She smiles. \"He wrote you down in that ledger of his. YouГўв‚¬в„ўre in the system now. Congratulations.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eShe gestures toward the fire. \"Sit. Eat. You look like people who could use a warm meal more than they could use advice, but IГўв‚¬в„ўll give you both.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Caravan Members\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the party accepts the meal, they encounter SГѓВ¶ldГѓВ­sГўв‚¬в„ўs caravan family. Use these moments to make the caravan feel real:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSteinГѓВѕГѓВіr\u003c/strong\u003e (mid-30s, the caravanГўв‚¬в„ўs muscle) is hauling firewood in loads that should require two people. He nods at the party without speaking, but if anyone offers to help, he accepts with a surprised look Гўв‚¬вЂќ not many people volunteer. He works beside them in companionable silence. If asked about SГѓВ¶ldГѓВ­s, all he says is: \"She knows where to go. I carry things. It works.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRagna\u003c/strong\u003e (70s, herb-woman) is sitting on a wagon seat, wrapped in blankets, and pronounces judgment on the party the moment she sees them: \"Thin. All of you. The road is eating you and you havenГўв‚¬в„ўt even reached the hard part yet.\" She produces a small bundle of dried herbs and presses it into the hands of whoever looks most tired. \"Brew that tonight. YouГўв‚¬в„ўll sleep. You look like people who havenГўв‚¬в„ўt slept properly in a week.\" SheГўв‚¬в„ўs right.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEinar\u003c/strong\u003e (10, ГѓВЃstrГѓВ­ГѓВ°rГўв‚¬в„ўs son) approaches the party with the directness of a child who hasnГўв‚¬в„ўt yet learned fear: \"Are you going to the place where the ice comes from? ГѓвЂњttar says you are. ГѓвЂњttar says youГўв‚¬в„ўre going to die. Mama says ГѓвЂњttar doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt know what heГўв‚¬в„ўs talking about.\" He looks at Kaelen with particular interest. \"Why is your head warm?\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eГѓвЂњttar\u003c/strong\u003e (early 20s, apprentice trader) hovers nearby, asking questions heГўв‚¬в„ўs clearly been told not to ask: \"Where exactly are you headed? North, obviously. But where in the north? WhatГўв‚¬в„ўs the actual destination? Because the routes diverge at the Stair, and if youГўв‚¬в„ўre taking the eastern fork, I know a man whoГўв‚¬вЂќ\" SГѓВ¶ldГѓВ­s cuts him off with a look. He retreats, but not far.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVГѓВ©laug\u003c/strong\u003e (35, silent repair-master) says nothing. But when the party finishes the meal, they will notice that a piece of damaged gear Гўв‚¬вЂќ a torn pack strap, a loosened boot heel, a fraying rope Гўв‚¬вЂќ has been quietly repaired. She did it while they ate and never drew attention to it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eWhat SГѓВ¶ldГѓВ­s Offers\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eDuring the meal, SГѓВ¶ldГѓВ­s answers \u003cem\u003eone\u003c/em\u003e direct question the party asks:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAbout the road ahead:\u003c/strong\u003e WhatГўв‚¬в„ўs actually at Stairwatch, whoГўв‚¬в„ўs running it, what to expect on the mountain passes.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAbout the Pale Maw:\u003c/strong\u003e She knows more than is comfortable about their supply lines and checkpoint presence.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAbout the failing settlements:\u003c/strong\u003e SheГўв‚¬в„ўs been to most of them. She knows which ones are still holding.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eShe will \u003cem\u003enot\u003c/em\u003e answer a question about the sealed clay pot. \"ThatГўв‚¬в„ўs for later,\" she says, and changes the subject with the ease of someone who has deflected this question a thousand times.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Critical Moment\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSГѓВ¶ldГѓВ­s notices KaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs ember-mark. She does not comment on it. She does not react. But she notices Гўв‚¬вЂќ a small change in her expression, not fear, but recognition. She looks at Kaelen a moment longer than is casual, and then looks away.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf Kaelen catches this, all SГѓВ¶ldГѓВ­s will say is: \"You carry something. I just noticed the shadow it casts.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eMechanical Benefits\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eRagnaГўв‚¬в„ўs herbs grant +1 edge on one Recovery test during the partyГўв‚¬в„ўs next rest\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eVГѓВ©laugГўв‚¬в„ўs repairs restore one piece of damaged gear to full function (no test required)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSГѓВ¶ldГѓВ­sГўв‚¬в„ўs information provides +1 edge on one knowledge or navigation test in the next beat\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe warm meal counts as a Recovery for one party member (DirectorГўв‚¬в„ўs choice or party consensus)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ Director Note: The Caravan as Investment\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis encounter is designed to make the party \u003cem\u003ecare\u003c/em\u003e about these people. RagnaГўв‚¬в„ўs grumpy kindness, EinarГўв‚¬в„ўs fearless curiosity, VГѓВ©laugГўв‚¬в„ўs silent generosity, SteinГѓВѕГѓВіrГўв‚¬в„ўs simple reliability Гўв‚¬вЂќ these are individuals, not background props. The party is meeting the people they will eventually protect during the Siege of Hrafnborg.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEvery moment of warmth the caravan provides here is a debt the party will feel when SГѓВ¶ldГѓВ­s arrives at HrafnborgГўв‚¬в„ўs gates during the siege. These are her people. The party will want to keep them alive.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 6: Interlude Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Frozen Messenger\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePlace this scene on the mountain road between the toll and the second montage.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eA figure sits against a roadside boulder, hunched in a cloak. Snow has built up against one shoulder like a small drift. Their skin is blue-grey, their eyes open and glazed with frost.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA leather satchel hangs from one frozen hand.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe body is a courierГўв‚¬вЂќa Chainwarden runner, by the badge. Dead perhaps four days. The satchel contains:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eA wax-sealed letter addressed to \"The Watch-Commander, Stairwatch\" Гўв‚¬вЂќ the seal is the KingГўв‚¬в„ўs cipher, but \u003cstrong\u003enot\u003c/strong\u003e HaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs personal seal. Someone else in the court sent this. The letter warns Stairwatch to \"detain any travellers matching [the PCs\u0027 descriptions] and hold them for questioning.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e2 days\u0027 rations (frozen solid, but edible if thawed).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eA small Chainwarden map of the TitanГўв‚¬в„ўs Stair pass, annotated with hazard marks. (+1 edge on one navigation test in the next montage.)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis is evidence that the leak in Hrafnborg is real. Someone besides Harald knows the PCs left. The question: is this the work of a mortal traitor, or has something in HaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs court been passing information to forces outside the walls?\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLeave this ambiguous. The letter was generated by DreyfusГўв‚¬в„ўs influenceГўв‚¬вЂќintelligence whispered through Wyrd-channels from the KingГўв‚¬в„ўs chambers to a compromised court officialГўв‚¬вЂќbut the PCs cannot know that yet. It could equally be a well-meaning functionary acting on incomplete orders.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs take the letter, they can use it in StairwatchГўв‚¬вЂќeither to bluff their way past officials (claiming the courier was delayed and they are the escort) or to warn Lew that HrafnborgГўв‚¬в„ўs security is compromised.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 7: Combat Encounter Гўв‚¬вЂќ Dead on the Mountain Road\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Combat | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on victory\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Combat | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on victory\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eApproximately SГѓВіlmГѓВЎnuГѓВ°ur 12th. Night. The party camps on the mountain road between the toll and the Stair.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eContext\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe \"tracks\" that Warden-Sergeant Eirik warned about belong to a pair of \u003cstrong\u003eFrost-Draugr\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќdead things that have wandered up from the lowland barrows, drawn by some instinct toward the heights. They are not scouts or soldiers. They are the mindless dead, following a pull they donГўв‚¬в„ўt understandГўв‚¬вЂќsouthwest, always southwest, toward Hrafnborg. The partyГўв‚¬в„ўs campfire draws them off-course.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Encounter\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSetting:\u003c/strong\u003e A sheltered hollow on the mountainside. Broken stone walls from a collapsed shepherdГўв‚¬в„ўs hut form a rough windbreak. The partyГўв‚¬в„ўs fire is the only light for miles. The sky is overcastГўв‚¬вЂќno moon, no stars.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEnemies:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e2 Frost-Draugr\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 2 Platoon Brute, EV 8 each)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e4 Grave-Wisps\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 1 Minion Hexer, EV 3 for the squad)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTotal EV:\u003c/strong\u003e 19 (Standard for 4 Level 1 heroes)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eUndead Malice Features\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRavenous Horde\u003c/strong\u003e (2 Malice, Triggered): Trigger: An undead starts its turn. At the end of this round, each hero not already adjacent to one or more undead is beset by two Grave-Wisps who burst up from the frozen ground to appear in adjacent unoccupied spaces. Each summoned undead is winded. This feature canГўв‚¬в„ўt be used two rounds in a row.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eParanormal Fling\u003c/strong\u003e (3 Malice, Triggered): Trigger: An undead starts its turn. Up to three unattended objects on the encounter map rise to float 1 square off the ground. Each object is then pulled 5 squares toward the nearest enemy within 3 squares of the object.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Grasping, the Hungry\u003c/strong\u003e (5 Malice, Triggered): Trigger: An undead starts its turn. Ravenous undead arms burst forth from 9 connected squares of a vertical or horizontal surface. Any creature who ends their turn adjacent to an affected square makes an \u003cem\u003eAgility test\u003c/em\u003e: ГўвЂ°В¤11: 5 damage; restrained (save ends) | 12Гўв‚¬вЂњ16: 5 damage; restrained (EoT) | 17+: 5 damage. While restrained this way, a creature takes 1d6 damage at the start of each of their turns.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDread March\u003c/strong\u003e (7 Malice, Triggered): Trigger: An undead starts its turn. Up to four undead in the encounter move up to their speed and can make a free strike. The number of undead affected increases by 1 for each additional Malice spent. If an undead is reduced to 0 Stamina during this dread march, they donГўв‚¬в„ўt die until the march is resolved.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eFrost-Draugr\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eFrost-Draugr\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eUndead, Humanoid\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eLevel 2 Platoon Brute\u003c/strong\u003e | \u003cstrong\u003eEV 8\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSize:\u003c/strong\u003e 1M | \u003cstrong\u003eSpeed:\u003c/strong\u003e 5 | \u003cstrong\u003eStamina:\u003c/strong\u003e 50 | \u003cstrong\u003eStability:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 | \u003cstrong\u003eFree Strike:\u003c/strong\u003e 5\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eImmunity:\u003c/strong\u003e cold 2, poison | \u003cstrong\u003eWeakness:\u003c/strong\u003e fire 5\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMight\u003c/strong\u003e +2, \u003cstrong\u003eAgility\u003c/strong\u003e +0, \u003cstrong\u003eReason\u003c/strong\u003e ГўЛ†вЂ™3, \u003cstrong\u003eIntuition\u003c/strong\u003e +1, \u003cstrong\u003ePresence\u003c/strong\u003e ГўЛ†вЂ™2\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFrozen Grip\u003c/strong\u003e ГўвЂ”вЂ  2d10 + 2 Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003eSignature Ability, Main action\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eMelee, Strike, Weapon\u003c/em\u003e | Melee 1 | One creature or object\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eГўвЂ°В¤11: 6 cold damage\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e12Гўв‚¬вЂњ16: 9 cold damage; m\u0026lt;2] slowed (EoT)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e17+: 12 cold damage; m\u0026lt;2] slowed (save ends)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRelentless Advance\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003eTriggered action\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nTrigger: The Frost-Draugr is force moved.\u003cbr\u003e\nEffect: After the forced movement resolves, the Frost-Draugr shifts 2 squares toward the nearest enemy.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCold Aura\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ At the start of the Frost-Draugr\u0027s turn, each enemy adjacent to the Frost-Draugr takes 2 cold damage.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eUndead Resilience\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Frost-Draugr is immune to the frightened and sleeping conditions.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eDirector Notes: Frost-Draugr are slow, powerful, and inevitable. They walk toward the nearest warm body and hit it until it stops being warm. Their Cold Aura punishes melee engagementГўв‚¬вЂќthe smart play is ranged attacks and kiting. But the Grave-Wisps are designed to make kiting difficult.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eGrave-Wisp\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eGrave-Wisp\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eUndead, Spirit\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eLevel 1 Minion Hexer\u003c/strong\u003e | \u003cstrong\u003eEV 3 for four minions\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSize:\u003c/strong\u003e 1S | \u003cstrong\u003eSpeed:\u003c/strong\u003e 6 | \u003cstrong\u003eStamina:\u003c/strong\u003e 3 | \u003cstrong\u003eStability:\u003c/strong\u003e 0 | \u003cstrong\u003eFree Strike:\u003c/strong\u003e 1\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eImmunity:\u003c/strong\u003e cold 1, poison | \u003cstrong\u003eWeakness:\u003c/strong\u003e fire 3\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eMovement:\u003c/strong\u003e Fly | \u003cstrong\u003eWith Captain:\u003c/strong\u003e The wisp doesn\u0027t provoke opportunity attacks.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMight\u003c/strong\u003e ГўЛ†вЂ™2, \u003cstrong\u003eAgility\u003c/strong\u003e +2, \u003cstrong\u003eReason\u003c/strong\u003e ГўЛ†вЂ™3, \u003cstrong\u003eIntuition\u003c/strong\u003e +2, \u003cstrong\u003ePresence\u003c/strong\u003e +0\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCold Touch\u003c/strong\u003e ГўвЂ”вЂ  2d10 + 2 Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003eSignature Ability, Main action\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eMagic, Melee, Strike\u003c/em\u003e | Melee 1 | One creature per minion\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eГўвЂ°В¤11: 1 cold damage\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e12Гўв‚¬вЂњ16: 2 cold damage; target can\u0027t shift (EoT)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e17+: 3 cold damage; target can\u0027t shift (EoT)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLure\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003eManeuver\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eRanged\u003c/em\u003e | Ranged 5 | One enemy\u003cbr\u003e\np\u0026lt;0] the target is pulled 2 squares toward the wisp. The target sees the wisp as a distant campfire, a familiar face, or a beckoning lantern.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eIncorporeal\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ The wisp takes half damage from weapon attacks that don\u0027t have a magic keyword.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eDirector Notes: Wisps exist to pin targets in place for the Draugr. Lure pulls PCs into Cold Aura range; Cold Touch locks them there. Kill the wisps first or suffer the Draugr\u0027s patient, crushing advance.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eTerrain Features\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCampfire:\u003c/strong\u003e Provides light in a 4-square radius. Any undead that starts its turn within 2 squares of the fire takes 3 fire damage. The PCs\u0027 fire is both weapon and vulnerabilityГўв‚¬вЂќit draws the dead, but it also hurts them.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCollapsed Stone Walls:\u003c/strong\u003e Provide half cover and block movement. Can be toppled (easy Might test) to create difficult terrain.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eScree Slope:\u003c/strong\u003e The hillside above the camp is loose stone. A creature pushed into the scree must make an easy Agility test or fall prone and slide 2 squares downhill.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDarkness Beyond Firelight:\u003c/strong\u003e Creatures outside the campfireГўв‚¬в„ўs light radius have concealment. The wisps exploit thisГўв‚¬вЂќthey hover at the edge of visibility.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eAftermath\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe draugr fallГўв‚¬вЂќone collapsing like a puppet with cut strings, the other crumbling into hoarfrost that melts in the fireГўв‚¬в„ўs heat. The wisps scatter like sparks and blink out.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSilence. The fire crackles. The wind moans through the broken walls.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eNobody sleeps well after that.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs examine the draugr remains (easy Reason test): these arenГўв‚¬в„ўt recent dead. TheyГўв‚¬в„ўre \u003cstrong\u003eold\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќcenturies old, based on the corroded armour fragments and the archaic brooch-style. Whatever is raising the dead isnГўв‚¬в„ўt just waking recent corpses. ItГўв‚¬в„ўs reaching \u003cstrong\u003edeep\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 8: Point of Interest Гўв‚¬вЂќ Kross-stead\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePlace this on the mountain road, roughly Day 7Гўв‚¬вЂњ8.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe road passes through what was once a mining settlementГўв‚¬вЂќa dozen stone buildings clustered around a shaft-head, with a crude smelter and a Chainwarden outpost. The outpost flag still flies, but thereГўв‚¬в„ўs no one here.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe shaft-head is open. Warm air rises from the opening.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKross-stead was a silver mine. The miners evacuated three weeks ago when the temperature in the lower shafts began \u003cstrong\u003erising\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќslowly, inexplicably. The Chainwarden garrison followed.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs investigate the shaft (not recommended, but PCs are PCs): warm, sulphurous air. The walls of the shaft are veined with something that isnГўв‚¬в„ўt silverГўв‚¬вЂќa dark, root-like growth that pulses faintly with amber light. This is connected to YggdrasilГўв‚¬в„ўs root system, though the PCs canГўв‚¬в„ўt know that yet. Anyone who touches the growth feels a vibrationГўв‚¬вЂќlike a heartbeat, very slow, very deep.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs search the buildings: 1 dayГўв‚¬в„ўs rations, a minerГўв‚¬в„ўs pickaxe (decent weapon), and a Chainwarden logbook. The last entry reads: \u003cem\u003e\"The walls of the lower gallery are warm to the touch. Supervisor Alrek says itГўв‚¬в„ўs geothermal. Alrek is an idiot. Trees donГўв‚¬в„ўt grow underground.\"\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs take rope, pitons, or climbing gear from the mining stores: +1 edge on one Agility test at TitanГўв‚¬в„ўs Stair.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 9: Montage Test 2 Гўв‚¬вЂќ Midgard\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Montage Test (Titan Stair) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 VP on success, 1 VP partial, 0 VP failure\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Montage Test (Titan Stair) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 VP on success, 1 VP partial, 0 VP failure\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003eГўв‚¬в„ўs Shield \u0026amp; TitanГўв‚¬в„ўs Stair\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCovers Days 5Гўв‚¬вЂњ10: Chainwarden Toll ГўвЂ вЂ™ Mountain Road ГўвЂ вЂ™ TitanГўв‚¬в„ўs Stair ГўвЂ вЂ™ Descent to Stairwatch.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eParty Size Adjustment (4 heroes):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDifficulty\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eSuccess Limit\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eFailure Limit\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHard (adjusted)\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e6\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e2\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRounds:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 montage test rounds.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eRound 3 Sample Tests\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eChallenge\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCharacteristic\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDescription\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eNavigate around the rockfalls\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eReason\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eEirik warned about two rockfalls. The first is minor (scramble over rubble). The second, near Kross-stead, requires a full detour through an unmarked goat-track.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eEndure altitude and thinning air\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eMight\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe mountains are high and the air is thin. Characters not accustomed to altitude suffer headaches, nosebleeds, and shortness of breath. Pace management matters.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCross the Gorge Bridge\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAgility\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe stone bridge spans a gorge 60 feet deep. The western footing has shiftedГўв‚¬вЂќthe bridge tilts slightly, and stones crumble with each step. Cross quickly, test balance, or find an anchor-line solution.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eFind shelter from a mountain storm\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eIntuition\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eA storm sweeps in without warning. Whiteout conditions, wind strong enough to push characters off the path. Finding a cave, overhang, or lee-side shelter before exposure sets in.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eSpot and avoid an avalanche zone\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eIntuition\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe slope above the path is loaded with snow. The vibration of footsteps could trigger a slide. Identify the danger and route through safelyГўв‚¬вЂќor run.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eRepair a broken wagon axle / improvise a bridge\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eReason\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eA section of the mountain road has collapsed entirely, leaving a 10-foot gap over nothing. Use available timber, rope, and ingenuity to cross.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eRound 3 Interlude: The Watched Feeling\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAs you crest a hill, a feeling settles over the groupГўв‚¬вЂќa prickling at the back of the neck. Not a sound. Not a movement. Just the unmistakable sense that \u003cstrong\u003esomething\u003c/strong\u003e out there knows where you are.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe ridge to the northwest is empty. The sky is grey. Nothing moves.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBut the feeling doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt leave.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis is the first effect of GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs network. Intelligence from Hrafnborg has reached agents in the field, and the PCs are now being trackedГўв‚¬вЂќnot by the hound, but by the Pale MawГўв‚¬в„ўs informant chains: corrupted couriers, compromised Chainwarden posts, and Wyrd-touched carrion birds with silver eyes circling high above.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf anyone uses magic to scan: nothing registers. GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs agents are mortal. The Wyrd-channels that feed them are invisible to arcane detection.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eRound 4 Sample Tests\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eChallenge\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCharacteristic\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDescription\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eTraverse the TitanГўв‚¬в„ўs Stair switchbacks\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAgility\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eIce-slick switchbacks carved into the mountain face. The path is narrowГўв‚¬вЂќtwo abreast at bestГўв‚¬вЂќwith a sheer drop on one side. One slip means a very long fall.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eKeep the group moving through exhaustion\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePresence\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDay 9. Everyone is tired, cold, and running low on supplies. The Stair is the hardest section yet, and moral strength matters as much as physical.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHandle the ice-bridge at the summit\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAgility / Reason\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe final crossing before the descent: a natural ice-bridge formed over the top of the pass. It groans underfoot. Characters can test the ice (Reason) to find the strongest path or trust balance (Agility) and move fast.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDescend safely to the Interior Belt\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAgility\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe descent from TitanГўв‚¬в„ўs Stair is steep and looseГўв‚¬вЂќscree, ice-melt channels, and treacherous footing. A controlled descent requires skill; a rushed one invites broken ankles.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eScout for threats on the descent\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eIntuition\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe far side of the pass opens into the Interior Belt. From the heights, the PCs can see Stairwatch belowГўв‚¬вЂќand potentially spot anyone waiting for them.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eForage for emergency supplies\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eIntuition\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eSupplies running low? The high country offers slim pickings: mountain hare, snowberry bushes, frozen lichen. Enough to survive, not to thrive.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eRound 4 Interlude: The Cairn Field\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNear the summit of TitanГўв‚¬в„ўs Stair, the path widens into a flat plateau. Cairns stand hereГўв‚¬вЂќdozens of them, rough-stacked stone pillars ranging from knee-height to taller than a man. Each one is marked with runes.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThese are \u003cstrong\u003etravel-cairns\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќmonuments left by generations of travellers who survived the crossing. The tradition: add a stone to the pile, speak a name, and the crossing grants safe passage.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSome of the cairns are recent. One is barely a day oldГўв‚¬вЂќa small stack with a childГўв‚¬в„ўs mitten tucked between the stones.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe newest cairn has no runes. Just a word scratched into the topstone with a knife:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eHELP.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eNo mechanical effect, but this scene hammers home the stakes: this road is barely passable even for the desperate, and the PCs are walking it by choice. If any PC adds a stone to the cairn field, the wind drops for exactly one minuteГўв‚¬вЂќlong enough to feel the sunГўв‚¬в„ўs warmth through the clouds, faint but real.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 10: Montage 2 Outcomes\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 style=\"color:#66ff66;\"\u003eTotal Success (5+ successes before failure limit)\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe party clears TitanГўв‚¬в„ўs Stair and descends to the Interior Belt intact.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEarn \u003cstrong\u003e2 Victories\u003c/strong\u003e (cumulative with Montage 1; maximum 4 Victories from both).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eArrive in Stairwatch with supplies and energy.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs have proven themselves on the road. They are harder now than when they left.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 style=\"color:#ffff66;\"\u003ePartial Success (failure limit hit, but 2+ more successes than failures)\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eArrive in Stairwatch at cost. Choose one:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHeat cost:\u003c/strong\u003e Lose 2 days\u0027 rations navigating around the rockfalls. Supplies are now critical.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWeight cost:\u003c/strong\u003e One PCГўв‚¬в„ўs equipment is damaged crossing the Gorge Bridge or the ice-bridge (weapon, armour, or tool needs repair in StairwatchГўв‚¬вЂќcosts Weight).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWord cost:\u003c/strong\u003e The PCs were spotted by someone on the descentГўв‚¬вЂќa distant figure who turned back toward the toll. Their passage is now on record. (+1 to future Grafvitnir Pressure Checks.)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEarn \u003cstrong\u003e1 Victory\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 style=\"color:#ff6666;\"\u003eTotal Failure\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe party still reaches Stairwatch, but arrives \u003cstrong\u003ewrecked\u003c/strong\u003e:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLose remaining rations \u003cstrong\u003eand\u003c/strong\u003e one piece of equipment is broken.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs agents know exactly where the party is. The next Pressure Check triggers automatically at 5+.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOne PC arrives with a \u003cstrong\u003econdition\u003c/strong\u003e (exhausted, frostbitten, or rattledГўв‚¬вЂќchoose based on the worst failure).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNo Victories earned. Director gains 3 Malice for the next combat encounter.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch3\u003eMontage 2 Failure Encounter: Goblin Ambush (Optional)\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Combat (Optional - triggered on montage failure) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on victory\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Combat (Optional - triggered on montage failure) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on victory\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eThis encounter triggers on a Total Failure or at the Director\u0027s discretion after a Partial Success. GoblinsГўв‚¬вЂќthought extinct in the Titanspine for generationsГўв‚¬вЂќhave emerged from deep mountain caves, driven forward by an unknown power. They are desperate, feral, and organised under a self-styled monarch.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe descent path switchbacks through a narrow defileГўв‚¬вЂќloose scree above, a sheer drop below. Ahead, the trail is blocked by a crude barricade of broken cart wheels and piled stones.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThen the chittering starts.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSmall shapes scramble along the cliff walls above you. Green-grey skin, yellow eyes, crude weapons. One of themГўв‚¬вЂќslightly larger, wearing a battered crown made from bent nails and copper wireГўв‚¬вЂќstands on a boulder and shrieks something in a language you don\u0027t understand.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIt points at you. The others charge.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eGoblins. Here. That shouldn\u0027t be possible.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat\u0027s really happening:\u003c/strong\u003e These goblins have been driven from their deep caverns by something belowГўв‚¬вЂќthe same power that\u0027s raising the dead and pulling things southwest. They don\u0027t know what it is. They\u0027re as scared as they are dangerous. The Goblin Monarch is desperately trying to establish territory for its tribe before winter kills them all.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eNegotiation difficult but possible:\u003c/strong\u003e A PC who speaks Caelian or can communicate through gestures can attempt to parley (hard Presence test). Success means the goblins let them pass in exchange for food (half the party\u0027s remaining rations). The Monarch is pragmaticГўв‚¬вЂќit wants its people alive more than it wants a fight.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eEncounter Setup\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEncounter Difficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate (EV 21 for 4 heroes)\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eComposition:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e1 Goblin Monarch (Leader, EV 12)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e2 Goblin Warriors (Horde Harrier, EV 3 each)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e4 Goblin Runners (Minion Harrier, EV 3 for the squad)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTerrain:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBarricade:\u003c/strong\u003e Provides three-quarters cover. Can be dismantled (easy Might test) or climbed over (easy Agility test, costs 2 extra movement).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCliff Walls:\u003c/strong\u003e The goblins start on the walls above (Climb movement). 3 squares up. Creatures without Climb must make a easy Might test to scale.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eScree Slope:\u003c/strong\u003e Difficult terrain. A creature pushed through scree must make an easy Agility test or fall prone.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eNarrow Path:\u003c/strong\u003e Only 3 squares wide between the cliff face and the drop. Limits flanking opportunities for larger creatures.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTactics:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe Goblin Runners charge from the cliff walls, exploiting Crafty to avoid opportunity attacks.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe Goblin Warriors use Spear Charge for hit-and-run tactics, retreating to high ground.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe Goblin Monarch hangs back on the boulder, using Handaxe on two targets at range and \u003cem\u003eGet in Here!\u003c/em\u003e to summon more Runners.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eIf a PC is isolated, the Monarch uses Meat Shield to redirect attacks to nearby Runners.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWhen pressed, the Monarch triggers \u003cem\u003eKill!\u003c/em\u003e (VA3) to punish clustering.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eGoblin Malice Features\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGoblin Mode\u003c/strong\u003e (3 Malice): Each goblin shifts up to 3 squares. Until end of round, goblins have double edge on power rolls against creatures larger than them.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTiny Stabs\u003c/strong\u003e (5 Malice): 10 burst. Each enemy in the area takes 3 damage for each goblin adjacent to them.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSwamp Stink\u003c/strong\u003e (7 Malice): 10 burst. Each enemy must succeed on an easy Intuition test or become dazed (save ends). Each goblin then shifts up to 3 squares.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eGoblin Runner\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eGoblin Runner\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGoblin, Humanoid\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eLevel 1 Minion Harrier\u003c/strong\u003e | \u003cstrong\u003eEV 3 for four minions\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSize:\u003c/strong\u003e 1S | \u003cstrong\u003eSpeed:\u003c/strong\u003e 6 | \u003cstrong\u003eStamina:\u003c/strong\u003e 4 | \u003cstrong\u003eStability:\u003c/strong\u003e 0 | \u003cstrong\u003eFree Strike:\u003c/strong\u003e 1\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eMovement:\u003c/strong\u003e Climb | \u003cstrong\u003eWith Captain:\u003c/strong\u003e Gain an edge on strikes.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMight\u003c/strong\u003e ГўЛ†вЂ™2, \u003cstrong\u003eAgility\u003c/strong\u003e +2, \u003cstrong\u003eReason\u003c/strong\u003e +0, \u003cstrong\u003eIntuition\u003c/strong\u003e +0, \u003cstrong\u003ePresence\u003c/strong\u003e ГўЛ†вЂ™1\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eClub Charge\u003c/strong\u003e ГўвЂ”вЂ  2d10 + 2 Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003eSignature Ability, Main action\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eCharge, Melee, Strike, Weapon\u003c/em\u003e | Melee 1 | One creature or object per minion\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eГўвЂ°В¤11: 1 damage\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e12Гўв‚¬вЂњ16: 2 damage\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e17+: 3 damage\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCrafty\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ The runner doesn\u0027t provoke opportunity attacks by moving.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eGoblin Warrior\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eGoblin Warrior\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGoblin, Humanoid\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eLevel 1 Horde Harrier\u003c/strong\u003e | \u003cstrong\u003eEV 3\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSize:\u003c/strong\u003e 1S | \u003cstrong\u003eSpeed:\u003c/strong\u003e 6 | \u003cstrong\u003eStamina:\u003c/strong\u003e 15 | \u003cstrong\u003eStability:\u003c/strong\u003e 0 | \u003cstrong\u003eFree Strike:\u003c/strong\u003e 1\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eMovement:\u003c/strong\u003e Climb\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMight\u003c/strong\u003e ГўЛ†вЂ™2, \u003cstrong\u003eAgility\u003c/strong\u003e +2, \u003cstrong\u003eReason\u003c/strong\u003e +0, \u003cstrong\u003eIntuition\u003c/strong\u003e +0, \u003cstrong\u003ePresence\u003c/strong\u003e ГўЛ†вЂ™1\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSpear Charge\u003c/strong\u003e ГўвЂ”вЂ  2d10 + 2 Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003eSignature Ability, Main action\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eCharge, Melee, Strike, Weapon\u003c/em\u003e | Melee 1 | One creature or object\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eГўвЂ°В¤11: 3 damage\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e12Гўв‚¬вЂњ16: 4 damage\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e17+: 5 damage\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBury the Point\u003c/strong\u003e ГўвЂ”вЂ  2d10 + 2 Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003e2 Malice, Main action\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eMelee, Strike, Weapon\u003c/em\u003e | Melee 1 | One creature\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eГўвЂ°В¤11: 5 damage; m\u0026lt;0] bleeding (save ends)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e12Гўв‚¬вЂњ16: 6 damage; m\u0026lt;1] bleeding (save ends)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e17+: 7 damage; m\u0026lt;2] bleeding (save ends)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCrafty\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ The warrior doesn\u0027t provoke opportunity attacks by moving.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eGoblin Monarch\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eGoblin Monarch\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGoblin, Humanoid\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eLevel 1 Leader\u003c/strong\u003e | \u003cstrong\u003eEV 12\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSize:\u003c/strong\u003e 1S | \u003cstrong\u003eSpeed:\u003c/strong\u003e 6 | \u003cstrong\u003eStamina:\u003c/strong\u003e 80 | \u003cstrong\u003eStability:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 | \u003cstrong\u003eFree Strike:\u003c/strong\u003e 4\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eMovement:\u003c/strong\u003e Climb\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMight\u003c/strong\u003e +0, \u003cstrong\u003eAgility\u003c/strong\u003e +3, \u003cstrong\u003eReason\u003c/strong\u003e +1, \u003cstrong\u003eIntuition\u003c/strong\u003e +0, \u003cstrong\u003ePresence\u003c/strong\u003e +3\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHandaxe\u003c/strong\u003e ГўвЂ”вЂ  2d10 + 3 Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003eSignature Ability, Main action\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eMelee, Ranged, Strike, Weapon\u003c/em\u003e | Melee 1 or Ranged 5 | Two creatures or objects\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eГўвЂ°В¤11: 7 damage\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e12Гўв‚¬вЂњ16: 10 damage\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e17+: 13 damage\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eEffect: One ally within 10 squares of the monarch can make a free strike.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGet in Here!\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003e1 Malice, Maneuver\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eRanged\u003c/em\u003e | Ranged 20 | Special\u003cbr\u003e\nEffect: Two goblin runners appear in unoccupied spaces within distance.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMeat Shield\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003eTriggered action\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eMelee\u003c/em\u003e | Melee 1 | One ally\u003cbr\u003e\nTrigger: A creature targets the monarch with a strike.\u003cbr\u003e\nEffect: The ally is the target of the triggering strike instead.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCrafty\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ The monarch doesn\u0027t provoke opportunity attacks by moving.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEnd Effect\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ At the end of each of their turns, the monarch can take 5 damage to end one effect on them that can be ended by a saving throw. This damage can\u0027t be reduced in any way.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat Are You Waiting For?\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003eVillain Action 1\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eArea\u003c/em\u003e | 10 burst | Each ally in the area\u003cbr\u003e\nEffect: Each target can move up to their speed or make a free strike.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFocus Fire\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003eVillain Action 2\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eRanged\u003c/em\u003e | Ranged 10 | One enemy or object\u003cbr\u003e\nEffect: Each ally within 10 squares of the target can move up to their speed toward the target.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eKill!\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003eVillain Action 3\u003c/em\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nEffect: Each enemy in the encounter takes 2 damage for each goblin adjacent to them.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eAmbush Aftermath\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs \u003cstrong\u003ewin\u003c/strong\u003e the fight:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSearching the barricade reveals the goblins\u0027 meagre suppliesГўв‚¬вЂќstolen traveller\u0027s goods, dried cave-fish, and corroded coins. Worth 10 gold total.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eA crude map scratched on cave-bark shows the goblin caves deeper in the Titanspine, with an area marked in charcoal scratches. An easy Intuition test identifies this as the direction of HrafnborgГўв‚¬вЂќthe goblins were fleeing \u003cem\u003efrom\u003c/em\u003e that direction.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThis is key intelligence: something in the southwest is driving creaturesГўв‚¬вЂќliving and deadГўв‚¬вЂќout of their homes.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eEarn \u003cstrong\u003e1 Victory\u003c/strong\u003e for defeating the ambush.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs \u003cstrong\u003enegotiate\u003c/strong\u003e:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThey lose half their remaining rations but gain the crude map (same intelligence as above).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe Monarch offers a Гўв‚¬Е“giftГўв‚¬ВќГўв‚¬вЂќa tarnished bronze ring with a rune that neither the Monarch nor the PCs can read. (This is an ancient JГѓВ¶tunfolk traveller\u0027s ring. It\u0027s worth nothing, but it has sentimental value to the Monarch. Accepting it graciously earns +1 to future interactions with non-hostile goblin groups.)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs \u003cstrong\u003eflee\u003c/strong\u003e:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe goblins take their supplies from wherever the PCs were camped or resting. Lose all remaining rations.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe goblins don\u0027t pursue beyond their territory.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 11: Arrival at Stairwatch\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eApproximately SГѓВіlmГѓВЎnuГѓВ°ur 15thГўв‚¬вЂњ16th.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eRegardless of montage outcomes, the PCs arrive at Stairwatch.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eStairwatch hunches at the foot of TitanГўв‚¬в„ўs Stair like a dog thatГўв‚¬в„ўs been kicked too many times. ItГўв‚¬в„ўs a waystation townГўв‚¬вЂќbuilt for travellers who never stay long, and it shows. The buildings lean. The streets are mud frozen into ridges. Smoke rises from every chimney, but the fires burn low.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe inn-sign reads \u003cem\u003eThe Broken Stair\u003c/em\u003e. Below it, smaller: \u003cem\u003eRooms. Ale. No questions.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe townГўв‚¬в„ўs Ever-Ember burns in a stone ring at the central crossroads. ItГўв‚¬в„ўs the smallest youГўв‚¬в„ўve seenГўв‚¬вЂќbarely a campfire. But it burns. It burns.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eWhat the PCs Find in Stairwatch\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePopulation:\u003c/strong\u003e ~300 permanent residents, plus transient miners, traders, and refugees.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAtmosphere:\u003c/strong\u003e Tense, suspicious, but functional. People here donГўв‚¬в„ўt starveГўв‚¬вЂќthey trade in ore from the TitanГўв‚¬в„ўs Stair minesГўв‚¬вЂќbut they donГўв‚¬в„ўt trust outsiders.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Broken Stair Inn:\u003c/strong\u003e Run by a Dwarf named Hild. She asks no questions, charges fair prices, and waters the ale exactly enough to be annoying.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Chainwarden Post:\u003c/strong\u003e A small stone building near the Ever-Ember. Two Wardens: one bored, one paranoid. TheyГўв‚¬в„ўll want to see papers.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLew Tosferd:\u003c/strong\u003e Not immediately visible. He doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt advertise. He lives somewhere in the upper town. Finding him is Easy because heГўв‚¬в„ўs well-known around townГўв‚¬вЂќbut convincing him to help is another matter. (See Beat 5.)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eGrafvitnir Pressure Check\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eRoll the Grafvitnir Pressure Check (d6) upon arrival in Stairwatch. This represents GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs networkГўв‚¬вЂќnot Dreyfus himself, who remains in HrafnborgГўв‚¬вЂќacting on relayed intelligence.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eRoll\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eEffect\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e1-2\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eNo network activity. Intelligence from Hrafnborg hasnГўв‚¬в„ўt reached local agents yet. The PCs have breathing room.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e3-4\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eA minor complication: a stranger asks too many questions at the inn, or someone follows the PCs to their lodgingГўв‚¬вЂќa local informant paid by the Pale MawГўв‚¬в„ўs network.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e5\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eA flock of carrion-birds with silver eyes circles the town as the PCs arrive. They circle twice, then fly southwest toward Hrafnborg. Someone is watching from above.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e6\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDirect interception: the Chainwarden post has received a raven from Hrafnborg with updated descriptions of the PCs. They are detained at the gate for questioning. (This is a roleplay encounterГўв‚¬вЂќthe PCs can talk or bluff their way out.)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#2a6a2a;\"\u003eBeat 4a+4b Гўв‚¬вЂќ Victory Point Summary\u003c/h4\u003e\u003cp style=\"font-style:italic; color:#555; margin-top:6px;\"\u003eBoth 4a and 4b play in sequence - all mandatory events contribute VP.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:8px 0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#c0e0c0;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eEvent\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eDifficulty\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eVP Award\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 3: Coastal Road Montage\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHard\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e2/1/0 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003eChainwarden Patrol (on montage failure)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003eModerate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003e1 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 5: Chainwarden Toll Negotiation\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eModerate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e1 VP on success\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 7: Mountain Road Combat\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eModerate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e1 VP on victory\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 9: Titan Stair Montage\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHard\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e2/1/0 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003eGoblin Ambush (on montage failure)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003eModerate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003e1 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#98cc98;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eBeat Total (Mandatory)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eup to 6 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#2a6a2a;\"\u003eBeat 4a+4b Гўв‚¬вЂќ Victory Point Summary\u003c/h4\u003e\u003cp style=\"font-style:italic; color:#555; margin-top:6px;\"\u003eBoth 4a and 4b play in sequence - all mandatory events contribute VP.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:8px 0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#c0e0c0;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eEvent\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eDifficulty\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eVP Award\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 3: Coastal Road Montage\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHard\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e2/1/0 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003eChainwarden Patrol (on montage failure)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003eModerate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003e1 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 5: Chainwarden Toll Negotiation\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eModerate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e1 VP on success\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 7: Mountain Road Combat\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eModerate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e1 VP on victory\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 9: Titan Stair Montage\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHard\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e2/1/0 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003eGoblin Ambush (on montage failure)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003eModerate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003e1 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#98cc98;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eBeat Total (Mandatory)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eup to 6 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eTransition to Beat 5\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs are in Stairwatch. Ten days of hard road behind them. Two hundred miles of cold, corpses, and crumbling infrastructure.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThey need to find Lew Tosferd and convince him to help locate Kaelen.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eProceed to \u003cstrong\u003eBeat 5: Finding Lew\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","markdown":null},"src":null,"system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"sort":40,"flags":{},"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"exportSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"draw-steel","systemVersion":"0.10.0","createdTime":0,"modifiedTime":0,"lastModifiedBy":null}},{"_id":"RTFPAGE000000022","name":"Beat 5 Гўв‚¬вЂќ Finding Lew","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 ГўвЂ вЂ™ 2 (level-up occurs at end of this beat)\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eDuration:\u003c/strong\u003e 1Гўв‚¬вЂњ2 sessions\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eLocation:\u003c/strong\u003e Stairwatch\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eKey NPCs:\u003c/strong\u003e Llewyellen \"Lew\" Tosferd, Hild (innkeeper), Solvi (Ember-Keeper)\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Investigation, Negotiation encounter, local tasks\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eTone:\u003c/strong\u003e Noir-tinged, transactional, a town held together by stubbornness\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1a3a; color:#c8c8e8; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4a4ac8;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVP Status Гўв‚¬вЂќ Entering This Beat\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cstrong\u003eTotal VP (max):\u003c/strong\u003e 8 | \u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 | \u003cstrong\u003eVP into Level:\u003c/strong\u003e 8\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1a3a; color:#c8c8e8; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4a4ac8;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVP Status Гўв‚¬вЂќ Entering This Beat\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cstrong\u003eTotal VP (max):\u003c/strong\u003e 8 | \u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 | \u003cstrong\u003eVP into Level:\u003c/strong\u003e 8\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2\u003eOverview\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs have arrived in Stairwatch. Their objective is simple: find Lew Tosferd and convince him to locate Kaelen. The problem: Lew doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt work for free, he doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt trust strangers, and he has his own troubles in Stairwatch that need solving before heГўв‚¬в„ўll consider leaving.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis beat introduces the partyГўв‚¬в„ўs second major NPC ally, reveals the backstory connection between Lew and Gragnir, and ends with LewГўв‚¬в„ўs finding-gift pointing the way to the Ashen Woods.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 1: Stairwatch at a Glance\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eStairwatch is not a city. ItГўв‚¬в„ўs a waystation that forgot to die.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Town\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePopulation:\u003c/strong\u003e ~300 permanent, plus transients.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEconomy:\u003c/strong\u003e Ore from the TitanГўв‚¬в„ўs Stair mines, re-sold to traders heading to Hrafnborg or the Interior Belt. Some trapping, some charcoal-burning. Everything else is imported and expensive.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eArchitecture:\u003c/strong\u003e Stone foundations, timber upper floors, turf roofs. Most buildings lean. Some lean together, forming accidental archways over the narrow streets.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Ever-Ember:\u003c/strong\u003e Burns in a stone ring at the central crossroads. ItГўв‚¬в„ўs smallГўв‚¬вЂќbarely a campfireГўв‚¬вЂќbut itГўв‚¬в„ўs \u003cstrong\u003ewarm\u003c/strong\u003e. Locals gather near it at dusk and dawn. The Keeper here is a frightened teenager named Solvi who was chosen only six months ago.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMood:\u003c/strong\u003e People here donГўв‚¬в„ўt starve, but they donГўв‚¬в„ўt sleep well either. The mine produces enough iron to trade, but the miners report strange sounds deep in the tunnels. Three families left last month. Two more are packing.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eKey Locations\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eLocation\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDescription\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Broken Stair Inn\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe only inn. Run by Hild, a Dwarf who asks no questions, charges fair prices, and waters the ale just enough to be annoying. Three rooms upstairs, a common hall with a fire thatГўв‚¬в„ўs always burning, and a kitchen that smells of smoked mutton.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Chainwarden Post\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eA small stone building near the Ever-Ember. Two Wardens: Sergeant Tormund (bored, competent, drinks) and Deputy Freja (paranoid, by-the-book, doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt drink). They want to see papers.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Mine Head\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eA gated tunnel entrance at the north end of town. Currently half-operational. Miners go in pairs and donГўв‚¬в„ўt work past noon. The deep shafts are sealedГўв‚¬вЂќ\"bad air,\" they say.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Upper Town\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eA cluster of older stone buildings on the hill above the crossroads. Better-built, quieter. LewГўв‚¬в„ўs lodging is hereГўв‚¬вЂќa rented room above a chandlerГўв‚¬в„ўs shop.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Bone Market\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eNot bonesГўв‚¬вЂќthe name is old. An open-air market near the gate where trappers sell furs, miners sell raw ore, and everyone trades rumors. Meets every other day.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 2: Finding Lew\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLew is not hiding, exactly. HeГўв‚¬в„ўs just not advertising.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eHow the PCs Can Find Him\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAsk at the Broken Stair:\u003c/strong\u003e Hild knows Lew. \"The Finder? Upstairs room, when he bothers to sleep here. More likely at the chandlerГўв‚¬в„ўs. He owes me three nights\u0027 lodging.\" SheГўв‚¬в„ўll point them to the Upper Town.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAsk at the Bone Market:\u003c/strong\u003e Any trader knows Lew. \"The one-eyed man? Aye, he found my missing mule last winter. Charged me more than the mule was worth. Try the chandlerГўв‚¬в„ўs.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAsk at the Chainwarden Post:\u003c/strong\u003e Tormund knows him. \"Tosferd? HeГўв‚¬в„ўs useful. Keeps to himself. DoesnГўв‚¬в„ўt cause trouble I have to write up.\" Freja is more suspicious: \"He knows too many people. Nobody knows that many people honestly.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eJust walk the Upper Town:\u003c/strong\u003e A man sits on a bench outside the chandlerГўв‚¬в„ўs shop, whittling a piece of bone. One eyeГўв‚¬вЂќthe leftГўв‚¬вЂќis real, dark, sharp. The right eye catches the light wrong: it gleams faintly amber, like a coal seen through fog. He watches you approach with the calm patience of someone whoГўв‚¬в„ўs been expecting you.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eFirst Meeting\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"Three strangers with road-dust on their boots and a look like someoneГўв‚¬в„ўs given them a job they didnГўв‚¬в„ўt ask for.\" The man doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt look up from his whittling. The knife moves in small, precise strokes. \"Let me guessГўв‚¬вЂќsomeone sent you. Someone important. And they told you I could find something.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe looks up. One eye is dark and human. The other glints amber in the grey lightГўв‚¬вЂќnot glass, not quite stone. Something \u003cstrong\u003eelse\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"NameГўв‚¬в„ўs Lew. Sit down. YouГўв‚¬в„ўre making the chandler nervous.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLew is friendly, casual, and already three steps ahead. He knows \u003cstrong\u003eabout\u003c/strong\u003e the Konungs-ferГѓВ° (common knowledge), suspects these arenГўв‚¬в„ўt ordinary travelers (uncommon knowledge), and will listen to their pitch before naming his price.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: Playing Lew\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLew is not an obstacleГўв‚¬вЂќheГўв‚¬в„ўs a \u003cstrong\u003etransaction\u003c/strong\u003e. He genuinely wants to help, in the way a merchant genuinely wants to sell you something. HeГўв‚¬в„ўs warm, funny, and utterly without sentiment about money.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKey behaviors:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHe asks questions constantlyГўв‚¬вЂќabout the PCs, their homes, their skills. This is both genuine curiosity and professional assessment.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHe never lies, but he tells you exactly as much as heГўв‚¬в„ўs decided to tell you. No more.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHe refers to his finding-gift obliquely: \"I have a knack,\" \"I know people,\" \"things turn up.\" He does not explain the eye unless pressed far enough.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHe is never rude. He is always expensive.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 3: The Negotiation\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Negotiation | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate (I3/P4) | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on success\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Negotiation | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate (I3/P4) | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on success\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis is a \u003cstrong\u003eNegotiation Encounter\u003c/strong\u003e using Draw SteelГўв‚¬в„ўs negotiation rules.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eSetup\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eInterest:\u003c/strong\u003e 3 (Friendly) Гўв‚¬вЂќ Lew is interested in the job. He just needs proper compensation.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003ePatience:\u003c/strong\u003e 4 Гўв‚¬вЂќ HeГўв‚¬в„ўll hear them out, but heГўв‚¬в„ўs not patient with moralizing or demands.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMotivations (arguments that work):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eProfit:\u003c/strong\u003e Offer concrete paymentГўв‚¬вЂќHeat, Weight, Word, favors, access. \"WhatГўв‚¬в„ўs it worth to you?\" is music to his ears.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCuriosity:\u003c/strong\u003e Appeal to the mystery. Kaelen is the Keeper who vanishedГўв‚¬вЂќfinding her would be the greatest \"lost thing\" LewГўв‚¬в„ўs ever tracked. \"No one knows where she went. No one.\" This intrigues him deeply.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSelf-preservation:\u003c/strong\u003e The Ever-Embers are dying. If they go out, Stairwatch dies. Lew lives in Stairwatch. This is a hard argument for him to dismiss.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePitfalls (arguments that backfire):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThreats:\u003c/strong\u003e Lew does not respond to intimidation. He responds by becoming \u003cstrong\u003every\u003c/strong\u003e helpful to your enemies.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMoralizing:\u003c/strong\u003e \"You have a duty\" or \"Think of the people\" without concrete context makes his patience drop. HeГўв‚¬в„ўs heard it all.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDemanding charity:\u003c/strong\u003e \"Do this for free because itГўв‚¬в„ўs important\" is the fastest way to end the conversation. Lew always names his price.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eNegotiation Flow\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs make arguments. Each argument is a power roll using an appropriate characteristic:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePresence for persuasion, flattery, or social pressure\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eReason for logical arguments, evidence, or strategic framing\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIntuition for reading Lew and tailoring the pitch to what he actually wants\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eRefer to Draw SteelГўв‚¬в„ўs Negotiation rules for test resolution.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eWhat Lew Wants\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs do well, Lew names his price. He wants \u003cstrong\u003etwo things\u003c/strong\u003e:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eA favor, to be named later.\u003c/strong\u003e Not a threatГўв‚¬вЂќa genuine IOU. Lew trades in favors the way other people trade in iron. \"One day, IГўв‚¬в„ўll need something found. Or someone kept unfound. And youГўв‚¬в„ўll help. Fair?\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHelp with a local problem before he leaves.\u003c/strong\u003e Lew canГўв‚¬в„ўt just walk out of Stairwatch. He has obligations, debts, and a reputation to maintain. He needs the PCs to handle something first.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 4: LewГўв‚¬в„ўs Local Task\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLew has a problem he canГўв‚¬в„ўt solve himself because solving it would burn his cover as \"just a finder.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eChoose one (or both) of the following tasks based on session time and party preferences:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eOption A: The Missing Miners\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Combat | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard (Level 2 Boss) | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 VP on victory\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Combat | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard (Level 2 Boss) | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 VP on victory\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThree miners went into the deep shafts four days ago and havenГўв‚¬в„ўt returned. The Mine Head foreman sealed the tunnel and declared \"bad air.\" Lew doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt believe itГўв‚¬вЂќhe thinks something \u003cstrong\u003etook\u003c/strong\u003e them. He wants the PCs to go into the mine and bring them back (or bring back proof of what happened).\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhatГўв‚¬в„ўs Down There:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe deep shafts broke into an old barrow-complexГўв‚¬вЂќpre-Hrafnborg, pre-Svellheim, something \u003cstrong\u003eolder\u003c/strong\u003e. The miners broke through a wall and found a chamber with runic carvings and a cold that isnГўв‚¬в„ўt natural.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTwo miners are alive, trapped behind a cave-in. One miner is deadГўв‚¬вЂќkilled by a \u003cstrong\u003eBarrow-Wight\u003c/strong\u003e (use Draugr Barrow-Warden stats from Beat 2, or scale up) that guards the old chamber.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe runic carvings (medium Reason test) reference \"the binding below\" and \"the wolf that waits.\" This is a fragment of Grafvitnir loreГўв‚¬вЂќthe PCs wonГўв‚¬в„ўt understand it yet, but it connects to the Act 1 climax.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEncounter:\u003c/strong\u003e 1x Barrow-Wight (Level 2 Brute Elite) + 1x Grave-Singer (Level 2 Controller Elite) + 12x Draugr Thrall (Level 1 Brute Minion) вЂ” EV 68 (Hard) вЂ” plus environmental hazards (unstable ceiling, flooded passages, choking dust).\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eOption B: The Debt Collector\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Negotiation | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate (I2/P3) | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on success\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Negotiation | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate (I2/P3) | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on success\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA man named Rath has arrived in Stairwatch claiming Lew owes him a significant debt from a previous contract. Rath is technically correctГўв‚¬вЂќLew took payment for a finding-job and then didnГўв‚¬в„ўt deliver, because the thing he was hired to find turned out to be a person who was \u003cstrong\u003ehiding for good reason\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLew needs the PCs to either:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eNegotiate with Rath\u003c/strong\u003e (Moderate NegotiationГўв‚¬вЂќInterest 2, Patience 3, Motivations: Justice, Respect; Pitfalls: Lies, Evasion) Гўв‚¬вЂќ convince him to accept alternative payment or forgive the debt.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eInvestigate RathГўв‚¬в„ўs purpose\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ Rath isnГўв‚¬в„ўt just a debt collector. HeГўв‚¬в„ўs working for someone who wants that hidden person found. If the PCs dig (medium Intuition test, or social investigation), they learn RathГўв‚¬в„ўs employer has connections to the Pale Maw. This task becomes a moral choice: pay the debt (funding enemies) or expose Rath (burning LewГўв‚¬в„ўs reputation).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГўЕЎвЂќГЇВёВЏ Alternate Reward\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs help Lew with the Debt Collector task, Lew produces a weapon from his personal stash as partial payment: the @UUID[Item.SVH00ChainDagr01]{ChainwardenГўв‚¬в„ўs Confiscated Dagger}. Гўв‚¬Е“Took it off a Warden who owed me a favour. The favour is yours now.Гўв‚¬Вќ (Only available if the PCs did not already receive it from Eirik in Beat 4.)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 5: The Eye\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAfter the PCs complete LewГўв‚¬в„ўs task, heГўв‚¬в„ўs satisfied theyГўв‚¬в„ўre competent and trustworthy enough to travel with. Over a drink at the Broken Stair (or around a campfire if they completed the mine task), Lew explains how heГўв‚¬в„ўll find Kaelen.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLew reaches up and taps the amber eyeГўв‚¬вЂќthe one that catches the light wrong. He doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt remove it, but he turns his head so you can see it clearly.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Lost the real one years ago. Bad job, bad luck, bad timingГўв‚¬вЂќthe usual story when something bites you that shouldnГўв‚¬в„ўt exist.\" He shrugs. \"Gragnir pulled me out. Stitched me up. And when I was healing, he gave me this.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe taps it again. The amber gleams.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"ItГўв‚¬в„ўs a gem. Old. He said it was payment for the jobГўв‚¬вЂќfair trade for an eye, he said.\" A grim smile. \"Took me months to realize what it could do. I was looking for a lost shipment of peltsГўв‚¬вЂќroutine jobГўв‚¬вЂќand the eye justГўв‚¬В¦Гўв‚¬вЂ№ \u003cstrong\u003epulled\u003c/strong\u003e. Like a compass needle. Pointed me right to the cache, buried under a snowdrift twelve miles from where anyone was looking.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe leans back. \"Gragnir didnГўв‚¬в„ўt know. Or maybe he did and wanted me to figure it out myself. With him, itГўв‚¬в„ўs hard to tell.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: The EyeГўв‚¬в„ўs Nature\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe gem is genuineГўв‚¬вЂќa fragment of something old, possibly connected to YggdrasilГўв‚¬в„ўs sap-amber (fossilized world-tree resin). Gragnir gave it as honest payment, not as a tool. The finding-ability was \u003cstrong\u003eserendipity\u003c/strong\u003e: a happy accident of a powerful component in the right host.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe eye works like this:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhen Lew focuses on something \u003cstrong\u003elost\u003c/strong\u003e (a person, an object, a place that was known and became unknown), the eye warms and pulls in the correct direction.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt give distances or detailsГўв‚¬вЂќjust direction. \"That way. Far.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt work on things that were never known (you canГўв‚¬в„ўt find something nobody lost).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt work on things that are \u003cstrong\u003ehidden by Wyrd-level power\u003c/strong\u003e (e.g., GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs prison, the deepest roots of Yggdrasil). It can find Kaelen because Kaelen is hiding by \u003cstrong\u003echoice\u003c/strong\u003e, not by cosmic force.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe eye establishes:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLew and Gragnir have history.\u003c/strong\u003e TheyГўв‚¬в„ўve worked together before. Lew respects Gragnir but finds him infuriating.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGragnirГўв‚¬в„ўs gifts are real but not calculated.\u003c/strong\u003e He helps people in ways that turn out to be importantГўв‚¬вЂќbut he didnГўв‚¬в„ўt necessarily plan for it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLewГўв‚¬в„ўs gift is rare but limited.\u003c/strong\u003e ItГўв‚¬в„ўs a compass, not a map. The PCs still have to \u003cstrong\u003eget\u003c/strong\u003e to Kaelen.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eLew Uses the Eye\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhen Lew focuses on Kaelen:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLew closes his good eye. For a moment, nothing happens. Then the amber eye shiftsГўв‚¬вЂќnot the lid, not the socket, but the light \u003cstrong\u003einside\u003c/strong\u003e the gem. It brightens, dims, brightens again, like a heartbeat.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLewГўв‚¬в„ўs hand comes up slowly and points southeast. Through the wall of the inn, through the mountain, toward the vast grey emptiness of the Interior Belt.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"SheГўв‚¬в„ўs there,\" he says. \"Past the Shield. Past the dead farms. Deep in the Ashen WoodsГўв‚¬вЂќwhatГўв‚¬в„ўs left of them.\" His voice is quiet. \"SheГўв‚¬в„ўs alive. And she doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt want to be found.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe opens his eye. The amber fades.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"ThatГўв‚¬в„ўs the Great Green, friends. Or what used to be it. Three weeks\u0027 travel if weГўв‚¬в„ўre lucky. More if weГўв‚¬в„ўre not.\" He pauses. \"And we wonГўв‚¬в„ўt be.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 6: Level Up\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAt this point, the PCs have:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSurvived the road to Hrafnborg (Beat 2)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eReceived the mission from Harald (Beat 3)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCrossed MidgardГўв‚¬в„ўs Shield to Stairwatch (Beat 4)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCompleted LewГўв‚¬в„ўs local task (Beat 5)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSecured an ally and a heading\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe party advances to Level 2.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: Level-Up Moment\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis is a natural break point. Let the players take a short rest, discuss their build choices, and settle into the feeling of having survived the first phase of the journey.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eNarratively, frame it as: the PCs have proven they can handle the road, the cold, and the unexpected. TheyГўв‚¬в„ўre not wanderers anymoreГўв‚¬вЂќtheyГўв‚¬в„ўre \u003cstrong\u003eagents\u003c/strong\u003e of something larger, even if they donГўв‚¬в„ўt fully understand it yet.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 7: Departure\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLew needs one day to settle his affairs in Stairwatch (or less, if the PCs are in a hurry and help him pack). He travels light: a pack, a knife, his whittling bone, and equipment that suggests heГўв‚¬в„ўs been on the road more than heГўв‚¬в„ўs been home.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eBefore They Leave\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHild the innkeeper\u003c/strong\u003e packs them extra rations (on the house, if the PCs helped with the mine). \"Bring that one-eyed bastard back alive. He owes me.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSolvi, the young Ember-Keeper,\u003c/strong\u003e approaches the PCs at the Ever-Ember. SheГўв‚¬в„ўs heard theyГўв‚¬в„ўre heading into the Interior Belt. She presses a coal-ember into a small iron box and gives it to the party: the @UUID[Item.SVH0EmberCoal001]{SolviГўв‚¬в„ўs Ember-Coal Box}. Гўв‚¬Е“Take this. ItГўв‚¬в„ўs not much. ButГўв‚¬В¦ donГўв‚¬в„ўt let the fire die. Please.Гўв‚¬Вќ (This ember can be used once to ignite a campfire that burns warm for 8 hours regardless of weather. Mechanically: automatic success on one fire-related montage test.)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eA silver-eyed crow\u003c/strong\u003e perches on the gate post, watching the road southeast. It doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt startle when approached Гўв‚¬вЂќ just tilts its head, then lifts away south. (GM note: A Wyrd-touched bird. GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs network uses corrupted carrion birds as spotters. Dreyfus, still at HaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs side in Hrafnborg, relayed the partyГўв‚¬в„ўs planned route via Wyrd-channels when he overheard their departure preparations.)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eGrafvitnir Pressure Check\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eRoll the Grafvitnir Pressure Check (d6) as the PCs prepare to leave:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eRoll\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eEffect\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e1-2\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eNo activity. DreyfusГўв‚¬в„ўs intelligence hasnГўв‚¬в„ўt reached field agents yet Гўв‚¬вЂќ the network is slow this far from Hrafnborg.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e3-4\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eA stranger at the Bone Market asks Hild about the PCs\u0027 destination. Hild says nothing, but mentions it to the PCs as a warning. (GM note: A Pale Maw informant acting on intelligence relayed through the network.)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e5\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe Chainwarden post receives a raven the morning the PCs plan to leave. Deputy Freja comes to the inn asking pointed questions. The PCs must talk fast or leave immediately. (GM note: A corrupted official responding to network directives.)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e6\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eRath (from Option B, or a different agent if you used Option A) is found dead in his room. A rune is carved into his palm: the mark of the Pale Maw. Stairwatch goes into lockdown. The PCs must escape town (Easy montage, 2 rounds) or wait a day and miss their window.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eOutcomes\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBy the end of this beat, the PCs should have:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFound and allied with Lew Tosferd.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCompleted a local task that established their competence and moral compass.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLearned that Lew and Gragnir have a shared history (the eye, the old job, the injury).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLearned KaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs direction: deep in the Ashen Woods (the Great Green).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAdvanced to Level 2.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFelt GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs network tightening (suspicious strangers, pointed questions, silver-eyed birds, a sense of being watched).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#2a6a2a;\"\u003eBeat 5 Гўв‚¬вЂќ Victory Point Summary\u003c/h4\u003e\u003cp style=\"font-style:italic; color:#555; margin-top:6px;\"\u003eOne local task (A or B) is required before Lew agrees. Both A and B award VP if completed.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:8px 0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#c0e0c0;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eEvent\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eDifficulty\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eVP Award\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 3: Negotiation with Lew\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eModerate (I3/P4)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e1 VP on success\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 4 Option A: Barrow-Wight Combat\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHard (L2 Boss)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e2 VP on victory\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 4 Option B: Negotiation with Rath\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eModerate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e1 VP on success\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#98cc98;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eBeat Total (Mandatory)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003e2-3 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#2a6a2a;\"\u003eBeat 5 Гўв‚¬вЂќ Victory Point Summary\u003c/h4\u003e\u003cp style=\"font-style:italic; color:#555; margin-top:6px;\"\u003eOne local task (A or B) is required before Lew agrees. Both A and B award VP if completed.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:8px 0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#c0e0c0;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eEvent\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eDifficulty\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eVP Award\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 3: Negotiation with Lew\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eModerate (I3/P4)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e1 VP on success\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 4 Option A: Barrow-Wight Combat\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHard (L2 Boss)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e2 VP on victory\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 4 Option B: Negotiation with Rath\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eModerate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e1 VP on success\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#98cc98;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eBeat Total (Mandatory)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003e2-3 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eTransition to Beat 6\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe party departs Stairwatch heading southeast with Lew as guide. The road ahead passes through failing farmland, abandoned villages, and finally into the skeletal remains of the Great GreenwealdГўв‚¬вЂќnow called the Ashen Woods.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eProceed to \u003cstrong\u003eBeat 6: The Great Green\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","markdown":null},"src":null,"system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"sort":50,"flags":{},"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"exportSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"draw-steel","systemVersion":"0.10.0","createdTime":0,"modifiedTime":0,"lastModifiedBy":null}},{"_id":"RTFPAGE000000023","name":"Beat 6 Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Great Green","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 2\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eDuration:\u003c/strong\u003e 2Гўв‚¬вЂњ3 sessions\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eLocation:\u003c/strong\u003e Interior Belt ГўвЂ вЂ™ Ashen Woods (or Bone Fields / Frozen Steppe) ГўвЂ вЂ™ approaching the Green Heart\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eKey NPCs:\u003c/strong\u003e Lew Tosferd (guide), Gragnir (possible brief appearance)\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard Montage Test (3 rounds), 2 combat encounters, negotiation, route choice, Grafvitnir network pressure\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eTone:\u003c/strong\u003e Haunted landscape, creeping dread, beauty amid ruin, the world is dying\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1a3a; color:#c8c8e8; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4a4ac8;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVP Status Гўв‚¬вЂќ Entering This Beat\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cstrong\u003eTotal VP (max):\u003c/strong\u003e 11 | \u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 | \u003cstrong\u003eVP into Level:\u003c/strong\u003e 11\u003cbr\u003e\u003cem style=\"font-size:0.9em;\"\u003eBranch beat - players choose the Ashen Woods OR Bone Fields route, not both.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1a3a; color:#c8c8e8; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4a4ac8;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVP Status Гўв‚¬вЂќ Entering This Beat\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cstrong\u003eTotal VP (max):\u003c/strong\u003e 11 | \u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 | \u003cstrong\u003eVP into Level:\u003c/strong\u003e 11\u003cbr\u003e\u003cem style=\"font-size:0.9em;\"\u003eBranch beat - players choose the Ashen Woods OR Bone Fields route, not both.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2\u003eOverview\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe longest leg of Act 1. The PCs travel southeast from Stairwatch, across the failing Interior Belt, and ultimately to the Green HeartГўв‚¬вЂќthe last surviving grove of the Great Greenweald.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDistance:\u003c/strong\u003e ~160 miles via the Ashen Woods (primary route), or ~125 miles via the Bone Fields and Frozen Steppe (alternate route)\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eDuration:\u003c/strong\u003e ~9 days (Ashen Woods) or ~7 days (Bone Fields) Гўв‚¬вЂќ mildly hindered terrain throughout (18 miles/day)\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eCalendar:\u003c/strong\u003e Departure approximately SГѓВіlmГѓВЎnuГѓВ°ur 20th; arrival approximately SГѓВіlmГѓВЎnuГѓВ°ur 28thГўв‚¬вЂњ29th\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe journey is broken into three montage test rounds separated by combat encounters, narrative interludes, and points of interest. By the time the PCs reach the Green Heart, they should understand what the world has lostГўв‚¬вЂќand what, impossibly, still clings to life.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 1: The Route Choice\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBefore departure from Stairwatch, Lew presents the options. This is a meaningful player decision.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLew spreads a stained map across the table at the Broken Stair. His amber eye glows faintlyГўв‚¬вЂќbrighter when his finger traces southeast.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Two ways to get where weГўв‚¬в„ўre going,\" he says, tapping the map. \"Neither is good.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe draws a long curve south. \"Through the Ashen Woods. WhatГўв‚¬в„ўs left of the Great Greenweald. Hundred and sixty miles of charcoal and silence. Slow goingГўв‚¬вЂќthe roads are gone, the ground is treacherous, and the things living in the char donГўв‚¬в„ўt like visitors.\" He pauses. \"But thereГўв‚¬в„ўs cover. Shelter. And the woods areГўв‚¬В¦Гўв‚¬вЂ№ connected to where weГўв‚¬в„ўre going. WeГўв‚¬в„ўll find the trail.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHis finger shifts east, cutting a straighter line across open ground. \"Or through the Bone Fields. Hundred and twenty-five milesГўв‚¬вЂќshorter, faster. But the Fields are open country. No cover, no shelter, and the cold is worse than anything youГўв‚¬в„ўve felt. ThereГўв‚¬в„ўs a reason they call it the Frozen Steppe on the far side.\" He taps his amber eye. \"IГўв‚¬в„ўve been through the Fields before. With Gragnir. It didnГўв‚¬в„ўt go well.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe looks at you.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Your call.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: Route Choice\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBoth routes lead to the Green Heart. The choice affects the \u003cstrong\u003echaracter\u003c/strong\u003e of the journey, not the destination.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAshen Woods (160 miles, ~9 days):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLonger but with more shelter and cover.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs travel through devastated forestГўв‚¬вЂќoppressive, haunted, but navigable.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs network has a \u003cstrong\u003eharder\u003c/strong\u003e time tracking them (the dead woods confuse the Wyrd-touched carrion birds and informant chains).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMore biological threats: blighted beasts, poisoned water, corrupted root-things.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLewГўв‚¬в„ўs eye pulls them unerringly through the pathless interior.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBetter connection to the Green HeartГўв‚¬в„ўs storyГўв‚¬вЂќthey see what the world lost.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBone Fields / Frozen Steppe (125 miles, ~7 days):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eShorter but brutally exposed.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Bone Fields are an ancient killing groundГўв‚¬вЂќbones of men and giants jut from the frozen earth. The Steppe beyond is flat, featureless tundra.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs network can observe them easily on open ground (+1 to all Grafvitnir Pressure Checks on this route).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMore undead threats: the Fields are rich with restless dead. The SteppeГўв‚¬в„ўs cold tests endurance.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLew has personal history here (opens his backstory about Gragnir earlier).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGreater tactical risk but faster arrivalГўв‚¬вЂќimportant if the PCs suspect a time pressure.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the players canГўв‚¬в„ўt decide, Lew recommends the Ashen Woods: \"I know the Fields. ThatГўв‚¬в„ўs exactly why I donГўв‚¬в„ўt want to go back.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Ashen Woods route is detailed as the \u003cstrong\u003eprimary path\u003c/strong\u003e below. The Bone Fields route follows as an \u003cstrong\u003ealternate path\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eThe Ashen Woods Route\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 2: Setting the Scene\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Dead Farms\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSouth of Stairwatch, the world opens up. The mountains fall behind you, and the Interior Belt unfolds: flat grey fields that should be farmland, dotted with crofts that have gone dark. Fences still stand, but nothing grows behind them. Silos stand open and empty. Animal pens hold only snow.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLew walks ahead, his amber eye half-closed, one hand gesturing southeast like a man following a sound only he can hear.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"SheГўв‚¬в„ўs still there,\" he says, every morning and every evening. \"Still alive. Still hiding.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe roadГўв‚¬вЂќwhatГўв‚¬в„ўs left of itГўв‚¬вЂќleads into the grey.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Ashen Woods\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe first sign is the smell: charcoal and wet ash, as if the fire that burned here never quite stopped smouldering. Then the trees begin.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThey arenГўв‚¬в„ўt trees anymore. TheyГўв‚¬в„ўre pillars of charcoalГўв‚¬вЂќsixty, seventy feet tall, stripped of bark and branch, standing in rows that go on forever. The Great Greenweald was a forest. Now itГўв‚¬в„ўs a graveyard of wood.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eNothing moves. Nothing calls. The only sound is the crunch of char under your boots and the occasional \u003cstrong\u003ecrack\u003c/strong\u003e of a dead trunk giving way to its own weight.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe sky is grey. The ground is grey. The trees are black.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAnd deep in the distance, LewГўв‚¬в„ўs eye pulls you on.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: The Ashen Woods Atmosphere\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Ashen Woods are not dangerous because of obvious monsters. TheyГўв‚¬в„ўre dangerous because theyГўв‚¬в„ўre \u003cstrong\u003ewrong\u003c/strong\u003e. The War of Fire (Year 2 of Fimbulwinter) burned the Great Greenweald deliberatelyГўв‚¬вЂќto deny cover to enemies and produce fuel. WhatГўв‚¬в„ўs left is a landscape that shouldnГўв‚¬в„ўt exist: a forest-shaped absence.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKey sensory details to deploy:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSilence.\u003c/strong\u003e No birds, no insects, no wind through leaves. The silence is \u003cstrong\u003eaggressive\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќit pushes back against conversation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCharcoal dust.\u003c/strong\u003e Everything is covered in a fine black powder. It gets in clothes, lungs, eyes. By the end of day one, the PCs are grey-black from head to foot.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eScale.\u003c/strong\u003e The forest was enormous. The dead trunks go on for \u003cstrong\u003emiles\u003c/strong\u003e in every direction. It takes days to cross. The monotony is its own hazard.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe occasional green.\u003c/strong\u003e Every few miles, a small patch of moss or a single green shoot pushes through the char. These are the woods trying to come back. TheyГўв‚¬в„ўre failing, but theyГўв‚¬в„ўre trying.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 3: Montage Test Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Long Road\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Montage Test (Ashen Woods) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 VP on success, 1 VP partial, 0 VP failure (2 rounds)\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Montage Test (Ashen Woods) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 VP on success, 1 VP partial, 0 VP failure (2 rounds)\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eParty Size Adjustment (4 heroes + Lew as NPC companion):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDifficulty\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eSuccess Limit\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eFailure Limit\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHard (adjusted)\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e6\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e2\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRounds:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 montage test rounds. Insert combat encounters between rounds.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLewГўв‚¬в„ўs Contribution:\u003c/strong\u003e Lew assists one PCГўв‚¬в„ўs test per round (his choice if the players donГўв‚¬в„ўt ask). He uses Intuition (+4) or Reason (+2) to assist. He also provides automatic navigationГўв‚¬вЂќthe PCs cannot get \u003cstrong\u003elost\u003c/strong\u003e while LewГўв‚¬в„ўs eye is active. They can be delayed, ambushed, or worn down, but not lost.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eRound 1: The Dead Farms (Days 1Гўв‚¬вЂњ3)\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eChallenge\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCharacteristic\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDescription\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eNavigate the failing road network\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eReason\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCollapsed bridges, missing markers, roads that end in frozen bogs. Plot a route through the decay.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eScavenge supplies from abandoned crofts\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eIntuition\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe farmsteads arenГўв‚¬в„ўt emptyГўв‚¬вЂќtheyГўв‚¬в„ўre \u003cstrong\u003eabandoned\u003c/strong\u003e. Find preserved food, firewood, rope, tools. medium Reason test to find something useful without triggering a trap or collapse.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eEndure the cold and manage rationing\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eMight\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe Interior Belt is colder than the coast. The wind cuts. Frostbite is a real threat for the unprepared.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAvoid refugee columns\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePresence / Agility\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eFamilies fleeing southwest toward Hrafnborg clog the road. The PCs need to avoid drawing attention. Questions about their directionГўв‚¬вЂќheading \u003cstrong\u003esoutheast\u003c/strong\u003e when everyone else flees \u003cstrong\u003esouthwest\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќwill raise suspicion.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCross a frozen river\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAgility\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe ice looks solid. It isnГўв‚¬в„ўt. The current beneath is fast and cold enough to kill in minutes.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eKeep morale up at camp\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePresence\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe landscape is crushing. The PCs need to keep each other (and Lew) from despair. Stories, songs, small comforts.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eRound 1 Interlude: The Last Farm\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBetween Round 1 and the combat encounter, stage this brief scene:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe last farmstead before the Ashen Woods is larger than the others. A proper longhouse, stone-built, with a turf roof thatГўв‚¬в„ўs still mostly intact. The door is barred from the \u003cstrong\u003eoutside\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eInside: a familyГўв‚¬в„ўs belongings, neatly packed. A note on the table, weighted with a stone. The handwriting is shaky:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e\"We go southwest. May the Ember at Hrafnborg still burn. If you read this and the fire is outГўв‚¬вЂќGod help you. God help us all.\"\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Ever-Ember niche in the wall is cold. The ash is weeks old.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLet the PCs react. If they search the house: preserved food (1 dayГўв‚¬в„ўs rations), a good hand-axe, and a childГўв‚¬в„ўs doll left behind on a bed. The dollГўв‚¬в„ўs face is turned toward the southГўв‚¬вЂќtoward the woodsГўв‚¬вЂќas if watching something.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 4: Combat Encounter Гўв‚¬вЂќ Rot-Beasts at the Treeline\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Combat (Ashen Woods) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on victory\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Combat (Ashen Woods) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on victory\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAs the PCs leave the farms and enter the Ashen Woods, the first real threats emerge.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eContext\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Ashen Woods\u0027 charcoal shell hides something worse than dead trees. The burning didnГўв‚¬в„ўt kill everythingГўв‚¬вЂќsome things \u003cstrong\u003echanged\u003c/strong\u003e. Animals warped by the blight that followed the fire: rot-touched, aggressive, territorial. They donГўв‚¬в„ўt attack for food. They attack because their territory has been violated.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Encounter\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSetting:\u003c/strong\u003e The treelineГўв‚¬вЂќthe border between open farmland and the burnt forest. Charcoal trunks rise like prison bars. The ground is soft with ash and hidden roots.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEnemies:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e7 Rot-Beasts\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 2 Brute Minion)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e2 Vine Stranglers\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 2 Ambusher Elite)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eRot-Beast (Blighted Boar)\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eRot-Beast Гўв‚¬вЂќ Draw Steel NPC\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLevel 2 Brute Standard\u003c/strong\u003e | \u003cstrong\u003eEV 10\u003c/strong\u003e | \u003cstrong\u003eBeast, Blighted\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eStamina:\u003c/strong\u003e 40 | \u003cstrong\u003eSpeed:\u003c/strong\u003e 6 (walk) | \u003cstrong\u003eSize:\u003c/strong\u003e M | \u003cstrong\u003eStability:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 | \u003cstrong\u003eFree Strike:\u003c/strong\u003e 5\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCharacteristics:\u003c/strong\u003e Might +3, Agility +1, Reason ГўЛ†вЂ™3, Intuition +1, Presence ГўЛ†вЂ™2\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFeatures:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCharge:\u003c/strong\u003e When the Rot-Beast moves 3+ squares in a straight line before a strike, the strike deals +5 damage.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBlighted Hide:\u003c/strong\u003e Any creature that makes a melee free strike against the Rot-Beast takes 3 corruption damage (thorns, spines, and fungal barbs).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAbilities:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGore\u003c/strong\u003e (Action, Melee 1, Might): 4/7/10 + Might damage. On tier 3, the target is pushed 2 squares and falls prone.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFrenzy\u003c/strong\u003e (Triggered: the Rot-Beast drops below half stamina): The Rot-Beast gains +2 to all damage and +2 speed for the rest of combat. It attacks the nearest creature, ally or enemy.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDirector Notes:\u003c/strong\u003e Open with a Charge for maximum impact. Rot-Beasts are dumb and aggressiveГўв‚¬вЂќthey donГўв‚¬в„ўt retreat, donГўв‚¬в„ўt coordinate, and become more dangerous as they die. The Frenzy trigger is their defining moment; signal it dramatically (\"The beast screamsГўв‚¬вЂќa sound like tearing woodГўв‚¬вЂќand its eyes blaze green\").\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eVine Strangler\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eVine Strangler Гўв‚¬вЂќ Draw Steel NPC\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLevel 2 Ambusher Standard\u003c/strong\u003e | \u003cstrong\u003eEV 10\u003c/strong\u003e | \u003cstrong\u003ePlant, Blighted\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eStamina:\u003c/strong\u003e 30 | \u003cstrong\u003eSpeed:\u003c/strong\u003e 4 (walk), 6 (burrow through ash/soil) | \u003cstrong\u003eSize:\u003c/strong\u003e M | \u003cstrong\u003eStability:\u003c/strong\u003e 0 | \u003cstrong\u003eFree Strike:\u003c/strong\u003e 4\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCharacteristics:\u003c/strong\u003e Might +2, Agility +3, Reason ГўЛ†вЂ™4, Intuition +2, Presence ГўЛ†вЂ™3\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFeatures:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAmbush:\u003c/strong\u003e The Vine Strangler is hidden at the start of combat (buried in the ash). Its first attack from hiding has an edge and deals +3 damage.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRootwalk:\u003c/strong\u003e The Vine Strangler can burrow through ash and soil at speed 6. While burrowed, it cannot be targeted by attacks.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAbilities:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eConstrict\u003c/strong\u003e (Action, Melee 1, Might): 3/6/9 + Might damage. On tier 2+, the target is grabbed (the target takes a bane on the Escape Grab maneuver). While grabbed, the target takes 3 ongoing damage at the start of each of their turns.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDrag Under\u003c/strong\u003e (Maneuver, Melee 1): A grabbed creature is pulled 1 square toward the Vine Strangler and the Strangler burrows, dragging the target partially underground. The target is restrained instead of grabbed until they escape (same DC). The Vine Strangler is treated as having cover while partially burrowed.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDirector Notes:\u003c/strong\u003e Open from hidingГўв‚¬вЂќburst out of the ash to Constrict a squishy target (caster or shadow). Then Drag Under to isolate them. The Rot-Beasts serve as distractions while the Strangler does the real damage. If Lew is targeted, he uses Smoke Bomb to escapeГўв‚¬вЂќheГўв‚¬в„ўs not supposed to die here.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eTerrain Features\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCharcoal Trunks:\u003c/strong\u003e Provide cover but are brittle. A trunk can be toppled (easy Might test, Action) onto an adjacent creature: 5 damage and the creature is prone. Each trunk can only be toppled once.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAsh Drifts:\u003c/strong\u003e Difficult terrain (3+ feet deep). Moving through them kicks up choking cloudsГўв‚¬вЂќa creature that ends its turn in an ash drift takes 2 damage (inhaled particulates) unless they cover their mouth.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHidden Roots:\u003c/strong\u003e In 3 random squares, concealed roots trip creatures. A creature entering the square for the first time must make an easy Agility test or fall prone.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eAftermath\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe beasts lie stillГўв‚¬вЂќor whatГўв‚¬в„ўs left of them. Up close, they barely look like animals. The boars\u0027 tusks are wood. Their hides are patchy with bark and fungus. The vine-thing dissolves into the ash, already rotting.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLew looks at the remains and says nothing for a long time.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"The woods are dying,\" he says finally. \"Everything in them is dying. But dying things fight hardest.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs investigate the remains (easy Reason test): the blight is organic, not magical. Something in the soilГўв‚¬вЂќin the \u003cstrong\u003eroot system\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќis corrupt. The trees burned, but the roots didnГўв‚¬в„ўt. Whatever lives in those roots is spreading poison through the ground.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 5: Montage Test Гўв‚¬вЂќ Round 2: Deep in the Ashen Woods (Days 4Гўв‚¬вЂњ6)\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAfter the combat, the montage continues. The woods close in. The silence deepens.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eRound 2 Sample Tests\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eChallenge\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCharacteristic\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDescription\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eNavigate the pathless interior\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eReason / Intuition\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eNo roads, no landmarks, just endless charcoal pillars. LewГўв‚¬в„ўs eye helps, but the PCs must find \u003cstrong\u003epassable\u003c/strong\u003e routes through deadfall and ash-choked ravines.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eResist the silence\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePresence\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe Ashen Woods are psychologically oppressive. The silence gets inside your head. Characters who fail this test become \u003cstrong\u003erattled\u003c/strong\u003e (ГўЛ†вЂ™2 to Presence tests) until the next rest.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCross the Char-Gorge\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAgility / Might\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eA ravine splits the forest floorГўв‚¬вЂќa riverbed that went dry after the fire. The sides are crumbling charcoal and exposed root networks. The bottom is 30 feet down and full of ash. Rope, climbing, or creative solutions needed.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eFind clean water\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eIntuition\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAll surface water in the Ashen Woods is taintedГўв‚¬вЂќgrey, ashy, sometimes actively corrosive. Finding a clean spring or knowing how to filter the water is critical.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eSpot GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs agents\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eIntuition\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eSilver-eyed carrion birds circle at the edge of vision. A figure on a far ridge moves against the wind. If noticed, the PCs realise theyГўв‚¬в„ўve been watched since Stairwatch Гўв‚¬вЂќ not by one pursuer, but by a network. If not noticed, the Grafvitnir Pressure Check result worsens.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCamp safely in the burn zone\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eReason\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe charcoal trunks are unstable. Setting camp under one is asking for it to collapse. Finding stable ground, clearing a firebreak, and keeping watch in a landscape where everything is the same colour of grey.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eRound 2 Interlude: The Green Thread\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eMidway through the deep woods, Lew stops.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"Shh.\" Lew holds up a hand. His amber eye is open, bright, almost pulsing.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe kneels and brushes ash away from the ground. Beneath the charГўв‚¬вЂќgreen. A single root, thick as a manГўв‚¬в„ўs arm, running through the dead soil. ItГўв‚¬в„ўs \u003cstrong\u003ealive\u003c/strong\u003e. Pale green bark, sap beading at the surface, warm to the touch.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLew follows it with his fingers. It runs southeastГўв‚¬вЂќthe same direction the eye has been pulling. Toward the centre of the woods.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"ThatГўв‚¬в„ўs not a tree root,\" he says quietly. \"ThatГўв‚¬в„ўs a \u003cstrong\u003etaproot\u003c/strong\u003e. Something at the centre of these woods is still alive. And itГўв‚¬в„ўs been feeding the whole forest from below, trying to bring it back.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe looks up at you. \"ThatГўв‚¬в„ўs where she is.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis root is a tendril of the Green HeartГўв‚¬вЂќthe surviving grove. It is old, deep, and connected ultimately to YggdrasilГўв‚¬в„ўs root network (though the PCs wonГўв‚¬в„ўt know this yet). Kaelen lives at the centre of this network.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 6: Point of Interest Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Charcoal Cathedral\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePlace this between Round 2 and Round 3, as the PCs push deeper into the Ashen Woods.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe trees change. Not in colourГўв‚¬вЂќstill black, still deadГўв‚¬вЂќbut in arrangement. The trunks here grow closer together, and their upper branches interlock overhead, forming a natural vault. The charcoal ceiling is fifty feet up. Ash motes drift downward like black snow.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIt looks like a cathedral. A vast nave of dead wood, pillared and vaulted, stretching southeast into darkness.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAnd on the \"altar\"Гўв‚¬вЂќa flat slab of stone in the clearing at the cathedralГўв‚¬в„ўs centreГўв‚¬вЂќsomeone has left an offering: a bowl of still-warm porridge, a clay cup of water, and a sprig of green holly.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSomeone is tending this place. Someone who is alive, nearby, and careful.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs wait: nothing happens. The offering is left by a \u003cstrong\u003echarcoal-burner\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќone of the last humans living in the Ashen Woods. She will not show herself unless the PCs leave an offering in return.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs leave food, a tool, or a kind word:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou hear a sound you havenГўв‚¬в„ўt heard in the woods: a human throat clearing.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA woman emerges from behind a pillar. She is thinГўв‚¬вЂќterribly thinГўв‚¬вЂќwith skin stained grey-black by years of charcoal dust. Her clothes are ash-coloured furs. She carries a handaxe and a leather satchel.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"YouГўв‚¬в„ўre heading for the green place,\" she says. It is not a question.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis is \u003cstrong\u003eSolveig the Burner\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќa former woodcutter who refused to leave when the forest was put to the torch. She has lived in the Ashen Woods for three years, burning charcoal for fuel, navigating by the root-patterns beneath the ash, and avoiding the blighted beasts.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat Solveig knows:\u003c/strong\u003e SheГўв‚¬в„ўs seen the Green Heart from a distanceГўв‚¬вЂќa \"wall of thorns and light.\" SheГўв‚¬в„ўs also seen the root-system growing beneath the ash. \"The ground is alive under the dead. The roots glow at nightГўв‚¬вЂќamber, like your friendГўв‚¬в„ўs eye.\" She glances at Lew.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat Solveig wants:\u003c/strong\u003e News. She hasnГўв‚¬в„ўt spoken to another person in four months. SheГўв‚¬в„ўll talk for hours if they let her. She also wants a \u003cstrong\u003eknife\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќhers is worn to a nub.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat Solveig offers:\u003c/strong\u003e If treated well, she shares a shortcut through the cathedral that saves half a dayГўв‚¬в„ўs travel (+1 edge on one test in Round 3). She also warns them about the Rootgnaw Brood: \"There are things that chew the green roots. Big as dogs. Bigger. They come from the deep ash, and theyГўв‚¬в„ўre getting bolder.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: Solveig\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSolveig is a survivorГўв‚¬вЂќnot a quest-giver, not a tragic victim, but a stubborn, practical human who decided the Ashen Woods are her home now. She represents the worldГўв‚¬в„ўs resilience. If the PCs are kind, she becomes a contact in the woods who may reappear in Act 2 (guiding allies through the Ashen Woods). If they ignore her, the offering goes cold, and the cathedral feels lonelier.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs harm her or take her supplies: she vanishes into the ash. She knows these woods better than anyone alive. They will not find her.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 7: Post-Montage Interlude Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Singing Stone\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe path opens into a clearingГўв‚¬вЂќone of the few spaces in the Ashen Woods where you can see the sky. At the clearingГўв‚¬в„ўs centre stands a stoneГўв‚¬вЂќnot a cairn, not a marker, but a single upright boulder of dark granite, roughly cylindrical, taller than a man.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eItГўв‚¬в„ўs \u003cstrong\u003ehumming\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eNot audiblyГўв‚¬вЂќyou feel it in your teeth, your fingertips, the soles of your boots. A vibration rising from the ground, channelled through the stone, and radiating outward. The ash on the ground around the stone has been pushed aside by the vibration, revealing bare earthГўв‚¬вЂќand roots. Dozens of roots, all converging on the stone like spokes on a wheel.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLew presses his palm against the stone. His eye flares bright amber.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"The Tree,\" he whispers. \"This stone is sitting on one of the TreeГўв‚¬в„ўs roots. A deep one. I can feel it all the way down. Miles down.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis is a \u003cstrong\u003eroot-node\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќa point where YggdrasilГўв‚¬в„ўs deep root network surfaces. The stone was placed here by the original Ember-Keepers as a marker. The PCs donГўв‚¬в„ўt know this yet, but in Act 2 these nodes become waypoints for their journey to the Emberwell.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf any PC touches the stone: they feel warmthГўв‚¬вЂќgenuine, deep warmth, like standing beside a great fire. For one moment, the Fimbulwinter cold lifts entirely. Then it returns, and the warmth fades, and the world is grey again.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf Kaelen were here, she would weep. The stone is still connected. The root is still alive.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 8: Montage Outcomes\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 style=\"color:#66ff66;\"\u003eTotal Success (5+ successes before failure limit)\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eArrive at the Green HeartГўв‚¬в„ўs outer boundary intact and relatively healthy.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEarn \u003cstrong\u003e2 Victories\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe party has supplies, composure, and time to prepare before entering the grove.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs network is \u003cstrong\u003ebehind\u003c/strong\u003e them Гўв‚¬вЂќ the dead woods disrupted Wyrd-channel tracking and the field agents lost the trail.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 style=\"color:#ffff66;\"\u003ePartial Success (failure limit hit, but 2+ more successes than failures)\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eArrive at the Green HeartГўв‚¬в„ўs boundary, but at cost. Choose one:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHeat cost:\u003c/strong\u003e Rations are critically low. The party is hungry, cold, and weakened (ГўЛ†вЂ™1 to Might tests until fed properly).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMorale cost:\u003c/strong\u003e The Ashen Woods have worn on the party. One PC is \u003cstrong\u003erattled\u003c/strong\u003e (ГўЛ†вЂ™2 to Presence tests until a respite).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTime cost:\u003c/strong\u003e The journey took longer than expected. GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs agents have caught up Гўв‚¬вЂќ the next Grafvitnir Pressure Check triggers automatically at 4+.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEarn \u003cstrong\u003e1 Victory\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 style=\"color:#ff6666;\"\u003eTotal Failure\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe party reaches the Green Heart, but is \u003cstrong\u003eexhausted and compromised\u003c/strong\u003e:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAll PCs lose 1 Recovery.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs network is \u003cstrong\u003eahead\u003c/strong\u003e of them Гўв‚¬вЂќ agents of the Pale Maw are waiting near the Green HeartГўв‚¬в„ўs boundary.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNo Victories. Director gains 4 additional Malice for the next combat.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLew is injured (twisted ankle crossing the Char-Gorge; he can walk but not run, ГўЛ†вЂ™2 speed until healed).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 9: Combat Encounter Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Rootgnaw Brood\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Combat (Ashen Woods) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 VP on victory\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Combat (Ashen Woods) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 VP on victory\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eNear the boundary of the Green Heart, where living roots push up through dead soil and patches of impossible green moss glow in the charcoal twilight, the PCs encounter the \u003cstrong\u003eRootgnaw Brood\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќcreatures that feed on the Green HeartГўв‚¬в„ўs living root system.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eContext\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThese arenГўв‚¬в„ўt natural animals. TheyГўв‚¬в„ўre \u003cstrong\u003eblight-spawn\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќthings born from the corruption in the Ashen Woods\u0027 soil that are drawn to the Green HeartГўв‚¬в„ўs life the way moths are drawn to flame. TheyГўв‚¬в„ўre trying to eat their way to the source. The dryads of the Green Heart have been fighting them for years.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Encounter\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSetting:\u003c/strong\u003e A clearing where living roots have broken through the charcoal crust. Green moss covers the ground. The air smells of sap and rot simultaneously. Three large rootsГўв‚¬вЂќeach as thick as a barrelГўв‚¬вЂќpulse with amber light.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEnemies:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e12 Rootgnaw Grubs\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 1 Harrier Minion)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e2 Rootgnaw Queens\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 3 Controller Platoon)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e1 Vine Strangler\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 2 Ambusher Elite)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eRootgnaw Grub\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eRootgnaw Grub Гўв‚¬вЂќ Draw Steel NPC\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLevel 1 Minion\u003c/strong\u003e | \u003cstrong\u003eBeast, Blighted\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eStamina:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 | \u003cstrong\u003eSpeed:\u003c/strong\u003e 5 (walk, burrow 3) | \u003cstrong\u003eSize:\u003c/strong\u003e S | \u003cstrong\u003eFree Strike:\u003c/strong\u003e 2\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCharacteristics:\u003c/strong\u003e Might +1, Agility +2, Reason ГўЛ†вЂ™4, Intuition +0, Presence ГўЛ†вЂ™3\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAbilities:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGnaw\u003c/strong\u003e (Action, Melee 1, Might): 2/4/6 damage. On any hit, the grub can latch onto the target (the target must use an action to remove it; while latched, 2 ongoing damage).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDirector Notes:\u003c/strong\u003e Minions. They swarm, they latch, they distract. Their purpose is to tie up PCs while the Queen does her work. If the PCs ignore them to focus on the Queen, the grubs chew through the living roots, which causes the Green Heart to \u003cstrong\u003escream\u003c/strong\u003e (psychic burst: all creatures take 3 psychic damage, save ends rattled).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eRootgnaw Queen\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eRootgnaw Queen Гўв‚¬вЂќ Draw Steel NPC\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLevel 3 Boss Standard\u003c/strong\u003e | \u003cstrong\u003eEV 15\u003c/strong\u003e | \u003cstrong\u003eBeast, Blighted\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eStamina:\u003c/strong\u003e 70 | \u003cstrong\u003eSpeed:\u003c/strong\u003e 5 (walk), 4 (burrow) | \u003cstrong\u003eSize:\u003c/strong\u003e L | \u003cstrong\u003eStability:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 | \u003cstrong\u003eFree Strike:\u003c/strong\u003e 6\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCharacteristics:\u003c/strong\u003e Might +3, Agility +1, Reason ГўЛ†вЂ™2, Intuition +2, Presence ГўЛ†вЂ™1\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFeatures:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRoot-Sense:\u003c/strong\u003e The Queen can detect any creature touching the ground within 10 squares, even while burrowed.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBrood-Mother:\u003c/strong\u003e At the start of each round, the Queen spawns 2 Rootgnaw Grubs in unoccupied squares within 2 squares of her.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBoss Action (1/round):\u003c/strong\u003e The Queen takes one additional action on initiative count 0.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAbilities:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMandible Crush\u003c/strong\u003e (Action, Melee 1, Might): 6/9/13 + Might damage. On tier 2+, the target is grabbed (the target takes a bane on the Escape Grab maneuver).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAcid Spray\u003c/strong\u003e (Action, Cone 3, Might): 4/7/10 acid damage. Squares hit become difficult terrain (acid slick) for the rest of the encounter.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBurrow Surge\u003c/strong\u003e (Maneuver): The Queen burrows and moves up to her burrow speed. This movement does not provoke opportunity attacks. She emerges at the end of the movement.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBoss Action:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSeismic Tremor\u003c/strong\u003e (Area, Burst 2 centred on the Queen): All creatures in the burst must succeed on an easy Agility test or fall prone. The ground cracks open, creating difficult terrain.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDirector Notes:\u003c/strong\u003e The Queen fights from below. Open with Burrow Surge to reposition, then Acid Spray to control the battlefield. Use Mandible Crush on grabbed targets while grubs swarm the loose PCs. The Boss ActionГўв‚¬вЂќSeismic TremorГўв‚¬вЂќshould be used when PCs cluster up. If the PCs protect the living roots (preventing grubs from chewing them), the roots pulse brighter and the Green Heart sends aid: at initiative count 20 of round 3, vines erupt from the ground and restrain 2 enemies (the Heart is \u003cstrong\u003eaware\u003c/strong\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eTerrain Features\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLiving Roots (3 locations):\u003c/strong\u003e Each root has 15 stamina. If a grub is adjacent to a root and not engaged, it chews the root for 3 damage per round. If all 3 roots are destroyed, the Green HeartГўв‚¬в„ўs defences weaken and Beat 7Гўв‚¬в„ўs negotiation becomes harder (ГўЛ†вЂ™1 to Patience). If 2+ roots survive, the PCs earn a nature-blessing: +2 to Presence tests during KaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs negotiation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGreen Moss:\u003c/strong\u003e Provides footing in an otherwise treacherous landscape. Squares with moss are \u003cstrong\u003enot\u003c/strong\u003e difficult terrain and provide stability.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCharcoal Pillars:\u003c/strong\u003e As beforeГўв‚¬вЂќcover, brittle, can be toppled.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eAftermath\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe QueenГўв‚¬в„ўs body twitches once, twice, then goes still. The grubs scatter into the ash. The clearing is quietГўв‚¬вЂќbut a different kind of quiet than the dead woods. This silence is \u003cstrong\u003ewaiting\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe three roots pulse brighter. Sap beads on their surfaces like sweat. And deep in the southeast, very faint, you hear something you havenГўв‚¬в„ўt heard since Hrafnborg.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBirdsong.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLew points. His eye is burning bright now, almost uncomfortable to look at. \"SheГўв‚¬в„ўs close. Maybe a dayГўв‚¬в„ўs travel. Maybe less.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГўЕЎвЂќГЇВёВЏ Loot\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs can harvest chitin plates from the Rootgnaw Queen\u0026rsquo;s corpse (medium Reason test to identify structurally sound plates, or easy Might test for brute extraction). Lew suggests the idea: \u0026ldquo;That shell\u0026rsquo;s tougher than anything you\u0026rsquo;ll find at a smith. Might want to keep some.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eA PC can assemble the @UUID[Item.SVH00ChitinBkl01]{Rootgnaw Chitin Buckler} during a respite. If the PCs protected 2+ living roots during the combat, the chitin retains stronger Yggdrasil resonance \u0026mdash; the Director may grant +1 to the reactive damage at 1st level.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Green Heart is ahead.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eThe Bone Fields Route (Alternate)\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: Running the Alternate Route\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs choose the Bone Fields, use this section instead of Parts 2Гўв‚¬вЂњ8 above. The beat still ends at the Green Heart (Part 9: Rootgnaw Brood continues as normal regardless of route taken), but the character of the journey is completely different.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Bone Fields route is \u003cstrong\u003eshorter but harsher\u003c/strong\u003e: open terrain, more undead, worse cold, and GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs network can observe them easily. It also unlocks LewГўв‚¬в„ўs backstory earlierГўв‚¬вЂќhe has history here.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Bone Fields: Setting\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEast of Stairwatch, the mountains give way to broken flatlandГўв‚¬вЂќa vast, wind-scoured basin where nothing grows and the wind never stops. The Bone Fields.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe name is literal. Bones jut from the frozen earth: ribs the size of longships, femurs as tall as pine trees, skulls half-buried with eye sockets wide enough to camp in. These are the bones of giantsГўв‚¬вЂќor something olderГўв‚¬вЂќfallen in a war so ancient that even the skalds have forgotten which side won.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBetween the bones: graves. Thousands of them. Stone-ringed barrows, a dayГўв‚¬в„ўs march in every direction, their capstones cracked and frost-heaved andГўв‚¬вЂќin too many casesГўв‚¬вЂќopen.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLew stands at the edge of the Fields and goes very still.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Last time I was here,\" he says quietly, \"the ground split open and something came out of the earth. Something old.\" He touches his amber eye. \"ThatГўв‚¬в„ўs where this came from.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe takes a breath. \"Stay close. DonГўв‚¬в„ўt touch the bones. And for the love of all thatГўв‚¬в„ўs warm, donГўв‚¬в„ўt open any barrows.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eBone Fields Montage Test\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Montage Test (Bone Fields) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 VP on success, 1 VP partial, 0 VP failure (2 rounds)\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Montage Test (Bone Fields) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 VP on success, 1 VP partial, 0 VP failure (2 rounds)\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eRounds:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 (shorter route, but harsher conditions)\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDifficulty\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eSuccess Limit\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eFailure Limit\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHard (adjusted)\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e6\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e2\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eRound 1: The Bone Fields (Days 1Гўв‚¬вЂњ3)\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eChallenge\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCharacteristic\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDescription\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eNavigate by the bones\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eReason\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eNo roads, no markersГўв‚¬вЂќjust giant bones. The locals navigated by naming the major skeleton formations. Lew remembers some: \"The Keel\" (a rib cage), \"The Throne\" (a pelvis), \"Old Three-Eyes\" (a skull). Without these landmarks, the party walks in circles.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eEndure the steppe wind\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eMight\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe Bone Fields are flat and exposed. The wind is a physical forceГўв‚¬вЂќconstant, bone-dry, and cold enough to freeze exposed skin in minutes. Characters without face-coverings take ongoing cold damage.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAvoid the open barrows\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eIntuition / Agility\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eSome barrow-capstones have shifted. Movement is visible inside. The PCs must route around these without stumbling into a nest of newly-risen dead.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCross the Shatter-Field\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAgility\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eA section of the Fields where the ground has cracked into irregular plates, separated by crevasses 3Гўв‚¬вЂњ6 feet deep. The plates shift underfoot. A wrong step plunges a leg into freezing water pooled at the bottom.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eResist the whispers\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePresence\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAt night, the wind carries sounds that arenГўв‚¬в„ўt wind: voices, scraps of language, names. The dead in the barrows talk in their sleep. Characters who listen too closely become \u003cstrong\u003efrightened\u003c/strong\u003e (bane on all tests) until dawn.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eKeep GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs scouts at bay\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eIntuition\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe Bone Fields offer no cover. GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs agent-birds Гўв‚¬вЂќ Valravn with silver eyes Гўв‚¬вЂќ can observe the party continuously. Spotting the observers and adjusting course to stay unpredictable helps.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eRound 1 Interlude: LewГўв‚¬в„ўs Story\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBy the campfire, sheltered in the lee of a giantГўв‚¬в„ўs shoulder blade:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLew stares into the fire. The amber eye reflects the flame strangelyГўв‚¬вЂќthe light bends toward it, as if the eye is drinking warmth.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Gragnir brought me here three years ago. A jobГўв‚¬вЂќfinding something heГўв‚¬в„ўd lost. A seed, he said. A seed the size of my fist, wrapped in leather. HeГўв‚¬в„ўd left it here \u0027for safekeeping.\u0027\" Lew laughs bitterly. \"\u0027Safekeeping.\u0027 In the Bone Fields.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe taps his bad eye. \"We found the seed. We also found something else. The ground cracked open beneath usГўв‚¬вЂќnot an earthquake, not a cave-in, something \u003cstrong\u003edeliberate\u003c/strong\u003e. Like the earth was opening its mouth. And out of the crack cameГўв‚¬В¦Гўв‚¬вЂ№ I donГўв‚¬в„ўt know what it was. Big. Old. Made of roots and bone and frozen soil. It looked at Gragnir and \u003cstrong\u003espoke\u003c/strong\u003e.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA long pause.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Gragnir spoke back. In a language I donГўв‚¬в„ўt knowГўв‚¬вЂќsomething that made my teeth ache and my eye bleed. The thing listened. Then it went back into the earth, and the crack closed, and Gragnir was holding the seed and my eye was gone.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe touches the amber gem.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"He put this in the socket himself. Said it was \u0027fair exchange for what the earth took.\u0027 I didnГўв‚¬в„ўt understand then.\" He looks at you. \"I still donГўв‚¬в„ўt. But I can feel the green thread, and I can find whatГўв‚¬в„ўs lost, and my dead eye sees more than the living one ever did.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis is the fullest telling of LewГўв‚¬в„ўs backstory the PCs will get in Act 1. It establishes:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGragnirГўв‚¬в„ўs deep connection to the earth and its inhabitants.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Bone Fields sit atop something ancient and awareГўв‚¬вЂќpart of YggdrasilГўв‚¬в„ўs root network.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLewГўв‚¬в„ўs eye-gem is literally part of the tree. It was given in exchange for a human eye, making Lew a living bridge between the mortal world and the deep roots.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eBone Fields Combat: Barrow Ambush\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Combat (Bone Fields) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 VP on victory\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Combat (Bone Fields) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 VP on victory\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOn the second night in the Fields, the dead come.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSetting:\u003c/strong\u003e The party is camped near a cluster of barrows. The wind has diedГўв‚¬вЂќunnaturally still. The moon is a pale smear behind clouds.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEnemies:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e5 Barrow-Draugr\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 2 Brute Minion)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e1 Grave-Singer\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 2 Controller Elite)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e1 Barrow-Warden\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 2 Support Elite)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e1 Barrow-Sentinel\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 3 Brute Elite вЂ” new)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eBarrow-Draugr\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eBarrow-Draugr Гўв‚¬вЂќ Draw Steel NPC\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLevel 2 Brute Standard\u003c/strong\u003e | \u003cstrong\u003eEV 10\u003c/strong\u003e | \u003cstrong\u003eUndead\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eStamina:\u003c/strong\u003e 35 | \u003cstrong\u003eSpeed:\u003c/strong\u003e 5 (walk) | \u003cstrong\u003eSize:\u003c/strong\u003e M | \u003cstrong\u003eStability:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 | \u003cstrong\u003eFree Strike:\u003c/strong\u003e 5\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCharacteristics:\u003c/strong\u003e Might +3, Agility +0, Reason ГўЛ†вЂ™3, Intuition +1, Presence ГўЛ†вЂ™2\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFeatures:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eUndead Resilience:\u003c/strong\u003e Immune to poison, fear, and sleep. Takes double damage from fire.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGrave-Bound:\u003c/strong\u003e While within 5 squares of an open barrow, the Barrow-Draugr regains 5 stamina at the start of each of its turns.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAbilities:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRusted Blade\u003c/strong\u003e (Action, Melee 1, Might): 4/7/10 damage. On tier 2+, the target takes 3 ongoing poison damage (infected wound).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDeath Grip\u003c/strong\u003e (Maneuver, Melee 1): The target is grabbed. A grabbed creature feels the cold of the grave seeping into their bodyГўв‚¬вЂќthey take 2 cold damage at the start of each of their turns while grabbed.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDirector Notes:\u003c/strong\u003e Barrow-Draugr fight near their graves. They pull targets in with Death Grip and let the cold do the work. Smart PCs will draw them \u003cstrong\u003eaway\u003c/strong\u003e from their barrows to deny the regeneration, or seal the barrows (medium Might test to roll the capstone back).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eGrave-Singer\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eGrave-Singer Гўв‚¬вЂќ Draw Steel NPC\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLevel 2 Controller Standard\u003c/strong\u003e | \u003cstrong\u003eEV 10\u003c/strong\u003e | \u003cstrong\u003eUndead, Spirit\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eStamina:\u003c/strong\u003e 25 | \u003cstrong\u003eSpeed:\u003c/strong\u003e 6 (fly, hover) | \u003cstrong\u003eSize:\u003c/strong\u003e M | \u003cstrong\u003eStability:\u003c/strong\u003e 0 | \u003cstrong\u003eFree Strike:\u003c/strong\u003e 3\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCharacteristics:\u003c/strong\u003e Might ГўЛ†вЂ™1, Agility +2, Reason +0, Intuition +3, Presence +3\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFeatures:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eIncorporeal:\u003c/strong\u003e The Grave-Singer takes half damage from non-magical physical attacks. Force and fire damage is full.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGrave-Song:\u003c/strong\u003e At the start of the Grave-SingerГўв‚¬в„ўs turn, each living creature within 5 squares must succeed on a easy Presence test or become \u003cstrong\u003eslowed\u003c/strong\u003e (speed halved) until the end of their next turn The song is mournful, droning, and fills the mind with the desire to lie down and sleep.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAbilities:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDirge\u003c/strong\u003e (Action, Range 8, Presence): 3/6/9 psychic damage. On tier 2+, the target is also \u003cstrong\u003edazed\u003c/strong\u003e (can take only one action on their next turn).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRaise the Fallen\u003c/strong\u003e (Maneuver, Range 5): One destroyed Barrow-Draugr is raised with 15 stamina. The Grave-Singer can only use this once per encounter.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDirector Notes:\u003c/strong\u003e The Grave-Singer stays at range, using Grave-Song to slow the PCs and Dirge to daze the most dangerous fighter. The Barrow-Draugr advance to grab slowed targets. If the PCs focus the Singer first (smart), it uses Raise the Fallen to bring back a draugr as a distraction while it retreats. Fire is the answer to everything in this fight.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eTerrain\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOpen Barrows:\u003c/strong\u003e 3 barrows are open. Draugr within 5 squares regain stamina. PCs can seal barrows (medium Might test) to deny this healing.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGiant Bones:\u003c/strong\u003e Enormous ribs and vertebrae provide cover and elevated positions. Climbing a bone is easy Agility test.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFrozen Ground:\u003c/strong\u003e The entire battlefield is lightly difficult terrain. Characters who are pushed or knocked prone slide 1 additional square.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eAftermath\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe dead lie down. The singerГўв‚¬в„ўs voice fades into the wind. The barrows are quiet againГўв‚¬вЂќbut the silence feels temporary, like the pause between breaths.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLew kneels beside one of the draugr. Its armour is oldГўв‚¬вЂќgenerations oldГўв‚¬вЂќbut the runes embossed on the breastplate are still legible. He traces them with a finger.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"These werenГўв‚¬в„ўt warriors,\" he says. \"They were \u003cstrong\u003efarmers\u003c/strong\u003e. LookГўв‚¬вЂќploughshare runes, harvest-knots. They died before the giants fell. Before any of this.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe stands. \"The Fields go deep. Deeper than bone. LetГўв‚¬в„ўs not be here when something deeper decides to wake up.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eRound 2: The Frozen Steppe (Days 4Гўв‚¬вЂњ7)\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBeyond the Bone Fields, the terrain flattens into featureless tundraГўв‚¬вЂќthe Frozen Steppe. The party must cross this to reach the Green Heart from the east.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eChallenge\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCharacteristic\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDescription\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eNavigate featureless terrain\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eReason / Intuition\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eNo landmarks, no trees, no features. Navigation is by sun-position (barely visible), wind-direction, and LewГўв‚¬в„ўs eye. A wrong heading loses hours.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eEndure extreme cold exposure\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eMight\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe Steppe is the coldest place the PCs have been. The wind-chill is lethal. Characters must manage layers, rotation of exposed skin, and movement patterns to survive.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCross a pressure-ice field\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAgility\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe Steppe crosses a frozen plain where competing ice plates have buckled upward, creating a jagged maze of ice ridges and crevasses. Navigation through is slow and physically dangerous.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eSpot the treeline (or its absence)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eIntuition\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe Green Heart should be visible from the SteppeГўв‚¬вЂќa dark line on the horizon. But the Heart is hidden by some means. Finding it requires LewГўв‚¬в„ўs eye or a keen-eyed scout who notices where the skyГўв‚¬в„ўs colour \u003cstrong\u003echanges\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eResist isolation madness\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePresence\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eSeven days of travel with nothing to look at. The SteppeГўв‚¬в„ўs emptiness erodes sanity. Characters begin seeing landmarks that arenГўв‚¬в„ўt there, hearing voices in the wind, or turning around to walk back north.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eManage a supply crisis\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eReason\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eSeven days through barren terrain with no foraging opportunities. If supplies werenГўв‚¬в„ўt carefully managed from Stairwatch, the party faces genuine starvation. Rationing, hunting (for what?), or desperate measures.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eRound 2 Interlude: The Sky Changes\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLew stops. HeГўв‚¬в„ўs been stopping more oftenГўв‚¬вЂќhis eye burns, his head aches, and twice today heГўв‚¬в„ўs turned in a slow circle and pointed in a slightly different direction, correcting something only he can feel.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBut now heГўв‚¬в„ўs not correcting. HeГўв‚¬в„ўs staring south.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Look at the sky,\" he says.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou look. It takes a moment to see it. The sky over the Steppe is greyГўв‚¬вЂќthe same grey itГўв‚¬в„ўs been for a week. But to the south, near the horizon, the grey isГўв‚¬В¦Гўв‚¬вЂ№ different. Darker. Richer. Not storm-cloudsГўв‚¬вЂќsomething organic. Something that absorbs light rather than blocking it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"ThatГўв‚¬в„ўs the canopy,\" Lew says. His voice is awed. \"The trees. The \u003cstrong\u003ereal\u003c/strong\u003e trees. The Heart is still growing.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe points. \"Two days. Maybe less.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe party has spotted the Green HeartГўв‚¬в„ўs edge from the east. They still need to navigate to it, but they now have a visual bearing. The Heart appears as a dark smudge on the horizonГўв‚¬вЂќthe only thing taller than grass-height for fifty miles.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eBone Fields Route: Montage Outcomes\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe outcomes are identical to the Ashen Woods route (see Part 8 above), with one modification:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOn \u003cstrong\u003ePartial Success\u003c/strong\u003e or \u003cstrong\u003eTotal Failure\u003c/strong\u003e, add: GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs network has tracked them across the open ground. The Grafvitnir Pressure Check at the end of this beat triggers at +1 (the Bone Fields offered no concealment).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAfter the montage concludes, the party approaches the Green Heart from the east and encounters the Rootgnaw Brood (Part 9, above) at the HeartГўв‚¬в„ўs boundary regardless of route taken.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eGrafvitnir Pressure Check\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eRoll the Grafvitnir Pressure Check (d6) at the end of this beat:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eRoll\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eEffect\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e1-2\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eNo network activity. The Ashen Woods disrupted Wyrd-channel tracking, or the Bone Fields\u0027 restless dead interfered with the informant chains. GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs field agents have fallen behind.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e3-4\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe PCs find tracks near their campsite: booted feet, not animal. Someone circled the camp and left heading south. A Pale Maw informant has pinpointed their position and reported it through the network.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e5\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eA flock of \u003cstrong\u003eValravn\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ carrion-birds with silver eyes Гўв‚¬вЂќ circles above the party for an hour. They donГўв‚¬в„ўt attack, but theyГўв‚¬в„ўre clearly observing. Grafvitnir doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt need agents on the ground when his masterГўв‚¬в„ўs eyes are in the sky.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e6\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDirect encounter: a Pale Maw agent (Level 2 human cultist, Shadow-type) attempts to ambush the party at camp. The agent carries a message carved in bone: \"The Wolf remembers. The tree forgets.\" If captured, the agent knows nothing useful Гўв‚¬вЂќ theyГўв‚¬в„ўre a zealot, not a strategist. They received their orders through the network and have never met Dreyfus or Grafvitnir.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eLew Character Development\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eDuring the long journey, Lew opens upГўв‚¬вЂќnot all at once, but in small moments. Seed these conversations into rest stops and quiet travel:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAbout Gragnir:\u003c/strong\u003e \"We worked together years ago. A job in the Bone-FieldsГўв‚¬вЂќdonГўв‚¬в„ўt ask. He saved my life. I lost my eye. He gave me the gem as payment. \u0027Fair trade,\u0027 he said.\" A pause. \"IГўв‚¬в„ўm still not sure he was wrong.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAbout the finding-gift:\u003c/strong\u003e \"ItГўв‚¬в„ўs not magic. Or if it is, itГўв‚¬в„ўs the kind of magic that doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt know itГўв‚¬в„ўs magic. The eye justГўв‚¬В¦Гўв‚¬вЂ№ remembers where things were, and notices when theyГўв‚¬в„ўre not there anymore. Like an itch you canГўв‚¬в„ўt scratch until you find whatГўв‚¬в„ўs missing.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAbout Kaelen:\u003c/strong\u003e \"Never met her. But IГўв‚¬в„ўve heard the name. Gragnir mentioned her onceГўв‚¬вЂќsaid she was \u0027the best and worst thing to happen to Hrafnborg.\u0027 WouldnГўв‚¬в„ўt explain what he meant.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAbout himself:\u003c/strong\u003e \"I donГўв‚¬в„ўt have a home. I have rooms I sleep in more than others. Stairwatch is the closest thing, and thatГўв‚¬в„ўs only because Hild hasnГўв‚¬в„ўt kicked me out yet.\" A smile. \"I find things for people. ThatГўв‚¬в„ўs what I do. ItГўв‚¬в„ўs not heroic. But itГўв‚¬в„ўs useful.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: LewГўв‚¬в„ўs Backstory Pacing\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf the party took the Bone Fields route, LewГўв‚¬в„ўs full Gragnir story has already been told (see the Bone Fields interlude above). In that case, use these conversation beats to fill in the \u003cstrong\u003eother\u003c/strong\u003e detailsГўв‚¬вЂќhis finding-gift, his knowledge of Kaelen, his sense of himself.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the party took the Ashen Woods route, these are the primary opportunities for LewГўв‚¬в„ўs backstory. The Bone Fields story can be told in abbreviated form around a campfire: \"I went there once with Gragnir. Lost my eye. Got this instead.\" He doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt elaborate unless pushed.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eOutcomes\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBy the end of this beat, the PCs should have:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCrossed the Interior Belt and reached the Green Heart via the Ashen Woods or the Bone Fields.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eExperienced the devastation of the burned / frozen world firsthand.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSurvived combats appropriate to their route (Rot-Beasts + Rootgnaw, or Barrow-Draugr + Rootgnaw).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDiscovered elements of the living root network that connects the Green Heart to Yggdrasil.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMet people surviving in the wasteland (Solveig in the Ashen Woods; or faced the deeper loneliness of the Bone Fields).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBonded with Lew through shared hardship and conversation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eArrived at the boundary of the Green Heart with a heading on Kaelen.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFelt GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs network tighten or temporarily loosen.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#2a6a2a;\"\u003eBeat 6 Гўв‚¬вЂќ Victory Point Summary\u003c/h4\u003e\u003cp style=\"font-style:italic; color:#555; margin-top:6px;\"\u003eBranch - only one route is played. Both routes yield approximately 4-5 VP.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:8px 0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#c0e0c0;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eEvent\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eDifficulty\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eVP Award\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAshen Woods Montage (2 rounds)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHard\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e2/1/0 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAshen Woods: Rot-Beasts Combat\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eModerate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e1 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAshen Woods: Rootgnaw Brood Combat\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHard\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e2 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e---- OR (Bone Fields route) ----\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eBone Fields Montage (2 rounds)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHard\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e2/1/0 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eBone Fields: Barrow Ambush\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHard\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e2 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#98cc98;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eBeat Total (Mandatory)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eup to 5 VP (one route)\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#2a6a2a;\"\u003eBeat 6 Гўв‚¬вЂќ Victory Point Summary\u003c/h4\u003e\u003cp style=\"font-style:italic; color:#555; margin-top:6px;\"\u003eBranch - only one route is played. Both routes yield approximately 4-5 VP.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:8px 0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#c0e0c0;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eEvent\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eDifficulty\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eVP Award\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAshen Woods Montage (2 rounds)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHard\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e2/1/0 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAshen Woods: Rot-Beasts Combat\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eModerate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e1 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAshen Woods: Rootgnaw Brood Combat\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHard\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e2 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e---- OR (Bone Fields route) ----\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eBone Fields Montage (2 rounds)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHard\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e2/1/0 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eBone Fields: Barrow Ambush\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHard\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e2 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#98cc98;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eBeat Total (Mandatory)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eup to 5 VP (one route)\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eTransition to Beat 7\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe charcoal forest gives way to impossible green. Living treesГўв‚¬вЂќreal trees, with leaves and bark and birdsГўв‚¬вЂќrise from the ash like a miracle. A wall of thorns and vines marks the boundary of the Green Heart.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen is inside. She knows theyГўв‚¬в„ўre coming. SheГўв‚¬в„ўs been watching through the trees.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eProceed to \u003cstrong\u003eBeat 7: The Reluctant Hearth\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","markdown":null},"src":null,"system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"sort":60,"flags":{},"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"exportSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"draw-steel","systemVersion":"0.10.0","createdTime":0,"modifiedTime":0,"lastModifiedBy":null}},{"_id":"RTFPAGE000000024","name":"Beat 7 Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Reluctant Hearth","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 2\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eDuration:\u003c/strong\u003e 1Гўв‚¬вЂњ2 sessions\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eLocation:\u003c/strong\u003e The Green Heart Гўв‚¬вЂќ the surviving grove at the center of the Ashen Woods\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eKey NPCs:\u003c/strong\u003e Kaelen (The Seventh), Lew Tosferd, Dryad guardians\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Very Hard Negotiation encounter, potential combat, emotional climax\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eTone:\u003c/strong\u003e Beauty and grief, guilt and duty, the last green place in a grey world\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1a3a; color:#c8c8e8; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4a4ac8;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVP Status Гўв‚¬вЂќ Entering This Beat\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cstrong\u003eTotal VP (max):\u003c/strong\u003e 16 | \u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 | \u003cstrong\u003eVP into Level:\u003c/strong\u003e 0\u003cbr\u003e\u003cem style=\"font-size:0.9em;\"\u003eLevel 2 begins - heroes levelled up after finishing Beat 6.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1a3a; color:#c8c8e8; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4a4ac8;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVP Status Гўв‚¬вЂќ Entering This Beat\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cstrong\u003eTotal VP (max):\u003c/strong\u003e 16 | \u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 | \u003cstrong\u003eVP into Level:\u003c/strong\u003e 0\u003cbr\u003e\u003cem style=\"font-size:0.9em;\"\u003eLevel 2 begins - heroes levelled up after finishing Beat 6.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2\u003eOverview\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs enter the Green HeartГўв‚¬вЂќthe impossible: a living forest at the center of the dead Ashen Woods. Here, Kaelen has hidden for years, tending the grove and its furious dryad guardians. She doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt want to be found. She doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt want to go back. She believes she \u003cstrong\u003ecaused\u003c/strong\u003e the crisis, and sheГўв‚¬в„ўs terrified of making it worse.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis beat is the emotional center of Act 1. The PCs must convince Kaelen to return to Hrafnborg, and the outcome of the negotiation determines how she joinsГўв‚¬вЂќas a willing ally or a reluctant one forced by circumstance.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 1: Entering the Green Heart\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Boundary\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe change happens over the course of a mileГўв‚¬вЂќand then all at once. The charcoal pillars thin. Ash gives way to soilГўв‚¬вЂќreal soil, dark and damp. A single green fern uncurls from the ground, then another, then dozens, then \u003cstrong\u003ehundreds\u003c/strong\u003e, and suddenly the world is \u003cstrong\u003ealive\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eTrees. Real trees. Birch and ash and oak, winter-bare but \u003cstrong\u003ebreathing\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќbark intact, roots gripping living earth, branches reaching for a sky that seems somehow less grey here. Snow dusts the ground, but beneath it: moss, roots, the smell of wet earth and growing things.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA wall of thornsГўв‚¬вЂќfive feet thick, eight feet tallГўв‚¬вЂќblocks the path forward. Living bramble, dense as castle walls. Within the thorns, you can hear birdsong. You can feel warmth. Not fire-warmth. \u003cstrong\u003eGrowing\u003c/strong\u003e-warmth.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSomething moves in the canopy above you. A faceГўв‚¬вЂќbark-skinned, hollow-eyed, beautiful and terribleГўв‚¬вЂќwatches you from the leaves and says nothing.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Dryad Welcome\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe dryads of the Green Heart are \u003cstrong\u003eprotectors\u003c/strong\u003e, not friends. There are three of them (Level 4 Controller Standards if combat occurs), and they have been defending this place since the War of Fire with murderous dedication.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTheir default response to intruders:\u003c/strong\u003e Kill them. Quietly. Efficiently. Feed the bodies to the roots.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhy the PCs arenГўв‚¬в„ўt dead:\u003c/strong\u003e Two reasons.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLewГўв‚¬в„ўs eye.\u003c/strong\u003e The amber gem resonates with the root network. The dryads sense itГўв‚¬вЂќit feels like Yggdrasil to them, and they hesitate.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eKaelen.\u003c/strong\u003e SheГўв‚¬в„ўs been watching (through the trees, through the roots, through the dryads\u0027 eyes) since the PCs crossed the Rootgnaw battleground. She told the dryads to let them through.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe thorn-wall shifts. Not opensГўв‚¬вЂќ\u003cstrong\u003eshifts\u003c/strong\u003e. The brambles pull apart like fingers unclenching, leaving a gap just wide enough for one person at a time.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA voice drifts from deeper in the grove: \"Come in. Leave weapons sheathed. The trees are watching.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs hesitate, the dryad in the canopy hisses: \u003cem\u003e\"The Keeper said come. So come. Before we change our minds.\"\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 2: The Green Heart\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe grove is warm. Not Hrafnborg-warmГўв‚¬вЂќnot the press of bodies and braziers and desperationГўв‚¬вЂќbut \u003cstrong\u003eearth\u003c/strong\u003e-warm. The warmth rises from below, from the roots that pulse with amber light. The air smells of resin and rain.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA clearing opens at the center: perhaps a hundred feet across, ringed by ancient oaks. Their canopies interlock overhead, forming a living ceiling. Moss carpets the ground. A streamГўв‚¬вЂќclear, unfrozen, \u003cstrong\u003eimpossible\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќruns through the clearingГўв‚¬в„ўs center.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eNear the stream, a young woman sits cross-legged on a stone. SheГўв‚¬в„ўs wearing practical traveling clothesГўв‚¬вЂќpatched, repaired, forest-stained. Her hair is dark, cropped short. On her forehead, a scar glows faintly amber in the groveГўв‚¬в„ўs light: the ember-mark.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eShe doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt look up as you enter. SheГўв‚¬в„ўs carving something into a piece of bark with a small knife. Her hands are steady. Her jaw is tight.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"I know why youГўв‚¬в„ўre here,\" she says. \"The answer is no.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis is \u003cstrong\u003eKaelenГўв‚¬вЂќthe Seventh\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: Playing Kaelen\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen is \u003cstrong\u003enot\u003c/strong\u003e a damsel to be rescued. She is not waiting to be convinced. She has made a deliberate, reasoned, guilt-driven choice to stay here, and she will defend that choice with intelligence and conviction.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKey behaviors:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eShe speaks directlyГўв‚¬вЂќno evasion, no deflection. She will tell the PCs exactly why she wonГўв‚¬в„ўt go.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eShe is not hostile. She is \u003cstrong\u003etired\u003c/strong\u003e. She has been carrying this guilt alone for years.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eShe genuinely cares about SvellheimГўв‚¬в„ўs people. ThatГўв‚¬в„ўs what makes this hard.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eShe is terrifiedГўв‚¬вЂќnot of the mission, but of \u003cstrong\u003eherself\u003c/strong\u003e. She believes she broke something fundamental, and she fears sheГўв‚¬в„ўll break it worse.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eShe is protective of the Green Heart and its dryads. They are her family now.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 3: KaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs Story\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBefore the formal negotiation begins, Kaelen explains herself. This is both exposition and a chance for the PCs to understand what theyГўв‚¬в„ўre asking of her.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat Kaelen tells them willingly:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eShe was chosen as Ember-Keeper at thirteen. Youngest ever. She served faithfully for three years.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDuring a duty journey in her third year, she came upon a northern village in crisisГўв‚¬вЂќthe entire population sick, fires unattended, children and families huddled freezing in the temple. She used the townГўв‚¬в„ўs Ever-Ember to start hearth fires, heat water, and cook food.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eShe broke the prohibition she knew by heart: \u003cem\u003eГўв‚¬Е“The Ever-Ember gives warmth, but does not share its fire.Гўв‚¬Вќ\u003c/em\u003e An Ember may warm those who sit by it, but flame may not be taken from it to light other fires. The EmberГўв‚¬в„ўs power is its singularityГўв‚¬вЂќan unbroken anchor between the living and the dead.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThere was a small, real consequenceГўв‚¬вЂќa slight dimming of the anchor for a season, a few more restless dead in that region that winter. Nothing provable. Nothing anyone could trace to her. But Kaelen noticed. She counted it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhen Fimbulwinter came and the dead rose everywhere, she added her small real effect to the account and inflated it into the cause. She believes her single act of mercy cracked the wall between the living and the dead. The guilt has been her only companion for twelve years.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eShe came here because the Green Heart is the only place left that feels \u003cstrong\u003ewhole\u003c/strong\u003e. The dryads donГўв‚¬в„ўt ask what she did. They care about the grove. She tends the roots. They protect the boundary. It works.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003e GM Notes: Playing the Guilt Scene\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis confession should feel \u003cem\u003ehonest\u003c/em\u003e, not theatrical. Kaelen is not performing her guilt. She has lived with it, examined it from every angle, and concluded it is real and deserved. She does not flinch from it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe critical thing the PCs must understand: \u003cem\u003eshe is not wrong that she did something that had a real effect.\u003c/em\u003e She lit fires from the Ember. The anchor dimmed. People did rise that winter. Her guilt is founded on something true. What she got wrong is the \u003cem\u003escale\u003c/em\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќshe assigned civilization-ending weight to a small real harm, because that is what guilt does when it has no one to correct it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDo not let PCs dismiss her guilt. The pitfall rules below exist precisely to prevent this. Her guilt is the load-bearing wall of her identity right now.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat Kaelen does NOT tell them (GM secretГўв‚¬вЂќLayer 2, Act 3 reveal):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Ever-Ember spoke to Kaelen directly, before she fledГўв‚¬вЂќsomething it had never done with any Keeper before and left no record of. It showed her prophetic visions: Fimbulwinter, the War of Fire, the dead rising everywhere. All true. All fulfilled.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThen it showed her something she has never admitted to anyone: the other six Keepers, years later, placing a carved stone in her empty seat to replace her role in the witnessing rite. She saw this and read it as her abandonment and erasureГўв‚¬вЂќthe other Keepers erasing her from the record while the world ended without her. She left to spare herself from being forgotten. She didnГўв‚¬в„ўt understand she was seeing \u003cem\u003etheir\u003c/em\u003e manipulation by GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs agent.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhat the Ember was actually showing her: the void her departure would leave, which GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs agent would exploit to void the binding. Yggdrasil showed her this vision deliberatelyГўв‚¬вЂќnot to warn her, but to \u003cem\u003emove her\u003c/em\u003e. The tree needed her gone before the corruption of the other Keepers made her complicit. Her departure was guided, not accidental.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe thing that broke her was not the vision of apocalypse. It was the vision of being replaced by a rock. That is the secret she carries that no one knows. (This is revealed in Act 3, when the party learns what the other Keepers actually did and why.)\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 4: The Negotiation\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Negotiation | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Very Hard (I5/P3) | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on success\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Negotiation | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Very Hard (I5/P3) | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on success\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis is a \u003cstrong\u003eVery Hard Negotiation Encounter\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ Why Гўв‚¬Е“Very HardГўв‚¬Вќ at I2/P2\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe rules-reference defines Very Hard as I1Гўв‚¬вЂќ2 / P2. KaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs starting Interest of 2 (rather than 1) might suggest Hard difficulty, but the label is warranted because: (1) pitfalls cost both Interest \u003cem\u003eand\u003c/em\u003e Patience (Гўв‚¬вЂќ1/Гўв‚¬вЂќ1), making a single misstep almost certainly fatal to the negotiation; (2) non-motivation arguments penalise Interest on T1; (3) the effective target is Interest 4 (not the standard 5), but Patience 2 means only two arguments totalГўв‚¬вЂќno room for recovery; (4) each motivation can only be invoked once.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003e Why Гўв‚¬Е“Very HardГўв‚¬Вќ at I2/P2\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe rules-reference defines Very Hard as I1Гўв‚¬вЂќ2 / P2. KaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs starting Interest of 2 (rather than 1) might suggest Hard difficulty, but the label is warranted because: (1) pitfalls cost both Interest \u003cem\u003eand\u003c/em\u003e Patience (Гўв‚¬вЂќ1/Гўв‚¬вЂќ1), making a single misstep almost certainly fatal to the negotiation; (2) non-motivation arguments penalise Interest on T1; (3) the effective target is Interest 4 (not the standard 5), but Patience 2 means only two arguments totalГўв‚¬вЂќno room for recovery; (4) each motivation can only be invoked once.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eSetup\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eInterest:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 (Suspicious) Гўв‚¬вЂќ Kaelen cares about Svellheim. She doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt want people to die. But sheГўв‚¬в„ўs made a deliberate, reasoned choice to stay, and she will defend it.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003ePatience:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 Гўв‚¬вЂќ SheГўв‚¬в„ўs already decided. The PCs have very little room to maneuver. Wasted arguments end this conversation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: Draw Steel Negotiation Mechanics\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eUnder Draw Steel rules, each argument is a power roll using Reason, Intuition, or Presence (with any applicable interpersonal skill). Motivations require a \u003cem\u003emedium\u003c/em\u003e difficulty roll; arguments with no motivation or pitfall require a \u003cem\u003edifficult\u003c/em\u003e roll.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMotivation appeal (medium difficulty):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTier 1 (11 or lower):\u003c/strong\u003e Patience -1. No Interest change.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTier 2 (12Гўв‚¬вЂќ16):\u003c/strong\u003e Interest +1, Patience -1.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTier 3 (17+):\u003c/strong\u003e Interest +1, Patience unchanged.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eNo motivation or pitfall (difficult):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTier 1:\u003c/strong\u003e Patience -1, Interest -1.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTier 2:\u003c/strong\u003e Patience -1 only.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTier 3:\u003c/strong\u003e Interest +1, Patience -1. (Natural 19Гўв‚¬вЂќ20: Patience unchanged.)\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePitfall invoked:\u003c/strong\u003e Automatic failure. Interest -1, Patience -1.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWith Patience 2 and Interest 2, the party needs to reach Interest 4 for Kaelen to agree (Гўв‚¬Е“YesГўв‚¬вЂќIГўв‚¬в„ўll come, on my termsГўв‚¬Вќ). Two successful Tier 3 motivation appeals can do it cleanly. One Tier 2 hit and one Tier 3 hit spends all Patience. One pitfall invoked almost certainly ends the negotiation in failure. Stakes are real.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEach motivation can only be successfully invoked \u003cem\u003eonce\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMotivations (medium difficulty roll Гўв‚¬вЂќ arguments that can raise Interest):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRedemption as action, not absolution:\u003c/strong\u003e Do NOT frame this as Гўв‚¬Е“fix what you brokeГўв‚¬Вќ (see pitfall below). Frame it as: Гўв‚¬Е“You lit fires for people who would have frozen. You knew the rule and you chose mercy. That choice deserves a successor act Гўв‚¬вЂќ not punishment, not forgiveness. Action.Гўв‚¬Вќ Kaelen wants her transgression to have \u003cem\u003emeant something\u003c/em\u003e. She lit those fires. If she can act now in a way that flows from that decision, the twelve years of guilt become a preparation rather than a sentence.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDuty (the mark still glows):\u003c/strong\u003e The Ever-Ember chose her at thirteen. It has not chosen another in twelve years. The ember-mark on her forehead still burns Гўв‚¬вЂќ she is still a Keeper whether she accepts the title or not. The office doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt expire when the Keeper flees. Kaelen bristles at this but cannot dismiss it: the evidence is written into her own face.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eProtecting the common folk (make it specific):\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬Е“The people of Hrafnborg are going to die. Not soldiers. Not kings. Families. Children.Гўв‚¬Вќ The same instinct that made her light fires for a sick village is the instinct the party must reach. Make the human cost real and specific Гўв‚¬вЂќ name people theyГўв‚¬в„ўve met, describe what theyГўв‚¬в„ўve seen on the road. Abstract stakes donГўв‚¬в„ўt move her. Named people do.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePitfalls (automatic failure Гўв‚¬вЂќ Interest -1, Patience -1):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGlory:\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬Е“YouГўв‚¬в„ўll be a hero.Гўв‚¬Вќ Kaelen does not want to be a hero. She wants to have done something worthy, which is entirely different. Framing her return as fame or legend reduces a moral question to a performance opportunity. She closes off immediately.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOrders from authority:\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬Е“The King commands it.Гўв‚¬Вќ Kaelen left a structure of institutional authority that gave her rules and no one to ask when she needed guidance. Any argument that boils down to Гўв‚¬Е“because someone above you says soГўв‚¬Вќ triggers defiance rather than complianceГўв‚¬вЂќeven though she respects Harald personally.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMinimizing her guilt (the worst pitfall):\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬Е“It wasnГўв‚¬в„ўt your faultГўв‚¬Вќ or Гўв‚¬Е“YouГўв‚¬в„ўre being too hard on yourself.Гўв‚¬Вќ Her guilt is real, founded on something true, and she has examined it for twelve years. Anyone who dismisses it is dismissing the evidence of her own experience. This is the most dangerous pitfallГўв‚¬вЂќit reads as condescension and tells her the PCs donГўв‚¬в„ўt understand what theyГўв‚¬в„ўre asking. Avoid it entirely.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003ewasnГўв‚¬в„ўt your faultГўв‚¬Вќ or Гўв‚¬Е“YouГўв‚¬в„ўre being too hard on yourself.Гўв‚¬Вќ Her guilt is real, founded on something true, and she has examined it for twelve years. Anyone who dismisses it is dismissing the evidence of her own experience. This is the most dangerous pitfallГўв‚¬вЂќit reads as condescension and tells her the PCs donГўв‚¬в„ўt understand what theyГўв‚¬в„ўre asking. Avoid it entirely.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eNegotiation Flow\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs can discuss strategy between arguments (the Гўв‚¬Е“out of character planningГўв‚¬Вќ approach is explicitly supported by Draw Steel). Let them feel the weight of Patience 2Гўв‚¬вЂќthey have very few swings.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePresence:\u003c/strong\u003e Emotional appeals, empathy, personal connection. Best for Redemption and Common Folk arguments.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eReason:\u003c/strong\u003e Logical arguments, strategic framing, evidence. Works well for Duty and specific-stakes arguments.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eIntuition:\u003c/strong\u003e Reading KaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs responses mid-negotiation. Can be used to pivot when a line of argument isnГўв‚¬в„ўt landing.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLewГўв‚¬в„ўs contribution:\u003c/strong\u003e If the PCs allow it, Lew can make one argument using Presence +3. He uses it like this: Гўв‚¬Е“I donГўв‚¬в„ўt know what you did. I donГўв‚¬в„ўt care. I know what itГўв‚¬в„ўs like to lose something you canГўв‚¬в„ўt get back and spend years deciding if you deserved to. The question isnГўв‚¬в„ўt whether you deserve a second chance. The question is whether Hrafnborg deserves to die because youГўв‚¬в„ўre afraid of one.Гўв‚¬Вќ\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLewГўв‚¬в„ўs argument always hits Tier 2 minimum (Presence +3 on a medium roll). It raises Interest by 1Гўв‚¬вЂќbut it also costs 1 Patience. Kaelen resents being \u003cstrong\u003emanaged\u003c/strong\u003e, even expertly. A wise party uses Lew only if theyГўв‚¬в„ўre in trouble and have Patience to spare.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eReading KaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs Responses\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eUse these to guide roleplay between arguments:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eInterest goes up:\u003c/strong\u003e Kaelen goes quiet. Her jaw unclenches. She looks at the ground rather than at the PCsГўв‚¬вЂќthis is her processing, not disengagement. Гўв‚¬Е“I hear youГўв‚¬Вќ is the highest praise sheГўв‚¬в„ўll offer in the moment.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eInterest stays flat (no-motivation argument):\u003c/strong\u003e She sighs. Гўв‚¬Е“YouГўв‚¬в„ўre repeating yourself.Гўв‚¬Вќ Or: Гўв‚¬Е“ThatГўв‚¬в„ўs not an argument. ThatГўв‚¬в„ўs a hope.Гўв‚¬Вќ\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eInterest drops (pitfall):\u003c/strong\u003e Her eyes go flat. Her voice drops to something controlled and cold. Гўв‚¬Е“Say that again and IГўв‚¬в„ўll ask the dryads to show you out.Гўв‚¬Вќ\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePatience at 1:\u003c/strong\u003e She checks the sun. Looks at the thorn-wall. Her body has already started making the calculation between Гўв‚¬Е“this conversationГўв‚¬Вќ and Гўв‚¬Е“the grove that needs me.Гўв‚¬Вќ The PCs should feel the pressure.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003eBonus from Beat 6a/6b\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs protected 2+ living roots during the Rootgnaw Brood combat (Beat 6), the Green HeartГўв‚¬в„ўs root-blessing grants +2 to Presence tests during this negotiation. The groveГўв‚¬в„ўs approval is visibleГўв‚¬вЂќsmall flowers bloom near the PCs\u0027 feet, and the dryads relax their stance.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 5: Outcomes\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eNegotiation Success (Interest reaches 5)\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen agrees to comeГўв‚¬вЂќbut on her terms.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen is quiet for a long time. The amber light of the grove pulses around her. The ember-mark on her forehead brightensГўв‚¬вЂќnot with warmth, but with something like \u003cstrong\u003erecognition\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Fine,\" she says. Not surrendering. Deciding. \"IГўв‚¬в„ўll come. IГўв‚¬в„ўll speak to the Ever-Ember, if itГўв‚¬в„ўll still speak to me. But IГўв‚¬в„ўm not going back to be a Keeper. IГўв‚¬в„ўm going back to \u003cstrong\u003efix\u003c/strong\u003e what I broke. And when itГўв‚¬в„ўs fixedГўв‚¬вЂќif it can be fixedГўв‚¬вЂќIГўв‚¬в„ўm coming back here.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eShe stands. Looks at you. For the first time, the grief in her eyes has company: something harder, sharper.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eResolve.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"DonГўв‚¬в„ўt make me regret this.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eConditions of success:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen joins the party as an NPC ally for the journey back.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eShe insists on saying goodbye to the dryads (1 hour).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eShe brings nothing from the groveГўв‚¬вЂќ\"IГўв‚¬в„ўm not \u003cstrong\u003etaking\u003c/strong\u003e from this place. IГўв‚¬в„ўve taken enough.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eShe cooperates fully but remains guarded. Earning her real trust will take Acts 2 and 3.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eNegotiation Failure (Patience reduced to 0)\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen refuses. SheГўв‚¬в„ўs made her choice.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"I said no.\" KaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs voice is flat. \"IГўв‚¬в„ўve heard your arguments. All of them. And I understand. But I canГўв‚¬в„ўtГўв‚¬вЂќ\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eShe stops. Looks past you, toward the thorn-wall.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe dryads are screaming.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe negotiation is interrupted by an attack. Whether the PCs failed or simply ran out of time, \u003cstrong\u003esomething\u003c/strong\u003e breaches the Green HeartГўв‚¬в„ўs boundary: Pale Maw agents (directed by GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs network acting on DreyfusГўв‚¬в„ўs intelligence from Hrafnborg), Rootgnaw creatures drawn by the disturbance, or a Rot-warped landvaettrГўв‚¬вЂќa corrupted nature spirit that the dryads canГўв‚¬в„ўt stop alone.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eThe Attack That Convinces Her\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEnemies (Option A вЂ” Pale Maw Assault, EV 118):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e3 Pale Maw Acolytes\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 2 Ambusher Elite)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e2 Pale Maw Zealots\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 3 Harrier Elite)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e3 Rot-Warped Landvaettrs\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 3 Controller Platoon вЂ” corrupted tree-spirits, once dryad allies)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEnemies (Option B вЂ” Rootgnaw Brood, EV 114):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e12 Rootgnaw Grubs\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 1 Harrier Minion)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e3 Rootgnaw Queens\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 3 Controller Platoon)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e3 Vine Stranglers\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 2 Ambusher Elite вЂ” corrupted plants from the Ashen Woods fringe)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs must fight to protect the grove. Kaelen fights alongside themГўв‚¬вЂќnot as an ally (yet) but as a \u003cstrong\u003edefender of her home\u003c/strong\u003e. Use her NPC stat block from the MODULE.adoc.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Aftermath of the Attack\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Combat (Conditional - only if negotiation fails and Kaelen is threatened) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate to Hard | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on victory\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Combat (Conditional - only if negotiation fails and Kaelen is threatened) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate to Hard | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on victory\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhen itГўв‚¬в„ўs over, Kaelen stands in the ruined clearing, breathing hard. A dryad lies broken among the rootsГўв‚¬вЂќnot dead, but hurt. Sap runs from its bark like blood.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen kneels beside the dryad and presses her hand to the wound. The ember-mark flares. The dryadГўв‚¬в„ўs bark seals.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eShe looks up at you, and her expression has changed. The fear is still there. But so is \u003cstrong\u003eanger\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"They found this place,\" she says. \"They found the only living thing left in these woods, and they \u003cstrong\u003eattacked\u003c/strong\u003e it.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eShe stands.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Alright. IГўв‚¬в„ўll come. Not for Hrafnborg. Not for the King. For \u003cstrong\u003ethis\u003c/strong\u003e.\" She gestures at the wounded grove. \"Because if I stay, theyГўв‚¬в„ўll keep coming. And the Green Heart canГўв‚¬в„ўt survive that.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eConditions of failure-to-success:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen joins, but her motivation is \u003cstrong\u003eanger\u003c/strong\u003e, not duty. She is less cooperative and more volatile.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eShe does not trust the party as quicklyГўв‚¬вЂќthey failed to convince her with words, and that stings.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe attack itself is evidence that GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs network knows about the Green Heart. Dreyfus overheard the partyГўв‚¬в„ўs plans in Hrafnborg and relayed the information via Wyrd-channels. This accelerates the Grafvitnir timeline.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMechanically: Kaelen starts with 1 fewer recovery (emotional/physical cost of the fight) and her Interest in future negotiations with the party starts at 1 instead of 2.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 6: The Farewell\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhether Kaelen agreed through words or was forced by violence, her departure from the Green Heart is a moment.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen walks the perimeter of the grove one last time. She touches each tree. She speaks to each dryad in a language you donГўв‚¬в„ўt understandГўв‚¬вЂќolder than NorrГ…вЂњnt, older than anything youГўв‚¬в„ўve heard. The words sound like roots growing.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe dryads donГўв‚¬в„ўt cry. But the leaves around them darken, and the birdsong fades to silence.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAt the thorn-wall, Kaelen stops. She presses her palm to the brambles. They part for herГўв‚¬вЂќslowly, reluctantlyГўв‚¬вЂќand on the other side is the grey.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"DonГўв‚¬в„ўt look back,\" the lead dryad says. Not to Kaelen. To you. \"If she looks back, she wonГўв‚¬в„ўt leave.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt look back.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou step through. The thorns close behind you. And the warmth of the Green Heart cuts off like a door slamming shut.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 7: Grafvitnir Pressure Check\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eRoll the Grafvitnir Pressure Check (d6) as the party leaves the Green Heart:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eRoll\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eEffect\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e1-2\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eNo network activity. The Green HeartГўв‚¬в„ўs Wyrd-presence scrambled the informant chains. The party has a clean exit.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e3-4\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eSilver-eyed Valravn circle the canopy as the party exits the Green Heart. They perch in the dead trees just beyond the thorn-wall, watching. Within hours, GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs agents will know the partyГўв‚¬в„ўs heading: west, toward Hrafnborg.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e5\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe party finds a dead Pale Maw agent at the groveГўв‚¬в„ўs boundary (killed by dryads). Carved into the dead manГўв‚¬в„ўs arm: a map showing the route from Stairwatch to the Green Heart. Someone has been feeding GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs agents real-time intelligence. The leak is active Гўв‚¬вЂќ and itГўв‚¬в„ўs coming from inside Hrafnborg itself.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e6\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eA sound echoes through the Ashen Woods as the party leaves Гўв‚¬вЂќ not wind, not animal. A resonant pulse carried through the dead root network beneath their feet. All PCs make an medium Intuition test: success = they feel words in the vibration, transmitted through YggdrasilГўв‚¬в„ўs dying roots: \"She comes. The seal weakens. The Wolf is patient.\" Failure = they feel only a deep unease, as though the ground itself is listening.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eOutcomes\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBy the end of this beat, the PCs should have:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEntered the Green Heart and experienced genuine beauty in a dead world.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMet Kaelen and understood the weight of her guilt and her choice.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSuccessfully negotiated her return (or been forced to fight alongside her when the Heart was attacked).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eUnderstood that KaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs guilt is connected to the Ever-Ember crisis (though the full truth is still hidden).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGained a powerful NPC allyГўв‚¬вЂќreluctant, complicated, and carrying secrets.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFelt the groveГўв‚¬в„ўs farewell as a genuine loss.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#2a6a2a;\"\u003eBeat 7 Гўв‚¬вЂќ Victory Point Summary\u003c/h4\u003e\u003cp style=\"font-style:italic; color:#555; margin-top:6px;\"\u003eConditional combat triggers only if negotiation fails and Kaelen is threatened.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:8px 0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#c0e0c0;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eEvent\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eDifficulty\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eVP Award\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 4: Negotiation with Kaelen\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eVery Hard (I5/P3)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e1 VP on success\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003ePart 5: Pale Maw Attack (conditional)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003eModerate to Hard\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003e1 VP on victory\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#98cc98;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eBeat Total (Mandatory)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003e1 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#2a6a2a;\"\u003eBeat 7 Гўв‚¬вЂќ Victory Point Summary\u003c/h4\u003e\u003cp style=\"font-style:italic; color:#555; margin-top:6px;\"\u003eConditional combat triggers only if negotiation fails and Kaelen is threatened.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:8px 0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#c0e0c0;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eEvent\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eDifficulty\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eVP Award\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 4: Negotiation with Kaelen\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eVery Hard (I5/P3)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e1 VP on success\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003ePart 5: Pale Maw Attack (conditional)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003eModerate to Hard\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003e1 VP on victory\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#98cc98;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eBeat Total (Mandatory)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003e1 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eTransition to Beat 8\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe partyГўв‚¬вЂќnow four strong (3 PCs, Lew, and Kaelen)Гўв‚¬вЂќbegins the long return to Hrafnborg. The road home is not the same road they came by: the Ashen Woods have shifted, the weather has worsened, and GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs network is closing in.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eProceed to \u003cstrong\u003eBeat 8: The Long Road Home\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","markdown":null},"src":null,"system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"sort":70,"flags":{},"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"exportSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"draw-steel","systemVersion":"0.10.0","createdTime":0,"modifiedTime":0,"lastModifiedBy":null}},{"_id":"RTFPAGE000000025","name":"Beat 8 Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Long Road Home","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 ГўвЂ вЂ™ 3 (level-up occurs at end of this beat)\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eDuration:\u003c/strong\u003e 2Гўв‚¬вЂњ3 sessions\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eLocation:\u003c/strong\u003e Green Heart ГўвЂ вЂ™ Ashen Woods (or Bone Fields) ГўвЂ вЂ™ Interior Belt ГўвЂ вЂ™ MidgardГўв‚¬в„ўs Shield ГўвЂ вЂ™ Hrafnborg approach\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eKey NPCs:\u003c/strong\u003e Kaelen, Lew, Gragnir (major appearance Гўв‚¬вЂќ reveals Dreyfus)\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate Montage Test, combat encounter, negotiation, character development, GragnirГўв‚¬в„ўs reveal\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eTone:\u003c/strong\u003e Companionship forged in hardship, growing trust, a world visibly dying, and then Гўв‚¬вЂќ the truth\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1a3a; color:#c8c8e8; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4a4ac8;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVP Status Гўв‚¬вЂќ Entering This Beat\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cstrong\u003eTotal VP (max):\u003c/strong\u003e 18 | \u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 | \u003cstrong\u003eVP into Level:\u003c/strong\u003e 2\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1a3a; color:#c8c8e8; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4a4ac8;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVP Status Гўв‚¬вЂќ Entering This Beat\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cstrong\u003eTotal VP (max):\u003c/strong\u003e 18 | \u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 | \u003cstrong\u003eVP into Level:\u003c/strong\u003e 2\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2\u003eOverview\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe return journey. The PCs travel west from the Green Heart through deteriorating terrain toward Hrafnborg, now with Kaelen and Lew in tow.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDistance:\u003c/strong\u003e ~220 miles\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eDuration:\u003c/strong\u003e ~12 days Гўв‚¬вЂќ blended terrain rates (24 miles/day on roads, 18 mildly hindered, 12 severely hindered in mountain passes)\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eCalendar:\u003c/strong\u003e Departure approximately Heyannir 3rd; arrival approximately Heyannir 14thГўв‚¬вЂњ15th. Early winter is setting in Гўв‚¬вЂќ the first true cold of Vetr bleeds into the tail of Sumar. The days shorten noticeably during this leg.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe road is familiar but changed. The weather has worsened. The undead are more active and \u003cstrong\u003eorganized\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќmoving in columns toward Hrafnborg. GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs network is closing.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis beat serves three purposes:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCharacter development:\u003c/strong\u003e Time with Kaelen and Lew as real people, not quest objectives.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGrowing threat:\u003c/strong\u003e The world is visibly deteriorating. The Ever-Embers are failing faster.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGragnirГўв‚¬в„ўs reveal:\u003c/strong\u003e The druid appears and exposes the kingГўв‚¬в„ўs hound Гўв‚¬вЂќ Dreyfus is a shape-walker spy serving Grafvitnir, the Grave-Wolf Гўв‚¬вЂќ and the horror is that heГўв‚¬в„ўs still in Hrafnborg, over two hundred miles away, at HaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs side.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 1: Leaving the Green Heart\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe thorn-wall closes behind you. One moment, green Гўв‚¬вЂќ light, birdsong, the smell of living earth. The next: ash. Silence. Grey.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen walks at the rear of the group. She hasnГўв‚¬в„ўt spoken since the wall sealed. Lew, for once, doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt fill the silence. His eye is dimГўв‚¬вЂќthe amber barely a glow. \"She doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt want to be tracked,\" he murmurs to you. \"The Heart is hiding itself. Even from me.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe dead trees stand like gravestones. And you walk.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eTwelve days. Over two hundred miles. The longest road yet.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: Return Route\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe party retraces the general path of their outbound journey, but the landscape has \u003cstrong\u003echanged\u003c/strong\u003e in the days since they passed. The world is deteriorating faster now Гўв‚¬вЂќ Heyannir marks the transition from late summer into early winter under Fimbulwinter conditions. What was merely cold on the outbound trek is now bitter. What was passable is now dangerous.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the party took the \u003cstrong\u003eAshen Woods\u003c/strong\u003e outbound, they exit the Green Heart into familiar (but worsening) charcoal forest, then cross the Dead Farms and the mountains.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the party took the \u003cstrong\u003eBone Fields\u003c/strong\u003e outbound, they may choose to return that way (shorter but exposed) or swing through the Ashen Woods (longer but with more shelter). Lew recommends the Ashen Woods for the return: \"I donГўв‚¬в„ўt want to cross the Fields twice. And the Woods have cover. If what Gragnir said about the dead moving southwest is true, cover matters.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eEither way, the montage structure below works. Adjust geographic descriptions to match the outbound route.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 2: The Route Гўв‚¬вЂќ 12 Days\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe return journey covers three phases:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePhase\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eTerrain\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDays\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePhase 1: The Wasteland Exit\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAshen Woods or Bone Fields Гўв‚¬вЂќ exiting the Green HeartГўв‚¬в„ўs vicinity\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDays 1Гўв‚¬вЂњ4\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePhase 2: The Interior Belt\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDead Farms, failing roads, refugee country\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDays 5Гўв‚¬вЂњ8\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePhase 3: The Mountain Crossing\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eMidgardГўв‚¬в„ўs Shield Гўв‚¬вЂќ the TitanГўв‚¬в„ўs Stair pass back to the coast\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDays 9Гўв‚¬вЂњ12\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe weather worsens progressively. Phase 1 is cold. Phase 2 is freezing. Phase 3 is the first true blizzard of early winter.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 3: Montage Test Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Return\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Montage Test | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 VP on full success, 1 VP partial, 0 VP failure (2 rounds)\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Montage Test | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 VP on full success, 1 VP partial, 0 VP failure (2 rounds)\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate (the route is known; the risks are different)\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eParty Size Adjustment (4 heroes + 2 NPC companions):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDifficulty\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eSuccess Limit\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eFailure Limit\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eModerate (adjusted)\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e5\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e3\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRounds:\u003c/strong\u003e 2. Insert combat, character development, and points of interest between rounds.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eNPC Contributions:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLew:\u003c/strong\u003e Assists one PCГўв‚¬в„ўs test per round (Intuition +4 or Reason +2). His navigation is less useful on the return (the eye is dim), but his survival skills and paranoia compensate.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eKaelen:\u003c/strong\u003e Can assist one PCГўв‚¬в„ўs test per round (Might +3 or Intuition +2). She is strong, practical, and observant. She also drives the paceГўв‚¬вЂќshe doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt want to linger in the wasteland.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eRound 1: The Wasteland Exit (Days 1Гўв‚¬вЂњ4)\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eChallenge\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCharacteristic\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDescription\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eNavigate back through the Ashen Woods\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eReason\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe charcoal forest has shiftedГўв‚¬вЂќtrunks have fallen, ash drifts have changed, and the root network beneath is active (moving soil, closing paths). Retrace the route with adjustments.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePace through worsening weather\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eMight\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe temperature has dropped since the outbound trek. Frost now rimes the charcoal trunks each morning. Wind has picked upГўв‚¬вЂќcarrying ash and ice crystals both.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAvoid blighted beasts\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAgility / Intuition\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe Rot-Beasts and Vine Stranglers are more active now, driven by the cold toward the Green HeartГўв‚¬в„ўs warmth. The PCs cross their territory going the wrong direction. Give them a wide berth.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eFind usable shelter\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eReason\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe shelters from the outbound trekГўв‚¬вЂќthe Charcoal Cathedral, the root-cavesГўв‚¬вЂќmay be occupied. Finding somewhere safe to camp requires scouting and improvisation.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eRead the weather signs\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eIntuition\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eStorm systems move differently in Fimbulwinter. Reading cloud patterns, wind shifts, and animal behaviour (what little survives) can help predict whether to push on or hunker down.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eKeep Kaelen moving\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePresence\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eKaelen is mourning. Leaving the Green Heart cost her. She moves slowly, stops often, stares southeast. The PCs need to keep her engaged without being cruel about it.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eRound 1 Interlude: The World is Worse Гўв‚¬вЂќ Part I\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBetween Rounds 1 and 2, seed these observations. The world has deteriorated measurably in the ~10 days since the party passed through:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe clearing where you camped on the outbound journey is different. The charcoal trunks you used as windbreaks have fallen. The fire-pit you dug is full of grey ice.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAnd on the stone where you left a small offering of food for Solveig Гўв‚¬вЂќ nothing. The offering is untouched. No, not untouched Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cstrong\u003egone\u003c/strong\u003e. And in its place, a single charcoal stick, broken in half. A message, perhaps, or a sign. Lew studies it and shrugs.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Either sheГўв‚¬в„ўs moved on, or sheГўв‚¬в„ўs telling us to.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs took the Bone Fields outbound, replace with:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe barrows you sealed on the outbound journey are \u003cstrong\u003eopen\u003c/strong\u003e again. Every one of them. The capstones have been pushed aside from the \u003cstrong\u003einside\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe bones inside are gone.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 4: Point of Interest Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Dead Waystation\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePlace this between Round 1 and Round 2, as the party exits the Ashen Woods / wasteland and enters the Interior Belt.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou come to a crossroads you remember from the outbound journey Гўв‚¬вЂќ or think you do. The signpost is gone. The road is buried under a foot of frozen mud. But the waystation at the crossroads is still standing: a stone shelter with a turf roof, built to house travelers and stock feed for horses.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eInside: bodies.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eNot undead. Not risen. Just dead. Seven people Гўв‚¬вЂќ a family, by their clothing. Two adults, three children, two elders. They died huddled together around a fire that went out. Their supplies are scattered but mostly intact: grain, salted fish, a good wool blanket, a medicine box.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThey didnГўв‚¬в„ўt die of cold. They died of \u003cstrong\u003edespair\u003c/strong\u003e. The elderГўв‚¬в„ўs hand still holds a knife. There are marks on the floor Гўв‚¬вЂќ tally marks, scratched into stone. Fourteen days\u0027 worth.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThey waited for help that never came.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: The Dead Waystation\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis is pure narrative weight. No skill check, no loot grab, no moral choice (though the PCs may want to bury them Гўв‚¬вЂќ let them).\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe point: fourteen days ago, when the PCs were heading south toward the Green Heart, this family was alive and waiting. If the PCs had stopped, if theyГўв‚¬в„ўd come this way, if theyГўв‚¬в„ўd done somethingГўв‚¬В¦Гўв‚¬вЂ№ but they didnГўв‚¬в„ўt. They couldnГўв‚¬в„ўt have. They didnГўв‚¬в„ўt know.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis is the cost of Fimbulwinter. Not monsters. Not evil. Just cold and time and silence.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs bury the family (takes 2 hours, costs nothing, earns no mechanical benefit): Kaelen helps dig. She doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt speak, but she works harder than anyone. Lew finds a prayer-stone in the medicine box and places it on the cairn.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe party gains no Victories from this. But it matters.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 5: Character Development Scenes\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eDistribute these scenes across the journey Гўв‚¬вЂќ between montage rounds, during rest stops, on the march. They should feel organic, not staged.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eScene: Kaelen and the Ember-Mark\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAround the campfire (such as it is), Kaelen touches the scar on her forehead. It glows faintlyГўв‚¬вЂќmore than it did in the Green Heart, as if distance from the grove makes it brighter.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"It never went away,\" she says, to no one in particular. \"I thought it would. I hoped it would. But the Ever-Ember marks you \u003cstrong\u003eforever\u003c/strong\u003e. Even if you run.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eShe looks at the fireГўв‚¬вЂќyour small, mortal campfire.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Do you know what it feels like? When the Ember chooses you? ItГўв‚¬в„ўs not warm. ItГўв‚¬в„ўs \u003cstrong\u003eheavy\u003c/strong\u003e. Like someone put the weight of every person whoГўв‚¬в„ўll ever stand near that fire on your shoulders, and said: \u0027DonГўв‚¬в„ўt drop this.\u0027\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eShe pulls her hand away from the scar.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"I dropped it.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLet the PCs respond. Kaelen doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt want comfortГўв‚¬вЂќshe wants to be \u003cstrong\u003eheard\u003c/strong\u003e. If a PC shares their own failure or regret, Kaelen listens carefully and nods. She doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt open up further, but a connection forms.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eScene: Lew and Gragnir\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs ask Lew about Gragnir (or he volunteers during a quiet march):\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"GragnirГўв‚¬в„ўs not what you think he is,\" Lew says, adjusting his pack. \"HeГўв‚¬в„ўs not a wizard. HeГўв‚¬в„ўs not a hermit. HeГўв‚¬в„ўs aГўв‚¬вЂќ\" He searches for the word. \"HeГўв‚¬в„ўs a \u003cstrong\u003egardener\u003c/strong\u003e. The world is his garden. And right now, the garden is on fire and he canГўв‚¬в„ўt put it out alone.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA pause.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"He talks to trees. That sounds mad, I know. But IГўв‚¬в„ўve \u003cstrong\u003eseen\u003c/strong\u003e it. We were in the Bone-FieldsГўв‚¬вЂќyears ago, bad job, long storyГўв‚¬вЂќand the ground split open and something came out of the earth. Something old. And Gragnir walked up to it and \u003cstrong\u003etalked to it\u003c/strong\u003e. Not magic. Not a spell. JustГўв‚¬В¦Гўв‚¬вЂ№ spoke. Like he was speaking to something that understood.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe taps his amber eye. \"He gave me this after. Said, \u0027YouГўв‚¬в„ўve paid enough for one lifetime, Lew. This is change, not compensation.\u0027 I didnГўв‚¬в„ўt know what he meant then.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA grim smile. \"I still donГўв‚¬в„ўt, most days.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eScene: Kaelen and Lew\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLet this happen naturallyГўв‚¬вЂќaround a fire, during a march, wherever it fits:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen eyes LewГўв‚¬в„ўs amber eye. Lew notices her noticing.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"ItГўв‚¬в„ўs a gem,\" he says. \"Not glass.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"I know what it is,\" Kaelen says quietly. \"I can \u003cstrong\u003efeel\u003c/strong\u003e it. It resonates withГўв‚¬вЂќ\" She stops. Touches her ember-mark. \"With the same frequency. The same \u003cstrong\u003ehum\u003c/strong\u003e.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLew raises an eyebrow. \"Gragnir gave it to me.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Of course he did.\" Kaelen almost smiles. Almost. \"That man never gives gifts. He gives \u003cstrong\u003eobligations\u003c/strong\u003e.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis scene establishes that KaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs ember-mark and LewГўв‚¬в„ўs eye-gem share a connectionГўв‚¬вЂќboth are linked to YggdrasilГўв‚¬в„ўs root network. This will become important in Act 2.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 6: Montage Test Гўв‚¬вЂќ Round 2: The Interior Belt (Days 5Гўв‚¬вЂњ8)\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Dead Farms. The PCs remember them from the outbound journey Гўв‚¬вЂќ grey fields, empty crofts, silence. But the Interior Belt has gotten \u003cstrong\u003eworse\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eRound 2 Sample Tests\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eChallenge\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCharacteristic\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDescription\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eNavigate through refugee-clogged roads\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eReason / Presence\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe roads the PCs used outbound are now packed with refugees heading north Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cstrong\u003eaway\u003c/strong\u003e from Hrafnborg. Word has spread that the dead are gathering. The PCs are heading into the flow.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eForage in a depleted landscape\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eIntuition\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe Dead Farms have been picked clean by refugees and worse. Finding food, fuel, or shelter requires creativityГўв‚¬вЂќold root cellars, frozen caches, hunting what little game remains.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCross a collapsing bridge\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAgility / Might\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe river bridge they crossed outbound has partially collapsed. Supports rotted by the grey water. Options: repair (medium Reason test), climb across debris (easy Agility test), ford the river (medium Might test but costs Heat from cold exposure).\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAvoid undead patrol columns\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAgility / Intuition\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe dead are moving in \u003cstrong\u003eorganized columns\u003c/strong\u003e now Гўв‚¬вЂќ dozens of draugr, walking southwest, heading toward Hrafnborg. They donГўв‚¬в„ўt hunt the PCs specifically, but their routes intersect. A wrong turn puts the party in a columnГўв‚¬в„ўs path.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eMaintain supply discipline\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eReason\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eTwelve days is long. Eight days in, supplies are thinning. Rationing now affects morale (Presence tests at bane if rations are cut) but preserves options.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eKeep the party together emotionally\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePresence\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eKaelen is volatile. Lew is worried about Kaelen. The PCs are tired. Managing morale and preventing friction is its own challenge.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eRound 2 Interlude: The World is Worse Гўв‚¬вЂќ Part II\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSeed these through the Interior Belt crossing:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eA village they passed outbound is empty.\u003c/strong\u003e Not abandonedГўв‚¬вЂќempty. Doors open. Food on tables. No people, no bodies. Just absence. Footprints in the frost lead \u003cstrong\u003esouthwest\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ toward the draugr columns. The implication is horrifying: the living followed the dead. Or became them.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe sky is darker.\u003c/strong\u003e Not nightГўв‚¬вЂќa grey-brown overcast that doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt lift. The sun is a pale disc, barely visible. Kaelen says the Ever-Ember at Hrafnborg is \"straining Гўв‚¬вЂќ I can feel it from here.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRivers that were frozen outbound are now unfrozen\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ not because of warmth, but because the ice is \u003cstrong\u003erotting\u003c/strong\u003e. The water beneath is grey and doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt freeze properly anymore. It smells of iron and decay.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAt one point, the party passes a line of draugr walking southwest.\u003c/strong\u003e Dozens of them Гўв‚¬вЂќ not attacking, not hunting, just \u003cstrong\u003ewalking\u003c/strong\u003e. All heading toward Hrafnborg. They ignore the party completely, as if following instructions from elsewhere.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe column stretches back further than you can see. They walk in rough formation Гўв‚¬вЂќ three abreast, shields hanging loose, weapons rusted but functional. Their eyes are the dead grey of bog ice.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen watches them pass. \"TheyГўв‚¬в„ўre not just moving,\" she says. \"TheyГўв‚¬в„ўre \u003cstrong\u003emustering\u003c/strong\u003e. Someone is \u003cstrong\u003ecalling\u003c/strong\u003e them.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLew touches his eye. \"Southwest. Always southwest. Same direction as Hrafnborg.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe column takes twenty minutes to pass. None of the dead look at you. They have orders. You are not part of them.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs ember-mark flares once, bright enough to cast a shadow. Two or three draugr turn their heads Гўв‚¬вЂќ slowly, mechanically Гўв‚¬вЂќ and Kaelen steps back and presses her palm over the mark, hiding the light.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe draugr turn away. The column moves on.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"DonГўв‚¬в„ўt do that again,\" Lew says quietly.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 7: Negotiation Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Holdfast at Greyfen\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Negotiation | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on success\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Negotiation | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on success\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePlace this between Round 2 and Round 3. As the party approaches the mountain pass, they encounter a fortified refugee camp.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eContext\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe road to MidgardГўв‚¬в„ўs Shield passes through Greyfen Гўв‚¬вЂќ or whatГўв‚¬в„ўs left of it. The village itself is a ruin: burned timbers, caved roofs, a broken well. But someone has fortified the ruins. Barricades of stone and timber ring the village centre. Sharpened stakes face outward. Torches burn along an improvised parapet.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA voice calls from behind the barricade.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"ThatГўв‚¬в„ўs far enough. State your business or take the long way round.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou count maybe thirty people behind the walls. Civilians Гўв‚¬вЂќ families, farmers, merchants Гўв‚¬вЂќ but armed. Badly, desperately armed. Kitchen knives lashed to staves. Hunting bows with mismatched arrows. A few proper blades, notched and dull.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eTheyГўв‚¬в„ўre terrified. And terrified people are dangerous.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Negotiation\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Holdfast is led by \u003cstrong\u003eThyra Blackhand\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ a former Chainwarden sergeant who deserted her post when the dead began moving and gathered survivors to this fortified position.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eNegotiation:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eInterest:\u003c/strong\u003e 3 (Wary but willing to listen Гўв‚¬вЂќ she needs allies, even if she wonГўв‚¬в„ўt admit it)\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003ePatience:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 (how long before Thyra tells them to leave or the mob turns hostile)\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eWhat the PCs Want\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePassage through Greyfen\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ the barricades block the most direct road to the TitanГўв‚¬в„ўs Stair pass. Going around adds 2 days.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eInformation\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ Thyra knows the mountain pass conditions. She may also have news about Hrafnborg.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSupplies\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ the Holdfast is better-provisioned than the PCs expect (they raided a granary).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eWhat Thyra Wants\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eNews from the south\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ sheГўв‚¬в„ўs heard nothing from beyond the Interior Belt in weeks.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eReassurance that Hrafnborg stands\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ if the city has fallen, her plan to evacuate north is pointless.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eA solution for the dead column\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ a draugr column is expected to pass Greyfen within 24 hours. She doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt know if the barricades will hold.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eMotivations and Pitfalls\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eMotivation\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDescription\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHope (Interest +1)\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eIf the PCs share that the Green Heart still lives, or that Kaelen bears the Ember-mark, ThyraГўв‚¬в„ўs people rally. Hope is rare. This earns immediate trust.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePragmatism (Interest +1)\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eOffering practical help Гўв‚¬вЂќ tactics for the draugr column, use of fire as a weapon, lending physical labour to reinforce the barricades Гўв‚¬вЂќ speaks ThyraГўв‚¬в„ўs language.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAuthority (Interest +0, Patience ГўЛ†вЂ™1)\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eInvoking the KingГўв‚¬в„ўs name or official authority gets a cold response. Thyra deserted the Chainwardens. She doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt trust institutions anymore.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThreats (Patience ГўЛ†вЂ™2)\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAny attempt to force passage triggers immediate hostility. Thyra has nothing to lose. Her people are ready to die defending what little they have.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eKaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs Presence (Edge on Arguments)\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eIf Kaelen is present and reveals her ember-mark, the effect is immediate and powerful. Several refugees weep. One elderly man kneels. Thyra stares for a long time. \"An Ember-Keeper. Walking south. In Fimbulwinter.\" She exhales. \"Maybe weГўв‚¬в„ўre not done yet.\" For the remainder of this negotiation, all party members gain an \u003cstrong\u003eedge on argument rolls\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eOutcomes\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eInterest filled:\u003c/strong\u003e Thyra opens the gate. She provides passage, trail rations (3 days\u0027 worth), and critical intelligence: the TitanГўв‚¬в„ўs Stair is passable but treacherous Гўв‚¬вЂќ ice has claimed the upper switchbacks and a rockslide has narrowed the pass. She also shares a warning: \"The dead arenГўв‚¬в„ўt random. TheyГўв‚¬в„ўre converging. EverythingГўв‚¬в„ўs flowing toward Hrafnborg like water downhill.\" Before the PCs leave, Thyra pulls them aside: \"If Hrafnborg falls, we fall. You know that. Get to the city. get to the Ember. And \u003cstrong\u003ehold it\u003c/strong\u003e.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePatience exhausted:\u003c/strong\u003e Thyra orders the PCs away. Going around adds 2 days and denies them the supply bonus and intelligence. If the PCs push, combat beginsГўв‚¬вЂќbut fighting refugees earns no Victories and costs 1 Victory if they harm anyone.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: Thyra as a Recurring NPC\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThyra Blackhand is a potential recurring ally. If the PCs help her in any material way (tactics, supplies, even just honest news), she survives the draugr column and leads her people to Hrafnborg, arriving during or after the siege. In Act 2, she becomes a valuable military contact Гўв‚¬вЂќ a sergeant who knows how to fight the dead.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs ignore Greyfen or fail the negotiation badly, ThyraГўв‚¬в„ўs holdfast falls to the draugr column. The PCs may find the aftermath on a later journey: barricades broken, bodies frozen, stakes still standing.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 8: Final Approach Гўв‚¬вЂќ Mountain Crossing to Hrafnborg\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe final phase. The PCs retrace their path through MidgardГўв‚¬в„ўs Shield Гўв‚¬вЂќ the mountain range separating the Interior Belt from the coast. The TitanГўв‚¬в„ўs Stair pass is their route back.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe weather has \u003cstrong\u003eturned\u003c/strong\u003e. This is the first true blizzard of early winter. Heyannir is the threshold monthГўв‚¬вЂќthe last of Sumar giving way to Vetr. The Fimbulwinter makes the transition savage.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eNarrative Interlude: The View from the Summit\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAt the summit of TitanГўв‚¬в„ўs Stair, the wind drops. Just for a momentГўв‚¬вЂќa gap between gusts, a breath of stillness in the blizzard.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAnd from the summit, looking south toward the coast, you see it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHrafnborg.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Ever-EmberГўв‚¬в„ўs light is visible even through the stormГўв‚¬вЂќa warm amber glow on the horizon, impossibly bright and impossibly small. Like a candle in a cathedral.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBut around it: \u003cstrong\u003edarkness\u003c/strong\u003e. Not storm-darkness. Something else. A stain on the land, surrounding the city in every direction. From this distance, it could be shadow. It could be an army.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs ember-mark blazes. She gasps and grabs at her forehead.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"ItГўв‚¬в„ўs still lit,\" she says. \"The EmberГўв‚¬в„ўs still burning.\" She pauses. \"But itГўв‚¬в„ўs \u003cstrong\u003escreaming\u003c/strong\u003e. Something is pressing against it. Something cold and old and patient.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLew squints into the distance. \"What am I looking at? Is thatГўв‚¬вЂќare thoseГўв‚¬вЂќ\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Yes,\" Kaelen says. \"The dead.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe wind returns. The summit vanishes in white. The PCs begin the descent.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 9: Montage Outcomes (Round 1Гўв‚¬вЂњ2)\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 style=\"color:#66ff66;\"\u003eTotal Success (5+ successes before 3 failures)\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eReturn journey is swift and efficient. The party arrives near Hrafnborg with supplies, energy, and time.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEarn \u003cstrong\u003e2 Victories\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe undead column is behind themГўв‚¬вЂќtheyГўв‚¬в„ўve outpaced the dead.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen is shaken but steady. SheГўв‚¬в„ўs ready to face the Ember.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 style=\"color:#ffff66;\"\u003ePartial Success (failure limit hit, but 2+ more successes than failures)\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe party reaches the outskirts of Hrafnborg, but at cost. Choose one:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHeat cost:\u003c/strong\u003e Rations are gone. The party is starving by the time they sight Hrafnborg.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTime cost:\u003c/strong\u003e The return took longer than expected. The undead column is \u003cstrong\u003eahead\u003c/strong\u003e of them, and Hrafnborg is already under pressure when they arrive.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eInjury cost:\u003c/strong\u003e One PC was injured in the mountain crossingГўв‚¬вЂќa fall, a rockslide, a frostbiten limb. They arrive with 1 fewer Recovery.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEarn \u003cstrong\u003e1 Victory\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 style=\"color:#ff6666;\"\u003eTotal Failure\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe party arrives but is exhausted and compromised.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAll PCs and NPCs lose 1 Recovery.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe undead army has already reached Hrafnborg. The siege has begun \u003cstrong\u003eand the PCs are outside the walls\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNo Victories earned. Director gains 4 Malice for the Act 1 climax.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 10: GragnirГўв‚¬в„ўs Appearance Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Reveal\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis is the turning point of Beat 8 and the setup for Act 1Гўв‚¬в„ўs climax.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eWhen It Happens\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAfter the montage test concludes, as the party camps within a dayГўв‚¬в„ўs travel of Hrafnborg Гўв‚¬вЂќ near the base of the mountains on the coastal side. The fire burns low. The night is cold. The PCs can see the distant glow of HrafnborgГўв‚¬в„ўs Ever-Ember on the horizonГўв‚¬вЂќor perhaps the glow of fires that arenГўв‚¬в„ўt Ever-Embers at all.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Arrival\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe fire pops. A log shifts.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAnd Gragnir is there.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHeГўв‚¬в„ўs sitting on the other side of the fire, as if heГўв‚¬в„ўs been there for hours. His soot-stained hands rest on his knees. His grey furs are dusted with ash. He looks \u003cstrong\u003etired\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќnot the fatigue of travel, but the exhaustion of someone who has been fighting a war no one else can see.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"You found her,\" he says, looking at Kaelen. His voice is rough. \"Good.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen stiffens. \"Gragnir.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Kaelen.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThey look at each other across the fire. Something old and uncomfortable passes between them.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"We need to talk,\" Gragnir says. \"All of us. Now. Before tomorrow.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eGragnirГўв‚¬в„ўs Warning\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eGragnir speaks plainly for the first time. He is done with riddles.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"Your King has a companion,\" Gragnir says quietly. He stares into the fire. \"A grey hound. Sits at his feet during every council. Sleeps at the foot of his bed. Follows him to the Ever-Ember chamber. Never barks. Never eats. Just watches.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHis black fingers tighten on his knees.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"It is not a dog. It is not a wolf. It is a \u003cstrong\u003eshape-walker\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ a fragment given form. A spy. And it has been listening to every word spoken in the KingГўв‚¬в„ўs presence since before you arrived in Hrafnborg.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe looks at each of you in turn.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"It is listening \u003cstrong\u003eright now\u003c/strong\u003e. Over two hundred miles away. Sitting beside your King in the dark.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLet the PCs react. The crucial horror: Dreyfus is not here. He is not at the edge of the firelight. He is not on the road behind them. He is in Hrafnborg, at HaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs side, and has been the entire time. Every conversation the King has had since they left Гўв‚¬вЂќ about the mission, about troop movements, about the cityГўв‚¬в„ўs defences Гўв‚¬вЂќ Dreyfus has heard. And through the Wyrd-channels Гўв‚¬вЂќ root-whispers carried through YggdrasilГўв‚¬в„ўs dying network Гўв‚¬вЂќ that intelligence flows directly to GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs agents in the field.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs cannot confront Dreyfus. They cannot warn Harald. They are over two hundred miles from Hrafnborg, and the spy is still whispering.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Truth About Grafvitnir\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"Its masterГўв‚¬в„ўs name is Grafvitnir,\" Gragnir says. The word falls like a stone. \"The Grave-Wolf. An entity older than Svellheim, older than the Ember-Keepers, older than anything that walks above ground.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe stands. The fire dips as if his shadow weighs more than it should.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Grafvitnir was imprisoned during the First KindlingГўв‚¬вЂќwhen the original Ember-Keepers sealed the root-chamber beneath YggdrasilГўв‚¬в„ўs deepest root. It was not killed. It cannot be killed. It was \u003cstrong\u003ebound\u003c/strong\u003eГўв‚¬вЂќby fire, by oath, by the roots of the World Tree itself.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe looks at each of you in turn.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Every Ever-Ember that fails is a lock that opens. Every Keeper who dies is a chain that breaks. When the last Ember goes darkГўв‚¬вЂќGrafvitnir walks free. And when the Grave-Wolf walks, the dead do not rest. Not in their graves. Not anywhere.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf someone asks Gragnir \u003cem\u003ehow\u003c/em\u003e the binding works Гўв‚¬вЂќ how fire can hold something like the Grave-Wolf in the earth Гўв‚¬вЂќ he picks up a handful of ash from the fireГўв‚¬в„ўs edge and squeezes it in his fist.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eГўв‚¬Е“Think of it as... the space between the world and the dark place underneath. Not a wall. Not a door. A \u003cem\u003esubstance\u003c/em\u003e. Thick, like the fat on a cold stew. While the Embers burn, the substance is dense Гўв‚¬вЂќ nothing can push through it. Nothing below can reach up. Nothing dead can crawl out.Гўв‚¬Вќ\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHe opens his hand. The ash sifts through his fingers.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eГўв‚¬Е“But every Ember that goes out Гўв‚¬вЂќ the substance thins. Things begin to seep. Small things first. Cold. Whispers. The dead stirring in their barrows. Then bigger things. Bolder things. Things with teeth and purpose.Гўв‚¬Вќ\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHe dusts his palm on his knee.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eГўв‚¬Е“When the last Ember fails, the substance is gone. There is nothing between the Grave-Wolf and the sky.Гўв‚¬Вќ\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ Director Note: The Barrier Metaphor\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis is the campaignГўв‚¬в„ўs core metaphysical explanation. The binding is not a cage or a chain Гўв‚¬вЂќ it is a \u003cem\u003ebarrier substance\u003c/em\u003e, a dense membrane between realms. Strong flame = thick barrier. Weak flame = thin barrier. No flame = no barrier. Every supernatural symptom the party has encountered Гўв‚¬вЂќ the dead farms, the Ashen Woods decay, the Pale MawГўв‚¬в„ўs growing boldness, the cold that seeps up from below Гўв‚¬вЂќ is a consequence of the barrier thinning. When Kaelen eventually transforms at the Green Heart, she is not merely Гўв‚¬Е“sealing locksГўв‚¬Вќ Гўв‚¬вЂќ she is \u003cem\u003erestoring the barrierГўв‚¬в„ўs density\u003c/em\u003e, becoming the substance itself. This is the framework Gragnir gives them. It should inform how they understand everything that follows.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Horror of Distance\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThere is no confrontation. There is no shape-shifting escape. There is only the dawning understanding that the enemyГўв‚¬в„ўs greatest weapon is over two hundred miles behind them, curled at the feet of their King, and they cannot do a single thing about it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eKaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs face goes white. \"He heard everything. When Harald told us about the Ever-Ember. When he gave us our mission. Every name, every route, every supply count.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLew is very still. \"ThatГўв‚¬в„ўs how they always knew where we were. Not a tracker on the road. A listener in the throne room.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eGragnir nods.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"It has been reporting since before you left Hrafnborg. Everything you told the King, Grafvitnir knows. Your mission. Your route. Your allies.\" He looks at Kaelen. \"Especially you.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"And when you return,\" he says, \"the hound will still be there. Sitting. Watching. It cannot act directly Гўв‚¬вЂќ guest-right binds even shape-walkers. But it does not need to act. It only needs to \u003cstrong\u003elisten\u003c/strong\u003e.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: Gragnir After the Reveal\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGragnir doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt stay long. He came to deliver this warning and to prepare the PCs for whatГўв‚¬в„ўs ahead.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe key dramatic tension: the party now KNOWS about Dreyfus, but Dreyfus doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt know they know. When they return to Hrafnborg, they must decide how to handle this Гўв‚¬вЂќ warn Harald openly (which alerts Dreyfus), try to act in secret, or simply endure the spyГўв‚¬в„ўs presence while they work. This tension carries into Act 2.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs ask questions:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\"Why didnГўв‚¬в„ўt you tell us sooner?\"\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \"Because you needed to see the world first. The dead farms. The Ashen Woods. The Green Heart. You needed to understand whatГўв‚¬в„ўs dying before I could explain \u003cstrong\u003ewhy\u003c/strong\u003e itГўв‚¬в„ўs dying.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\"Can we stop Grafvitnir?\"\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \"Not yet. Not with what you are now. But you can slow him. The Ever-Ember at Hrafnborg still burns. If Kaelen can speak to itГўв‚¬вЂќtruly speakГўв‚¬вЂќit may tell us how the bindings can be renewed.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\"What does Grafvitnir want?\"\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \"Freedom. And then? The end of everything green, everything warm, everything that remembers the light. The Grave-Wolf does not hate life. It simply \u003cstrong\u003edoes not recognize it as valid\u003c/strong\u003e.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\"Can we expose the hound?\"\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \"You can try. But guest-right is ancient law. Even Harald Гўв‚¬вЂќ especially Harald Гўв‚¬вЂќ cannot simply destroy a creature under his roof. And the shape-walker is clever. If it feels cornered, it will act. Better to know where the spy sits than to drive it into hiding.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\"Where have you been?\"\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \"Tending whatГўв‚¬в„ўs left. The roots are sick, not dead. I have been speaking to themГўв‚¬вЂќasking them to hold on a little longer. TheyГўв‚¬в„ўre listening. Barely.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\"WhatГўв‚¬в„ўs our next move?\"\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \"Get to Hrafnborg. Get Kaelen to the Ever-Ember. And pray the flame still recognizes her voice. As for the houndГўв‚¬В¦Гўв‚¬вЂ№ youГўв‚¬в„ўll have to decide what to do about that yourselves.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003eGragnirГўв‚¬в„ўs Price\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAs Gragnir rises to leave, he pauses. He looks at the fire Гўв‚¬вЂќ not at the party, not at Kaelen. At the fire.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eГўв‚¬Е“One more thing.Гўв‚¬Вќ His voice is quieter now. Not softer Гўв‚¬вЂќ quieter, the way a blade is quiet before it cuts.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eГўв‚¬Е“Your King gave you a mission. Find the Keeper. Bring her back. Good. Simple. A kingГўв‚¬в„ўs errand.Гўв‚¬Вќ\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHe turns to face the party.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eГўв‚¬Е“But the roots donГўв‚¬в„ўt answer to kings. Yggdrasil doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt care about HrafnborgГўв‚¬в„ўs walls or HaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs council or who sits on what throne. The tree cares about surviving. The binding cares about holding. And when those two things conflict with your KingГўв‚¬в„ўs orders Гўв‚¬вЂќ when serving the roots means defying the crown Гўв‚¬вЂќ you will have to choose.Гўв‚¬Вќ\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHe holds out his hand, palm up. Soot falls from his fingers like black snow.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eГўв‚¬Е“Swear to me. Not to Harald. Not to the Konungs-ferГўв‚¬вЂќ. Swear to the roots themselves: that when the moment comes, you will serve YggdrasilГўв‚¬в„ўs renewal above all other obligations. Above politics. Above loyalty. Above every comfortable promise youГўв‚¬в„ўve made to comfortable people in comfortable rooms.Гўв‚¬Вќ\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHe waits. The fire pops.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eГўв‚¬Е“If you cannot swear this, I will still help you. But I will know what you are. And so will the roots.Гўв‚¬Вќ\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ Director Note: The Root-Oath and Its Cost\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis oath \u003cem\u003edirectly conflicts\u003c/em\u003e with the Konungs-ferГўв‚¬вЂќ oath sworn to Harald in Beat 3. The party swore to serve the KingГўв‚¬в„ўs mission. Now Gragnir asks them to swear that, if forced to choose, they will serve the roots over the crown.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis is not hypothetical. The conflict will manifest:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eIn Act 2, when the party must decide whether to pursue the mission as Harald defined it (bring Kaelen back to Hrafnborg) or follow the rootsГўв‚¬в„ў guidance (which leads Kaelen north, away from the city, toward the Emberwell)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eIn Act 3, when HrafnborgГўв‚¬в„ўs political survival and YggdrasilГўв‚¬в„ўs ecological survival may require different sacrifices\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf the party swears the Root-Oath, they gain GragnirГўв‚¬в„ўs full trust and future cooperation. He will appear when the roots tell him to, and he will share information freely.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf the party refuses, Gragnir nods once. Гўв‚¬Е“Honest, at least. I can work with honest.Гўв‚¬Вќ He will still help, but he will withhold certain information Гўв‚¬вЂќ specifically, he will not reveal the location of the Green Heart until the party proves their commitment through actions rather than words.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eWord economy:\u003c/em\u003e This is a binding oath. If the party swears and later chooses HaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs orders over the rootsГўв‚¬в„ў needs, they lose 2 Word permanently and Gragnir will not answer their calls.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eGragnir departs before dawn. He does not say goodbye. He says: \"IГўв‚¬в„ўll find you when the roots tell me to.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen watches him go with an expression that is equal parts respect and resentment.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"That man has never once explained himself \u003cstrong\u003ebefore\u003c/strong\u003e it was almost too late,\" she says. \"Not once.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 11: Level Up\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAfter the reveal, with Hrafnborg visible on the horizon and the full weight of the crisis now understood:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe party advances to Level 3.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: Level-Up Moment\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFrame this as: the PCs have crossed a threshold. They started as local volunteers answering a summons. Now they understand the shape of the crisisГўв‚¬вЂќthe dying tree, the bound evil, the failing embers. They arenГўв‚¬в„ўt travelers anymore. TheyГўв‚¬в„ўre \u003cstrong\u003eagents of the flame\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLevel 3 in Draw Steel means access to more powerful abilities and better survivability. TheyГўв‚¬в„ўll need both for whatГўв‚¬в„ўs coming.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 12: Approach to Hrafnborg\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe final scene of Beat 8: the PCs crest the last ridge before Hrafnborg and see what awaits them.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou see Hrafnborg at dawn. The Ever-EmberГўв‚¬в„ўs glow is visible from miles awayГўв‚¬вЂќa small orange star in a grey world.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBut around it: \u003cstrong\u003edarkness\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe walls are intact. The gates are closed. Fires burn along the rampartsГўв‚¬вЂќnot warmth, but signal-fires. And beyond the walls, in a ring that stretches from the coast to the foothills, the dead stand.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThousands of them. Draugr, ghosts, barrow-wights, frost-walkersГўв‚¬вЂќa silent army of the restless dead, shoulder to shoulder, unmoving. Not attacking. Not retreating.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWaiting.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHrafnborg is under siege.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eOutcomes\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBy the end of this beat, the PCs should have:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCrossed over two hundred miles of deteriorating terrain and bonded with Kaelen and Lew.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWitnessed the worldГўв‚¬в„ўs accelerating collapse: empty villages, draugr columns, failing infrastructure.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNegotiated with survivors at Greyfen and seen how desperate the common folk have become.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLearned the truth about Dreyfus (shape-walker spy still at HaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs side, NГѓВ­ГѓВ°hГѓВ¶ggrГўв‚¬в„ўs eyes and ears) and the deeper threat (Grafvitnir, the Grave-Wolf, imprisoned and weakening).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eUnderstood the cosmic stakes: every failing Ever-Ember weakens GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs prison.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLearned the spy remains at the KingГўв‚¬в„ўs side in Hrafnborg Гўв‚¬вЂќ a ticking bomb they must decide how to handle.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAdvanced to Level 3.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSeen Hrafnborg under siegeГўв‚¬вЂќthe Act 1 climax is here.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#2a6a2a;\"\u003eBeat 8 Гўв‚¬вЂќ Victory Point Summary\u003c/h4\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:8px 0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#c0e0c0;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eEvent\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eDifficulty\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eVP Award\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eParts 3+6: Return Montage (2 rounds)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eModerate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eup to 2 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 7: Holdfast Negotiation\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eModerate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e1 VP on success\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#98cc98;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eBeat Total (Mandatory)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eup to 3 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#2a6a2a;\"\u003eBeat 8 Гўв‚¬вЂќ Victory Point Summary\u003c/h4\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:8px 0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#c0e0c0;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eEvent\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eDifficulty\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eVP Award\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eParts 3+6: Return Montage (2 rounds)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eModerate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eup to 2 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 7: Holdfast Negotiation\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eModerate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e1 VP on success\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#98cc98;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eBeat Total (Mandatory)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eup to 3 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eTransition to Beat 9\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHrafnborg is surrounded. The dead donГўв‚¬в„ўt attackГўв‚¬вЂќthey wait. But the city is cut off, supplies are dwindling, and the Ever-Ember burns lower every day.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs must break through the siege line and reach the city. Inside, theyГўв‚¬в„ўll learn the final truth: Yggdrasil is dying, and only a journey to the Emberwell can renew the spark.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eProceed to \u003cstrong\u003eBeat 9: The Siege of Hrafnborg\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","markdown":null},"src":null,"system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"sort":80,"flags":{},"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"exportSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"draw-steel","systemVersion":"0.10.0","createdTime":0,"modifiedTime":0,"lastModifiedBy":null}},{"_id":"RTFPAGE000000026","name":"Beat 9 Гўв‚¬вЂќ The Siege of Hrafnborg","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 3\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eDuration:\u003c/strong\u003e 2-3 sessions\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eLocation:\u003c/strong\u003e Hrafnborg outskirts, the siege line, Hrafnborg interior, the Ever-Ember chamber\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eKey NPCs:\u003c/strong\u003e High King Harald, Kaelen, Lew, Gragnir (brief appearance)\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard Montage Test, reunion scene, ritual narrative, Boss combat encounter, Act 2 hook\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eTone:\u003c/strong\u003e Desperation, siege horror, revelation, sacrifice, and the pivot from survival to quest\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1a3a; color:#c8c8e8; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4a4ac8;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVP Status Гўв‚¬вЂќ Entering This Beat\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cstrong\u003eTotal VP (max):\u003c/strong\u003e 21 | \u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 | \u003cstrong\u003eVP into Level:\u003c/strong\u003e 5\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1a3a; color:#c8c8e8; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4a4ac8;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVP Status Гўв‚¬вЂќ Entering This Beat\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cstrong\u003eTotal VP (max):\u003c/strong\u003e 21 | \u003cstrong\u003eLevel:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 | \u003cstrong\u003eVP into Level:\u003c/strong\u003e 5\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2\u003eOverview\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Act 1 climax. Hrafnborg is encircled by thousands of silent undead Гўв‚¬вЂќ not attacking, not retreating, simply \u003cem\u003ewaiting\u003c/em\u003e. The Ever-Ember burns lower every hour. The city is cut off, supplies are dwindling, and morale is crumbling.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs must:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBreak through the siege line\u003c/strong\u003e to reach the city (Hard Montage Test with combat complications).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eReunite with Harald\u003c/strong\u003e and witness the besieged cityГўв‚¬в„ўs desperation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBring Kaelen to the Ever-Ember\u003c/strong\u003e and witness her attempt to speak to the flame.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDefend the ritual\u003c/strong\u003e when the undead sense what Kaelen is doing and breach the walls (Boss combat).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLearn the final truth:\u003c/strong\u003e Yggdrasil itself is dying. The Embers cannot be sustained Гўв‚¬вЂќ only renewed at the source. The Emberwell awaits.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis beat ends Act 1 and pivots the campaign from \u003cem\u003efind the Keeper\u003c/em\u003e to \u003cem\u003esave the World-Tree\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 1: The Silent Ring\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs stand on the last ridge before Hrafnborg. Beat 8 ended with the image of the siege. Now they must reckon with it up close.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFrom the ridge, the scale of it hits you.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe dead surround Hrafnborg in a ring three bodies deep. Draugr stand shoulder to shoulder, frost-blue and motionless, their burial shrouds barely stirring. Behind them, taller shapes Гўв‚¬вЂќ barrow-wights in rusted hauberks, spectral figures that flicker at the edge of sight. And farther back, in the fog off the fjord, darker things move Гўв‚¬вЂќ vast and slow.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eNone of them make a sound.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe cityГўв‚¬в„ўs walls are intact. Signal-fires burn along the ramparts. You can see guards Гўв‚¬вЂќ living guards Гўв‚¬вЂќ pacing the wall-walk, their torch-light catching on spear-tips. The Ever-EmberГўв‚¬в„ўs glow is visible above the roofline: a faint orange star, dimmer than it should be.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eNo one is getting in. No one is getting out.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eReconnaissance\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBefore attempting the breach, the PCs can observe the siege line. Allow Investigation and tests:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEasy Intuition test:\u003c/strong\u003e The undead are densest at the main gates and the harbour approach. The southwestern stretch Гўв‚¬вЂќ near the old tanneries Гўв‚¬вЂќ is thinner. The ground there is marshy and unstable, which the dead seem to avoid.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMedium Reason test:\u003c/strong\u003e The siege isnГўв‚¬в„ўt tactical in the normal sense. There are no siege engines, no trenches, no supply lines. This is a \u003cem\u003espiritual\u003c/em\u003e blockade Гўв‚¬вЂќ the dead are drawn to the Ever-Ember like moths to a candle, pressing against its warmth. They arenГўв‚¬в„ўt commanded. TheyГўв‚¬в„ўre \u003cem\u003ecompelled\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEasy Might test:\u003c/strong\u003e A group this size means the barrow-fields for fifty miles around have emptied. This isnГўв‚¬в„ўt a local uprising Гўв‚¬вЂќ this is \u003cem\u003eevery grave in the Coastal Belt\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: The Nature of the Siege\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe dead are not under GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs direct command here. The Grave-Wolf is still imprisoned Гўв‚¬вЂќ but as the Ever-Embers weaken, the boundary between life and death thins. The dead simply \u003cem\u003erise\u003c/em\u003e and are drawn to the largest remaining source of warmth.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis is important thematically: the siege isnГўв‚¬в„ўt an army with a general. ItГўв‚¬в„ўs a symptom. A fever. The dead are the immune response of a dying world.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSome GM options for flavour:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe dead occasionally shift, like a crowd swaying. No individual moves Гўв‚¬вЂќ the whole ring breathes.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf anyone shouts, the nearest draugr turn their heads. Slowly. Then turn back.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eA few of the dead are \u003cem\u003erecent\u003c/em\u003e. Fresh faces. Villagers who died in the last week.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eKaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs Reaction\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen stares at the siege line. Her ember-mark flickers Гўв‚¬вЂќ the scar on her forehead glowing, then dimming, in rhythm with the distant Ever-Ember.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"ItГўв‚¬в„ўs calling them,\" Kaelen whispers. Her hand goes to her forehead, pressing the ember-mark. \"The flame is so weak itГўв‚¬в„ўs pulling instead of pushing. ItГўв‚¬в„ўs trying to feed, and all it can find isГўв‚¬В¦ the dead.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eShe looks at you. Her eyes are wet, and her voice is steel.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"We have to get in there. Now.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eLewГўв‚¬в„ўs Assessment\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLew studies the line with his amber eye, which pulses faintly.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"The southwest, near the tannery ditches. The groundГўв‚¬в„ўs soft Гўв‚¬вЂќ even dead legs donГўв‚¬в„ўt like mud. The lineГўв‚¬в„ўs two deep there instead of three, and the wights are clustered near the gates, not the margins.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe pauses. \"ItГўв‚¬в„ўs not a door. But itГўв‚¬в„ўs the closest thing to one.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 2: Breaking the Line (Hard Montage Test)\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Montage Test | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 VP on hard success, 1 VP success, 0 VP failure (2 rounds)\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Montage Test | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 VP on hard success, 1 VP success, 0 VP failure (2 rounds)\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe party must cross the siege ring and reach HrafnborgГўв‚¬в„ўs walls. The southwestern approach through the tannery marshes is the best route Гўв‚¬вЂќ but \"best\" is relative.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eParty Size Adjustment (4 heroes + 2 NPC companions):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDifficulty\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eSuccess Limit\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eFailure Limit\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHard (adjusted)\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e6\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e2\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRounds:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 montage test rounds. A combat complication triggers between rounds.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eNPC Contributions:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLew:\u003c/strong\u003e Assists one PCГўв‚¬в„ўs test per round (Intuition +4). His eye picks out the gaps in the line, the soft ground, the moments when the dead shift and create openings.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eKaelen:\u003c/strong\u003e Assists one PCГўв‚¬в„ўs test per round (Might +3 or Presence +2). She can suppress her ember-markГўв‚¬в„ўs glow temporarily, or physically shield someone from a grasping hand.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eRound 1: The Approach\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe party descends from the ridge, crosses open ground, and enters the tannery marshes. They must reach the edge of the siege ring without drawing the full hostГўв‚¬в„ўs attention.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eTest\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCharacteristic\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDescription\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eNavigate the marsh\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eIntuition\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePick a path through frozen mud and tannery runoff without getting stuck or making noise.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eControl your fear\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePresence\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe dead are \u003cem\u003eright there\u003c/em\u003e. Suppress panic and keep moving quietly.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMove unseen\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAgility\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eSlip between the bodies. Time your steps to the ringГўв‚¬в„ўs slow breathing.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePhysical endurance\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eMight\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCrawl through freezing muck, lift stuck companions, push through reeds.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRead the pattern\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eReason\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe dead shift in waves. Predict the next gap and signal the group.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSuppress the mark\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePresence (Kaelen only)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eKaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs ember-mark is drawing attention. Help her muffle the glow with mud, cloth, or will.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eNarrative Interlude: Among the Dead\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBetween rounds, describe the horror of being \u003cem\u003einside\u003c/em\u003e the siege ring.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYouГўв‚¬в„ўre among them now. The smell hits first Гўв‚¬вЂќ not rot, but \u003cem\u003ecold\u003c/em\u003e. A deep, mineral cold, like the inside of a cave that has never seen sunlight.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThey stand around you. Close enough to touch. A draugr in a farmerГўв‚¬в„ўs clothes, his jaw hanging loose, frost threading through his beard. A woman in a burial shift, her eyes blank white, her hands curled around nothing. A child.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eNone of them look at you.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen has her hand pressed over her forehead so hard her knuckles are white. The ember-mark pulses beneath her fingers like a second heartbeat.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Keep. Moving,\" Lew hisses.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eCombat Complication: The Watchers\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Combat (Optional - mid-montage complication) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on victory\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Combat (Optional - mid-montage complication) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 VP on victory\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBetween Round 1 and Round 2, something notices the party.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA cluster of \u003cstrong\u003eFrost-Ghouls\u003c/strong\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ faster, hungrier dead that have been circling the siege ringГўв‚¬в„ўs edge like sharks Гўв‚¬вЂќ detect the partyГўв‚¬в„ўs warmth. They donГўв‚¬в„ўt raise an alarm (the dead donГўв‚¬в„ўt communicate that way), but they attack.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eCombat: The Watchers in the Marsh\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Moderate (Level 3 PCs)\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSpecial Constraint:\u003c/strong\u003e This fight must be \u003cem\u003efast and quiet\u003c/em\u003e. If it drags past 3 rounds, the siege ring begins to close Гўв‚¬вЂќ see \"Noise Penalty\" below.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEnemies:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e4 \u003cstrong\u003eFrost-Ghouls\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 2 Standard)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTerrain:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFrozen marsh (difficult terrain throughout)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTannery channels (1-square-wide trenches, 4 feet deep, filled with icy chemical runoff Гўв‚¬вЂќ creature that falls in takes 3 cold damage and is restrained until they spend a move action to climb out)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDead standing (the surrounding draugr are effectively walls/obstacles Гўв‚¬вЂќ they donГўв‚¬в„ўt fight, but they block movement. Treat as blocking terrain.)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLighting:\u003c/strong\u003e None. The PCs cannot use torches or lanterns without drawing the entire host. If a PC has darkvision or another light source (KaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs ember-mark gives dim light within 1 square), they fight normally. Otherwise, attacks have a bane.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eFrost-Ghoul (Level 2 Standard)\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eUndead, Medium\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eStamina:\u003c/strong\u003e 24 | \u003cstrong\u003eSpeed:\u003c/strong\u003e 7 (unusually fast) | \u003cstrong\u003eSize:\u003c/strong\u003e M | \u003cstrong\u003eStability:\u003c/strong\u003e 0\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCharacteristics:\u003c/strong\u003e Might +2, Agility +4, Reason ГўЛ†вЂ™2, Intuition +3, Presence ГўЛ†вЂ™1\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAttacks:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFrost-Rake\u003c/strong\u003e (Melee, Agility): +5 vs. Agility; 5 cold damage and target is slowed (save ends).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePounce\u003c/strong\u003e (Move + Melee, Agility, 3 Malice): The frost-ghoul shifts up to its speed and makes a Frost-Rake attack. If the target is already slowed, they are instead restrained (save ends).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFeatures:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eHeat-Seeker:\u003c/em\u003e The frost-ghoul has an edge on attacks against targets that are the warmest creature within 3 squares (effectively: anyone holding a torch, standing near KaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs ember-mark, or who has used a fire-based ability this encounter).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eFragile Dead:\u003c/em\u003e When the frost-ghoul takes 10+ damage from a single attack, it is dazed until the end of its next turn.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eUnfeeling:\u003c/em\u003e Immune to fear, charm, and pain-based effects.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAppearance:\u003c/strong\u003e Lean, hunched, with elongated fingers ending in frost-blackened claws. Moves on all fours. Eyes glow pale blue. Constantly exhales plumes of freezing vapor.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#3a1a1a; color:#e0d0c0; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #cc3333;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#ff6666;\"\u003eГўЕЎВ  Noise Penalty\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf the fight lasts more than \u003cstrong\u003e3 rounds\u003c/strong\u003e, the commotion draws the siege ringГўв‚¬в„ўs attention. At the start of round 4 and each subsequent round:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e2 \u003cstrong\u003eDraugr Thralls\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 1 Minions, as per MODULE.adoc) shamble toward the fighting.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe available movement space shrinks by 1 square on each edge as the dead close in.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis is not winnable as a sustained fight. The PCs must finish the ghouls and \u003cem\u003emove\u003c/em\u003e. If they are still fighting at round 6, the entire host turns Гўв‚¬вЂќ run the retreat rules from the Draw Steel chase mechanics (or simply narrate a desperate scramble with consequences).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eRound 2: The Final Sprint\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAfter the ghoul fight, the party is close to the walls but exposed. The siege ring has shifted Гўв‚¬вЂќ the gap is closing.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eTest\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCharacteristic\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDescription\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSprint through the gap\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eMight\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eRaw speed and endurance through freezing mud while the dead close in.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFind the postern\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eReason\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHrafnborgГўв‚¬в„ўs walls have a tannery waste-gate. Find it in the dark.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSignal the wall\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePresence\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eGet the attention of the guards on the wall without alerting the dead. Use the KingГўв‚¬в„ўs cipher, a lantern code, or pure desperate shouting.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCover the retreat\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eAgility\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eStay behind, draw attention away from the group, then slip through at the last moment.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eShield Kaelen\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eMight or Presence\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eThe ember-mark is flaring. Put yourself between Kaelen and the reaching hands.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eKeep Lew moving\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eIntuition\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eLew is flagging (heГўв‚¬в„ўs no warrior). Keep him on his feet and moving forward.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eMontage Outcomes\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTotal Success (5+ successes, 0 failures):\u003c/strong\u003e The party reaches the postern gate undetected. Guards open it immediately Гўв‚¬вЂќ they recognize the KingГўв‚¬в„ўs cipher. The group enters without combat. +1 Victory.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePartial Success (reached success limit with 1 failure):\u003c/strong\u003e The party reaches the gate, but the commotion draws a secondary wave. They make it through, but one PC takes 5 damage from grasping hands, and the guards have to seal the gate with fire and oil. HrafnborgГўв‚¬в„ўs defenses are weakened Гўв‚¬вЂќ ГўЛ†вЂ™1 to the cityГўв‚¬в„ўs Defence Track (see Part 5).\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFailure (reached failure limit before success):\u003c/strong\u003e The postern route collapses. The dead surge. The party fights a running battle to the main gate, where Harald orders a sortie to pull them in. Each PC takes 8 damage. The sortie costs lives Гўв‚¬вЂќ 6 Hrafnborg guards die. HaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs anger and grief set the tone for the reunion scene. ГўЛ†вЂ™2 to the cityГўв‚¬в„ўs Defence Track.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 3: Inside the Walls\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eFirst Impressions\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHrafnborg under siege is a different city from the one the PCs left.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe city you remember is gone.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe streets are half-empty. The market square has been converted into a triage station Гўв‚¬вЂќ rows of cots under canvas, tended by exhausted healers. The Chainwardens\u0027 ledger-house has a queue stretching around the block: ration distribution.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eChildren donГўв‚¬в„ўt play. Dogs donГўв‚¬в„ўt bark. The only constant sound is the wind and the low, persistent hum of the Ever-Ember Гўв‚¬вЂќ a sound you can feel in your teeth more than hear.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eGuards walk the walls in double shifts. Their faces are hollow. Several wear bandages. One is missing an arm.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAnd over everything, the Ever-Ember burns Гўв‚¬вЂќ small, orange, and tired. It used to light the whole city. Now its glow barely reaches the second ring of buildings.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eDetails of the Siege\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the PCs investigate or ask questions:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDuration:\u003c/strong\u003e The siege began four days ago. The dead appeared overnight Гўв‚¬вЂќ no warning, no scouts, just a ring of corpses at dawn.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAttacks:\u003c/strong\u003e Three probing assaults so far. The dead push against the walls in waves, then retreat. Each wave is slightly larger. The guards have held, but at cost.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSupplies:\u003c/strong\u003e Two weeks of rationed food. Water is fine (wells are inside the walls). Fuel is the crisis Гўв‚¬вЂќ the Ever-Ember consumes fuel faster as it weakens, and the supply caravans are cut off.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMorale:\u003c/strong\u003e Terrible. Rumours range from \"the gods have abandoned us\" to \"the King caused this\" to \"the dead want someone specific.\" That last one is uncomfortably close to the truth.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Pale Maw:\u003c/strong\u003e Active inside the city. Preaching that resistance is futile, that the world should be allowed to end cleanly. Harald has arrested two of their agitators, which only makes them louder.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eHrafnborg Defence Track\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eUse a simple Defence Track to represent the cityГўв‚¬в„ўs ability to hold. Start at \u003cstrong\u003e10\u003c/strong\u003e. Reduce by the montage failure penalty (if any). Further reductions happen during the wall breach in Part 5.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eTrack Value\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCity Status\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e10-8\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHolding. Guards are tired but disciplined. Walls intact.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e7-5\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eStrained. Sections of wall require reinforcement. Rationing tightened.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e4-2\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eCritical. Breaches patched with rubble. Fires on the wall-walk. Civilian casualties.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e1-0\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eFalling. The dead are inside the second ring. Evacuation to the Ember chamber.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis track is a GM tool Гўв‚¬вЂќ the PCs donГўв‚¬в„ўt see the number, but they see the consequences.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eReunion with Harald\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHarald meets the PCs in person Гўв‚¬вЂќ not in his sitting room this time, but in the wall-walk command post, a fortified tower overlooking the main gate.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHarald is armoured now. Not the simple wool tunic of your first meeting Гўв‚¬вЂќ iron mail, scarred leather, a sword at his hip that has clearly seen use. His face is gaunt. His eyes are harder.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhen he sees you, something cracks behind those eyes. Relief, quickly mastered.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"You made it.\" His gaze moves to Kaelen. He studies her for a long moment Гўв‚¬вЂќ the ember-mark on her forehead, barely visible beneath road-grime and ash.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Keeper,\" he says. Not a question. An acknowledgment.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen meets his eyes. \"Highness.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe silence holds for three heartbeats.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Then thereГўв‚¬в„ўs still a chance,\" Harald says. And for the first time, his voice shakes.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs briefing (summarise or roleplay as needed):\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe siege is tightening. He expects a major assault within two days.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Ever-Ember is failing faster. The Keepers\u0027 absence has accelerated the decline Гўв‚¬вЂќ the flame has no one to speak to it, tend it, or calm it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHe has been unable to reach any other settlements. Hrafnborg is alone.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHe asks Kaelen directly: \"Can you speak to the flame?\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs answer: \"I havenГўв‚¬в„ўt spoken to an Ember in twelve years. I donГўв‚¬в„ўt know if it will still recognise me. But I have to try.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eLewГўв‚¬в„ўs Goodbye (Optional)\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the players have bonded with Lew, give him a departure scene. Lew is not a warrior Гўв‚¬вЂќ heГўв‚¬в„ўs a finder, and his part of the bargain is complete. He delivered the party to Kaelen and guided them home.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLew pulls you aside while Kaelen and Harald talk logistics.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"IГўв‚¬в„ўve done what I said IГўв‚¬в„ўd do. Found your Keeper. Walked your road. Nearly died twice Гўв‚¬вЂќ three times if you count the mud.\" He taps the amber eye. \"This thing is going dark. Has been since we left the Green Heart. WhateverГўв‚¬в„ўs happening with the treeГўв‚¬В¦ itГўв‚¬в„ўs pulling everything inward.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe holds out his hand. \"You owe me a favour. I intend to collect. But first, you have to survive this.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHis grin is thin but real.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Try not to die. Dead men are terrible at paying debts.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: LewГўв‚¬в„ўs Status\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLew can remain in Hrafnborg as a background NPC, or he can depart before the wall breach (slipping out through a route \"only I know about\"). His role in Act 2 depends on campaign direction:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eIf Lew stays:\u003c/strong\u003e He becomes an information broker inside the besieged city, feeding the PCs intel during Act 2Гўв‚¬в„ўs early planning phase.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eIf Lew leaves:\u003c/strong\u003e He surfaces later as a surprise ally or complication Гўв‚¬вЂќ perhaps heГўв‚¬в„ўs found something worse on the road, or perhaps GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs agents have found \u003cem\u003ehim\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eEither way, the favour remains uncollected. Plant this seed.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 4: The Ever-Ember (Ritual Scene)\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis is the emotional and narrative core of Beat 9. Kaelen attempts to speak to the Ever-Ember Гўв‚¬вЂќ the first time a Keeper has addressed the flame in over a year.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Ember Chamber\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Ever-Ember burns in a stone chamber beneath HrafnborgГўв‚¬в„ўs central hall. The room is ancient Гўв‚¬вЂќ older than the city above it, carved from the living rock of the fjord.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe stairway descends into warmth. Not comfortable warmth Гўв‚¬вЂќ desperate warmth. The heat of a dying coal giving everything it has left.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Ember Chamber is circular, thirty feet across, with a domed ceiling carved with runes so old theyГўв‚¬в„ўve smoothed to shapes. At the centre, on a ring of blackened stone, the Ever-Ember burns.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIt is small. Smaller than you expected. A flame the size of a manГўв‚¬в„ўs fist, dancing on a bed of white ash. Its light is orange, tinged with grey at the edges. The shadows it casts are too long, and they move wrong Гўв‚¬вЂќ stretching toward the flame instead of away from it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe air tastes of ash and something older. Something like sap, or resin, or the memory of a forest that no longer exists.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSeven stone seats ring the flame. Six are empty. The seventh Гўв‚¬вЂќ cracked, its surface scarred with the same ember-mark that Kaelen bears Гўв‚¬вЂќ waits.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Ritual\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen approaches the flame-ring. She removes her cloak, her gloves, her boots. Barefoot on the cold stone, she sits in the cracked seventh seat.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen closes her eyes. The ember-mark on her forehead ignites Гўв‚¬вЂќ not the faint pulse of before, but a steady, painful glow. Her face tightens. Her hands grip the stone armrests until her knuckles whiten.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"IГўв‚¬в„ўm here,\" she whispers. \"I left, and IГўв‚¬в„ўm sorry, and IГўв‚¬в„ўm \u003cem\u003ehere\u003c/em\u003e.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Ever-Ember flickers. Then, slowly, it \u003cem\u003ereaches\u003c/em\u003e. A tendril of flame stretches from the bed of ash toward Kaelen. Not heat Гўв‚¬вЂќ not light Гўв‚¬вЂќ but \u003cem\u003econnection\u003c/em\u003e. The flame touches her mark.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen screams.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eNot in pain. In \u003cem\u003egrief\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: Running the Ritual\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis scene is narrative, not mechanical. Do not roll dice. Let the players \u003cem\u003ewatch\u003c/em\u003e. Their characters can be present in the chamber, and they can react, but they cannot help Гўв‚¬вЂќ this is between Kaelen and the flame.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe emotions Kaelen experiences (and transmits through the chamberГўв‚¬в„ўs resonance) are:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLoneliness.\u003c/strong\u003e The flame has been alone. No one has spoken to it. It has been screaming into silence for a year.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eExhaustion.\u003c/strong\u003e The flame is not dying by choice. It is being \u003cem\u003edrained\u003c/em\u003e. Something is pulling its warmth downward, through the roots, into the deep dark.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMemory.\u003c/strong\u003e Flashes of the World-Tree Гўв‚¬вЂќ Yggdrasil as it once was: alive, green, vast, its roots threading through every stone in Svellheim. And Yggdrasil as it is now: grey, hollow, its sap turned to bitter resin, its roots cracking.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eA name.\u003c/strong\u003e Not spoken Гўв‚¬вЂќ \u003cem\u003efelt\u003c/em\u003e. \u003cstrong\u003eGrafvitnir.\u003c/strong\u003e The Grave-Wolf, gnawing at the deepest root. Not free yet. But close. So close.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eA direction.\u003c/strong\u003e Downward. Northward. To the place where the first Ember was lit. The \u003cstrong\u003eEmberwell\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis is the campaignГўв‚¬в„ўs pivot. Let it breathe. Let Kaelen cry. Let the players sit with what the flame is showing them.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eAfter the Ritual\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen slumps in the stone seat. The ember-mark dims to its usual faint glow. The Ever-Ember is slightly brighter Гўв‚¬вЂќ not healed, but \u003cem\u003eheard\u003c/em\u003e. Speaking to it has given the flame strength enough to last weeks instead of days.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhen Kaelen speaks, her voice is raw.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"ItГўв‚¬в„ўs not dying. ItГўв‚¬в„ўs being \u003cem\u003eeaten\u003c/em\u003e.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eShe looks at you with red-rimmed eyes.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Yggdrasil. The World-Tree. The Ever-Embers draw their power from its roots Гўв‚¬вЂќ always have. Sap, warmth, life Гўв‚¬вЂќ it all flows upward from the tree into the flames. But something is consuming the tree from below. Gnawing through the deepest root.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHer voice drops.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Grafvitnir. The name Gragnir gave us. The Grave-Wolf. ItГўв‚¬в„ўs real. ItГўв‚¬в„ўs been imprisoned in the roots since the First Kindling, and every Ember that dies is a lock that opens. When the last Ember goes darkГўв‚¬В¦\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eShe doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt finish the sentence.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"The flame showed me a place. The \u003cem\u003eEmberwell\u003c/em\u003e. ItГўв‚¬в„ўs where the first Ember was lit Гўв‚¬вЂќ where YggdrasilГўв‚¬в„ўs deepest root surfaces. If the tree can be renewed anywhere, itГўв‚¬в„ўs there.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eShe stands. Her legs shake.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"But itГўв‚¬в„ўs far. South, beyond the Interior Belt, beyond the White Waste. At the Throat of the World.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAllow the PCs to ask questions. Kaelen can answer:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat is the Emberwell?\u003c/strong\u003e \"The First Hearth. Where the World-TreeГўв‚¬в„ўs root breaks the surface. Where someone Гўв‚¬вЂќ the stories donГўв‚¬в„ўt say who Гўв‚¬вЂќ lit the first flame and the Embers spread outward through the roots to every settlement.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCan you heal the tree?\u003c/strong\u003e \"I donГўв‚¬в„ўt know. The flame showed me the place. It didnГўв‚¬в„ўt show me how. Maybe when we get there, weГўв‚¬в„ўll understand.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat about Hrafnborg?\u003c/strong\u003e \"The Ember is stronger now. Not much, but enough. Speaking to it bought time. Maybe a month, if nothing gets worse.\" She pauses. \"But things \u003cem\u003ewill\u003c/em\u003e get worse.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat about Grafvitnir?\u003c/strong\u003e \"ItГўв‚¬в„ўs not free. Not yet. But itГўв‚¬в„ўs \u003cem\u003eaware\u003c/em\u003e. It felt me speak to the Ember. It knows someone is listening now.\" She touches her ember-mark. \"And I think itГўв‚¬в„ўs angry.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 5: The Breach (Boss Combat)\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Combat (Boss) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 VP on victory\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a3a1a; color:#c8e8c8; padding:10px 14px; margin:10px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003cp style=\"margin:0;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVictory Points Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eType:\u003c/strong\u003e Combat (Boss) | \u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard | \u003cstrong\u003eVP Award:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 VP on victory\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs connection to the Ember did not go unnoticed. The ritual sent a pulse of warmth through YggdrasilГўв‚¬в„ўs roots Гўв‚¬вЂќ a flare in the dark. The dead felt it. Grafvitnir felt it. And now the siege army \u003cem\u003emoves\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Alarm\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis can trigger immediately after the ritual or after a brief rest (GMГўв‚¬в„ўs choice based on pacing). Alarm bells ring across Hrafnborg.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe bells start on the western wall. Then the eastern. Then everywhere.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou reach the ramparts and see it: the silent ring has broken. The dead are no longer waiting.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThey come in a single, massive wave Гўв‚¬вЂќ not at the gate, but at the southwestern wall. The section weakened by the marshes. The section \u003cem\u003eyou\u003c/em\u003e came through.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAt the front of the tide, something larger. A figure in corroded mail, bearing a banner of frozen bone. A crown of black iron sits on its skull. It walks upright, deliberate, and the dead \u003cem\u003epart\u003c/em\u003e around it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA Wight-Lord. And itГўв‚¬в„ўs heading for the breach.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eEncounter Setup\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eCombat: The Wall Breach\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDifficulty:\u003c/strong\u003e Hard (Level 3 PCs, climactic encounter)\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEnvironment:\u003c/strong\u003e HrafnborgГўв‚¬в„ўs southwestern wall section. The battle takes place on and around the wall-walk, with the dead surging below.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMap Features:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWall-walk\u003c/strong\u003e (2 squares wide, elevated 15 feet): The main fighting platform. PCs and guards hold this line.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBreach point\u003c/strong\u003e (3 squares wide): A section of wall that has partially collapsed from the marsh erosion. The dead climb through here. The Wight-Lord targets this point.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eInner courtyard\u003c/strong\u003e (below the wall, open ground): If the dead get through, civilians and the wounded are exposed.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSignal-fire braziers\u003c/strong\u003e (3 locations on the wall): Bright light in 4 squares. Can be toppled onto enemies below (Action: easy Might test, deals 8 fire damage in a 2ГѓвЂ”2 area, one-time use per brazier).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOil trenches\u003c/strong\u003e (1 square wide, along the base of the wall): Pre-prepared defence. Can be ignited (Action: touch with any fire source, burns for 3 rounds, deals 5 fire damage to any creature entering or starting its turn in the trench).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAllied Forces:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e6 Hrafnborg Guards\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 1 Minions, Stamina 1, Speed 5, Spear +3 vs Might for 3 damage). They hold the flanks. When a guard dies, describe it Гўв‚¬вЂќ these are named people with families.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHarald\u003c/strong\u003e is present but commanding the defence at other wall sections. He does not fight here unless the Defence Track drops to 0.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eKaelen\u003c/strong\u003e is exhausted from the ritual. She can take one action per round (either a melee attack at +4 for 6 damage, or use her ember-mark to create bright light in a 3-square radius, giving the undead a bane on attacks within it). She cannot sustain this past 3 rounds.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEnemies:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e1 \u003cstrong\u003eWight-Lord\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 4 Brute Elite)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e10 \u003cstrong\u003eDraugr Thralls\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 1 Brute Minion)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e4 \u003cstrong\u003eOath-Broken Draugr\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 3 Brute Elite)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eReinforcements:\u003c/strong\u003e At the start of round 3 and each subsequent round, 2 additional Draugr Thralls climb through the breach. This stops when the Wight-Lord is destroyed (its command aura sustains the assault).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eWight-Lord (Level 4 Boss)\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eUndead, Medium\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eStamina:\u003c/strong\u003e 80 | \u003cstrong\u003eSpeed:\u003c/strong\u003e 5 | \u003cstrong\u003eSize:\u003c/strong\u003e M | \u003cstrong\u003eStability:\u003c/strong\u003e 2 | \u003cstrong\u003eFree Strike:\u003c/strong\u003e 6\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCharacteristics:\u003c/strong\u003e Might +4, Agility +1, Reason +2, Intuition +3, Presence +4\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eImmunities:\u003c/strong\u003e Fear, charm, poison, cold\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAttacks:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFellblade\u003c/strong\u003e (Melee, Might, Signature): +6 vs. Might; 4/7/10 damage. On tier 3: target takes ongoing 3 cold damage (save ends) and is frightened of the Wight-Lord (save ends).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCommand the Fallen\u003c/strong\u003e (Action, 3 Malice, Range 10): The Wight-Lord raises 2 Draugr Thralls in unoccupied squares within range. These thralls act immediately with a single move action.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDeath-Gaze\u003c/strong\u003e (Action, Range 5, Presence): 6 vs. Presence; 6 psychic damage. On tier 2: the target is dazed (save ends). On tier 3: the target is instead stunned (save ends).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTriggered Actions:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eUndying Will\u003c/strong\u003e (Triggered, 1/encounter): When reduced to 0 Stamina, the Wight-Lord does not fall. Instead, it is reduced to 1 Stamina, gains resist 5 to all damage until the end of its next turn, and makes a free Fellblade attack against the nearest creature. It can be killed normally after this.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTraits:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eLord of the Barrow:\u003c/em\u003e All allied undead within 5 squares gain +1 to damage rolls and cannot be turned or banished while the Wight-Lord lives.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eCrown of Black Iron:\u003c/em\u003e The Wight-Lord continually emanates supernatural cold. Any creature that ends its turn adjacent to the Wight-Lord takes 2 cold damage.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eBarrow-Sense:\u003c/em\u003e The Wight-Lord can sense living creatures within 10 squares regardless of concealment or invisibility.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMalice Abilities (Director spends Malice):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGrave-Command\u003c/strong\u003e (2 Malice): All Draugr Thralls within 10 squares immediately shift 2 squares and make a free strike.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFrost Roar\u003c/strong\u003e (3 Malice): Each creature within 3 squares must make a medium Might test or be pushed 2 squares and take 4 cold damage. On a tier 1 result, they are also knocked prone. The breach point widens Гўв‚¬вЂќ treat the breach as 1 square wider for the rest of the encounter.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAppearance:\u003c/strong\u003e A towering figure in corroded mail, its skull crowned with black iron. The banner it carries is a human spine wrapped in frozen sinew. Its eye sockets burn with pale green fire. When it speaks, its voice is the grinding of stone on stone.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#b8860b;\"\u003eOath-Broken Draugr (Level 3 Standard)\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eUndead, Medium\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eStamina:\u003c/strong\u003e 40 | \u003cstrong\u003eSpeed:\u003c/strong\u003e 5 | \u003cstrong\u003eSize:\u003c/strong\u003e M | \u003cstrong\u003eStability:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 | \u003cstrong\u003eFree Strike:\u003c/strong\u003e 5\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCharacteristics:\u003c/strong\u003e Might +3, Agility +2, Reason +1, Intuition +2, Presence +1\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAttacks:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOath-Blade\u003c/strong\u003e (Melee, Might): +5 vs. Might; 7 damage. On tier 3: target takes ongoing 2 cold damage (save ends).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAccusing Howl\u003c/strong\u003e (Action, 5 Malice, Range 5, Presence): +4 vs. Presence; 5 psychic damage and target has a bane on their next power roll. (\u003cem\u003eThe draugr screams a name Гўв‚¬вЂќ not yours, but someone youГўв‚¬в„ўve failed.\u003c/em\u003e)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTraits:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eTactical Dead:\u003c/em\u003e The Oath-Broken fights with remembered skill. It flanks, retreats from fire, and targets isolated PCs.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eUnfeeling:\u003c/em\u003e Immune to fear, charm, and pain-based effects.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eThe Dead Remember:\u003c/em\u003e When the Oath-Broken drops to 0 Stamina, it whispers one true thing Гўв‚¬вЂќ a fragment of memory from its former life. This has no mechanical effect but can provide lore clues or emotional weight.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAppearance:\u003c/strong\u003e Better-preserved than thralls. Wears the remains of a hirdmanГўв‚¬в„ўs armour. Its eyes hold a dull, hateful intelligence.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eCombat Narrative Beats\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eUse these to structure the battleГўв‚¬в„ўs emotional arc:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRound 1-2: The Surge.\u003c/strong\u003e The dead pour through the breach. The wall guards hold the flanks. The PCs face the Oath-Broken vanguard.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe first draugr through the breach is a farmer. You can see the calluses on its hands. It lurches at the nearest guard with dead fingers.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBehind it: soldiers. Real soldiers, once Гўв‚¬вЂќ their armour is wrong, their movements are wrong, but the muscle memory of shield-walls is still there. They come through the breach in formation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRound 3-4: The Lord Arrives.\u003c/strong\u003e The Wight-Lord reaches the breach. When it steps onto the wall-walk, the temperature drops. Breath fogs. Weapons frost over.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Wight-Lord places one mailed hand on the broken wall and \u003cem\u003epulls itself up\u003c/em\u003e. Stone cracks under its grip. The banner of frozen bone plants itself in the rubble, and the dead around it \u003cem\u003estraighten\u003c/em\u003e. Their shuffling stops. Their movements become purposeful.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Wight-Lord opens its jaw and speaks. The voice is old and full of gravel and buried things.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"\u003cem\u003eThe Keeper has spoken to the flame. The flame has answered. And the answer is: it is too late.\u003c/em\u003e\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIt draws its blade Гўв‚¬вЂќ a black iron thing, sheeted in ice Гўв‚¬вЂќ and points it at your chest.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"\u003cem\u003eGive us the Keeper. Let the rest end.\u003c/em\u003e\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRound 5+: Desperation.\u003c/strong\u003e The battle turns on killing the Wight-Lord. When it uses Undying Will, the dead surge. When it finally falls Гўв‚¬вЂќ\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Wight-Lord falls. Its crown cracks against the stone, splitting into three pieces. The black iron corrodes to dust in seconds.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFor a heartbeat, the dead freeze. Then Гўв‚¬вЂќ like puppets with cut strings Гўв‚¬вЂќ they \u003cem\u003eslump\u003c/em\u003e. Not all of them. Not even most. But the coordination breaks. The wave falters. Guards shout, surge forward, push the thralls back through the breach.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSomewhere on the wall, someone starts hammering. Rubble goes into the gap. The line holds.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBarely.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eAftermath\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAfter the combat:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe breach is sealed with rubble. It will hold Гўв‚¬вЂќ for now.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Hrafnborg Defence Track drops by 1 (or more, if guards died or the breach widened via Frost Roar).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe dead outside resume their vigil. They donГўв‚¬в„ўt retreat, but the coordinated assault stops with the Wight-LordГўв‚¬в„ўs death.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf any named guards died, describe the aftermath. Hrafnborg cannot afford losses.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#4a4a4a;\"\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: Consequences and the Defence Track\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe current Defence Track value determines the tone of the Act 1 ending:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e8+:\u003c/strong\u003e Hrafnborg is hurting but hopeful. The breach held. The PCs are heroes. Harald speaks of the mission to the Emberwell with cautious optimism.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e5-7:\u003c/strong\u003e The city is wounded. The PCs are respected but feared Гўв‚¬вЂќ \"they brought the Keeper, and the dead attacked harder.\" Harald speaks of the Emberwell as a last option.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBelow 5:\u003c/strong\u003e Hrafnborg is on its knees. The PCs see stretchers, mourning, accusation. Harald orders the mission to the Emberwell not as hope but as \u003cem\u003ethe only thing left\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLet the track inform the emotional register of Part 6 and 7. The mission is the same regardless Гўв‚¬вЂќ but how the PCs feel about it changes everything.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 5b: The Shape-WalkerГўв‚¬в„ўs Move\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ Director Note: This Scene Interrupts Part 5\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis scene is triggered \u003cstrong\u003eduring\u003c/strong\u003e the wall breach combat Гўв‚¬вЂќ specifically at the start of Round 3, when the Wight-Lord reaches the breach and the battle is at its most chaotic. The party is split between holding the wall and saving the King. This is intentional. It is the hardest choice in Act 1.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Trigger\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAt the start of Round 3 of the wall combat, a runner arrives from the keep interior. He is young, bleeding from a gash across his forehead, and his voice cracks:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eГўв‚¬Е“The KingГўв‚¬в„ўs chambers Гўв‚¬вЂќ somethingГўв‚¬в„ўs \u003cem\u003ewrong\u003c/em\u003e Гўв‚¬вЂќ we heard screaming, the guards arenГўв‚¬в„ўt answering, the door wonГўв‚¬в„ўtГўв‚¬вЂќГўв‚¬Вќ\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHe grabs the nearest PCГўв‚¬в„ўs arm.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eГўв‚¬Е“The \u003cem\u003ehound\u003c/em\u003e. Someone said they saw the hound walk \u003cem\u003eupright\u003c/em\u003e.Гўв‚¬Вќ\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe party now has a decision that cannot wait: the Wight-Lord is on the wall and the wall will not hold itself. But Harald is alone in the KingГўв‚¬в„ўs chambers and Dreyfus has finally moved.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: The Split\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe intent is to force hard choices, not punish bad luck. Structure the split as follows:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eIf the party splits:\u003c/strong\u003e Some PCs stay to fight the Wight-Lord (the wall cannot hold without them Гўв‚¬вЂќ guards are Level 1 minions and Kaelen is exhausted). Some PCs go to Harald. Both tracks run simultaneously. Use a simple countdown: every 2 rounds that pass without the KingГўв‚¬в„ўs group reaching Harald, HaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs Stamina track drops by 1 step (see the table below).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eIf the entire party goes to Harald:\u003c/strong\u003e The Wight-Lord kills 2 guards per round and begins driving the dead deeper into the city. Defence Track drops by 1 per round until the Wight-Lord is destroyed. The party will have to defeat Dreyfus \u003cstrong\u003eand then\u003c/strong\u003e return to finish the Wight-Lord (it will still be present, directing the assault, having killed several guards).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eIf the entire party stays on the wall:\u003c/strong\u003e HaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs Stamina track depletes at 1 step per round. At track 0, Harald is gravely wounded Гўв‚¬вЂќ he survives, but barely, and he will carry the injury into Act 2. More importantly: Dreyfus \u003cstrong\u003eescapes\u003c/strong\u003e before the party can confront him, having completed his mission of intel-gathering and attempted to cripple the crown. He will not be seen again until Act 3.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eHaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs Stamina Track\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eTrack\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eStatus\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e3\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHarald is cornered but unhurt. Dreyfus is circling, waiting for an opening.\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e2\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHarald has a wound Гўв‚¬вЂќ cut across the arm, blood on the stones. HeГўв‚¬в„ўs fighting with a chair. Dreyfus is pressing the advantage.\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e1\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHarald is down. Unconscious but alive. Dreyfus is 1 round from finishing the job when the PCs arrive.\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e0\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHarald is dead. This ends the campaignГўв‚¬в„ўs political structure in Hrafnborg. It is \u003cstrong\u003esurvivable\u003c/strong\u003e as a campaign consequence, but it changes everything. Run it only if the choices truly led here.\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eDreyfus: The KingГўв‚¬в„ўs Chambers\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe door to the KingГўв‚¬в„ўs inner chambers is splintered from inside. The two guards posted here are not dead Гўв‚¬вЂќ they are pressed against the wall in a fugue, eyes wide and empty, breathing but absent. Something about the shape-walkerГўв‚¬в„ўs presence hollows people who arenГўв‚¬в„ўt protected by guest-right.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eInside: Harald is backed against his war-table. HeГўв‚¬в„ўs holding a hunting knife in one hand and a candlestick in the other, and he is absolutely, unmistakably furious rather than afraid.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAcross from him stands something that used to be a grey hound.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt is no longer a grey hound.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEnemies (split-party вЂ” 2\\u20133 heroes, EV ~60):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e1 Dreyfus\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 4 Ambusher Elite)\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e3 Pale Maw Operatives\u003c/strong\u003e (Level 4 Brute Platoon вЂ” disguised as castle servants, break cover when PCs enter)\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\nbackground:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ GM Notes: DreyfusГўв‚¬в„ўs Revealed Form\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDreyfus is a shape-walker Гўв‚¬вЂќ NГѓВ­ГѓВ°hГѓВ¶ggrГўв‚¬в„ўs eyes and ears given mortal form, serving through GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs network. His revealed shape is not a monster. That would be too easy.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHe is a man. Or the idea of a man: tall, grey-pale, features that are almost-right in a way that the eye cannot fix on. His face shifts slightly when you look directly at him, as if it hasnГўв‚¬в„ўt decided what to settle on. His clothes are HaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs hound-keeperГўв‚¬в„ўs livery, but they fit too well for a dog that just transformed. He has been wearing them for months, in his mind.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHis eyes are wrong. They are gold, and they are too still. They do not blink.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhen he speaks, his voice is pleasant. Educated. The voice of a court advisor.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eГўв‚¬Е“You made better time than expected,Гўв‚¬Вќ he says. He does not move. He is not afraid. He is \u003cstrong\u003ecalculating\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #b8860b; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"color:#b8860b; margin-top:0;\"\u003eDreyfus, Shape-Walker Agent (Level 4 Ambusher Elite)\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHumanoid (Wyrd-bound), Medium\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eStamina:\u003c/strong\u003e 60 | \u003cstrong\u003eSpeed:\u003c/strong\u003e 7 | \u003cstrong\u003eSize:\u003c/strong\u003e M | \u003cstrong\u003eStability:\u003c/strong\u003e 1 | \u003cstrong\u003eFree Strike:\u003c/strong\u003e 6\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCharacteristics:\u003c/strong\u003e Might +1, Agility +4, Reason +3, Intuition +4, Presence +3\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eImmunities:\u003c/strong\u003e Fear, charm\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAttacks:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWyrd-Claw\u003c/strong\u003e (Melee, Agility, Signature): +6 vs. Agility; 5/8/11 damage. On tier 2+: the target has a bane on their next power roll (the wound carries the shape-walkerГўв‚¬в„ўs Wyrd-taint). On tier 3: the target is also weakened until the end of their next turn.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHollowing Gaze\u003c/strong\u003e (Action, Range 5, Intuition, 3 Malice): +5 vs. Presence; 6 psychic damage. On tier 2+: target is dazed (save ends). On tier 3: target is stunned until end of their next turn and loses their next action as they are flooded with a false memory. (\u003cem\u003eThe false memory is mundane and disorienting, not horrific Гўв‚¬вЂќ something ordinary that shouldnГўв‚¬в„ўt be there.\u003c/em\u003e)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTriggered Actions:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eShape-Shift\u003c/strong\u003e (Triggered, 1/round): When Dreyfus takes 10+ damage from a single attack, he may immediately shift his form, becoming a Medium beast (dog, raven, or large rat). He moves up to 3 squares without provoking free strikes. He reverts to his humanoid form at the start of his next turn or when he chooses. While in beast form, he cannot attack but cannot be targeted by effects that require a humanoid target.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTraits:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eWyrd-Guest:\u003c/em\u003e Dreyfus is bound by the laws of guest-right. He cannot make the first attack on anyone he is bound to by guest-right within a space he has been \u003cstrong\u003einvited into\u003c/strong\u003e. Harald invited him inside as his hound. Dreyfus has been manoeuvering for weeks to get Harald to make a hostile move first Гўв‚¬вЂќ which Harald just did with the hunting knife. The guest-right is now void. (\u003cem\u003eThis matters for future encounters: if the PCs ever invite Dreyfus in anywhere, note it.\u003c/em\u003e)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eIntelligence Asset:\u003c/em\u003e Dreyfus has been listening for months. He knows the PCsГўв‚¬в„ў strengths, fighting styles, and likely tactics. At the start of combat, he identifies the hero with the highest Presence and the hero with the highest Might. He targets the Presence-highest first (most dangerous in conversation) and avoids melee with the Might-highest unless cornered.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eEscape Protocol:\u003c/em\u003e When Dreyfus is reduced to half Stamina or below, he immediately uses Shape-Shift to take raven form and attempts to flee through the nearest window, chimney, or gap. He uses his full movement to exit the building. He cannot be stopped by free strikes in raven form (he is too fast and too small). \u003cstrong\u003eHe escapes.\u003c/strong\u003e This is intentional Гўв‚¬вЂќ he has more appearances ahead.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMalice Abilities:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs Shadow\u003c/strong\u003e (3 Malice): All creatures within 3 squares must make a medium Intuition test or lose track of Dreyfus for 1 round Гўв‚¬вЂќ he seems to be somewhere he isnГўв‚¬в„ўt. Effectively grants him concealment for 1 round.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRoot-Whisper\u003c/strong\u003e (1 Malice, triggered on any successful Wyrd-Claw): Dreyfus relays what he just learned about the target through YggdrasilГўв‚¬в„ўs dying root network. This has no immediate mechanical effect, but the GM should note it: Grafvitnir now knows which PC Dreyfus wounded and gains information about their condition.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAppearance:\u003c/strong\u003e In humanoid form: tall, grey-pale, almost-right features, gold unblinking eyes, HaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs hound-keeper livery. In beast form: a large grey dog with gold eyes, silent movement, and the unsettling habit of looking directly at the person speaking rather than moving the way a dog moves.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Fight\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis is not a dungeon encounter. It is a tight, fast scene in the KingГўв‚¬в„ўs inner chamber Гўв‚¬вЂќ a private room with a war-table, a fireplace, a locked chest, and one narrow window.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSpace constraints:\u003c/strong\u003e The room holds 4Гўв‚¬вЂњ5 creatures comfortably. The war-table is difficult terrain if fighting across it. The fireplace is a hazard (1 square, 3 fire damage to any creature that enters or is pushed into it).\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs role:\u003c/strong\u003e He is not a combatant. He will use the hunting knife if cornered, but do not let him die here unless the defence track forced it. If a PC gets between Harald and Dreyfus, Harald will try to get to a guard position or behind cover. He watches everything with the expression of a man cataloguing the worst day of his reign.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDreyfusГўв‚¬в„ўs goal:\u003c/strong\u003e He is not trying to destroy the party. He was trying to kill Harald before anyone arrived. Now that the party is here, he wants to \u003cstrong\u003eescape with maximum information\u003c/strong\u003e. He fights to survive, not to win. He will attempt Hollowing Gaze on the most dangerous-looking PC to buy himself room, then try to wound Harald one more time, then escape.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhen Dreyfus flees:\u003c/strong\u003e He shifts to raven form and goes through the window Гўв‚¬вЂќ or up the chimney if the window is blocked. The raven form is fast enough to dodge a thrown object (difficult Agility test to hit him). When he is gone:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe raven hits the window ledge, folds Гўв‚¬вЂќ and then itГўв‚¬в„ўs just a grey shape dropping into the dark over the siege ring.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSomething small clatters to the stone floor. A talon Гўв‚¬вЂќ curved, black as obsidian, still warm. It fell from the ravenГўв‚¬в„ўs grasp during the shift, torn free by the violence of the transformation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThen the raven is gone.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHarald lowers the knife. His hand is shaking, though his face has gone very still.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eГўв‚¬Е“I invited that \u003cem\u003ething\u003c/em\u003e into my hall,Гўв‚¬Вќ he says. His voice is very quiet. Гўв‚¬Е“I let it sleep at my feet.Гўв‚¬Вќ\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHe looks at the window for a long time.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eГўв‚¬Е“How long has it been listening?Гўв‚¬Вќ\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; border-left:4px solid #4a4a4a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch4\u003eГ°ЕёвЂњВќ Director Notes: Managing DreyfusГўв‚¬в„ўs Designed Escape\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhy this escape serves the story.\u003c/strong\u003e Dreyfus is not a one-beat villain. His escape here creates a campaign-long shadow Гўв‚¬вЂќ every settlement, every exposed campfire, every intelligence failure in Act 2 carries the weight of knowing he is out in the world with everything he learned. When the party finally faces him in Beat 24, that confrontation is earned across fifteen beats of hatred and dread. Killing him here would remove one of the campaignГўв‚¬в„ўs most effective sources of tension.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMaking the escape feel earned, not arbitrary.\u003c/strong\u003e The party should never feel cheated. Ensure the following before Dreyfus flees:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe party \u003cstrong\u003ehurts him\u003c/strong\u003e. They must deal real damage Гўв‚¬вЂќ ideally reducing him to his escape threshold through their own skill. The escape triggers at half Stamina, not at the start of the fight.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThey save Harald. Even though Dreyfus escapes, the King is alive \u003cstrong\u003ebecause the party acted\u003c/strong\u003e. That is their victory.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThey get the talon. The Shape-WalkerГўв‚¬в„ўs Talon (see items-act1.adoc) is physical proof they drew blood. It is their trophy and a tool they can use later.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs reaction grounds the moment in consequence, not frustration. The read-aloud above gives Harald shame and fury Гўв‚¬вЂќ that emotional weight redirects the tableГўв‚¬в„ўs energy from Гўв‚¬Е“he got awayГўв‚¬Вќ to Гўв‚¬Е“look what he did to us.Гўв‚¬Вќ\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHandling clever players.\u003c/strong\u003e If players try to trap Dreyfus (blocking the window, grappling in human form, using abilities to pin him):\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eReward the thinking.\u003c/strong\u003e Acknowledge the clever play. If they block the window, he tries the chimney. If they block both, he burns GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs Shadow (3 Malice) to create confusion and finds a gap Гўв‚¬вЂќ the Wyrd gives him spatial awareness the party cannot match in an enclosed space.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGive them something extra.\u003c/strong\u003e If the party makes a genuinely brilliant play (successful hard Intuition test to anticipate his escape route, or dealing enough damage in a single round to nearly kill him), grant the talon automatically (no damage threshold required) and add a detail: the raven that escapes is trailing feathers, one wing dragging. They \u003cstrong\u003ealmost\u003c/strong\u003e had him. That Гўв‚¬Е“almostГўв‚¬Вќ is worth more narratively than a clean kill.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDo not let them kill him.\u003c/strong\u003e If by extraordinary luck or creative play they reduce him to 0 Stamina before the escape triggers, he still shifts Гўв‚¬вЂќ but the transformation is ragged, painful, and visibly costs him. He escapes but he is \u003cstrong\u003ebroken\u003c/strong\u003e. This will show when he reappears in Beat 24. Note exactly what the party did to him, because the Director should describe those specific injuries manifesting as degradation in his form fifteen beats later.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eForeshadowing the cost.\u003c/strong\u003e Whatever damage the party deals in this fight leaves a mark. Write down the specific injuries: which PC wounded him, with what weapon, where the blow landed. In Beat 24, when Dreyfus reappears with Гўв‚¬Е“edges that flickerГўв‚¬Вќ and shifting that is Гўв‚¬Е“less clean,Гўв‚¬Вќ reference those specific wounds. The party should see the evidence of what they did to him here Гўв‚¬вЂќ proof that their actions in Beat 9 mattered even though he escaped.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eAftermath: DreyfusГўв‚¬в„ўs Information\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe PCs know, and Harald now knows: Dreyfus was GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs agent for the entirety of their mission. Everything discussed in Hrafnborg Гўв‚¬вЂќ the mission to find Kaelen, the route to the Green Heart, the partyГўв‚¬в„ўs capabilities Гўв‚¬вЂќ was relayed through Wyrd-channels to GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs network.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhat Dreyfus did \u003cstrong\u003enot\u003c/strong\u003e know (because it happened after he fled the chambers): the full contents of KaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs ritual communication with the Ember. He was outside the Ember ChamberГўв‚¬в„ўs Wyrd-ward when it occurred. Grafvitnir knows Kaelen spoke to the flame, and knows it made the flame stronger Гўв‚¬вЂќ but not what was said or where the party is going.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis is the partyГўв‚¬в„ўs one intelligence advantage. They know where theyГўв‚¬в„ўre going. Grafvitnir does not Гўв‚¬вЂќ yet.\u003c/p\u003e\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 6: What the Ember Said\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAfter the battle, in a quieter moment, Kaelen and the PCs convene with Harald in the Ember Chamber. The flame is steadier now Гўв‚¬вЂќ KaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs communion stabilised it Гўв‚¬вЂќ but the fundamental truth is clear.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eKaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs Report\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eKaelen stands before the flame. She is bruised, exhausted, and still trembling from the battle. But her voice is steady.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"The Ever-Embers are not hearth-fires. They never were. TheyГўв‚¬в„ўre \u003cem\u003eleaves\u003c/em\u003e. YggdrasilГўв‚¬в„ўs warmth flows upward through the roots, surfaces at the Embers, and spreads outward. Every Ember is a node in a living system Гўв‚¬вЂќ warmth, life, the boundary between the living and the dead. All of it flows from the tree.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eShe touches the flame with one bare hand. It doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt burn her.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Yggdrasil is dying. Something Гўв‚¬вЂќ Grafvitnir, the Grave-Wolf Гўв‚¬вЂќ has been gnawing at the deepest root since the First Kindling. It was imprisoned there as part of the binding. The prison \u003cem\u003eis\u003c/em\u003e the root. And as the root weakens, the Embers fed by it Гўв‚¬вЂќ all of them Гўв‚¬вЂќ are guttering.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eShe looks at Harald.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"The flame showed me the Emberwell. The place where the first Ember was kindled, where the root surfaces. If the tree can be healed Гўв‚¬вЂќ or the prison reforged Гўв‚¬вЂќ it has to happen there.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"But the flame also showed me Grafvitnir. Not clearly. JustГўв‚¬В¦ hunger. An intelligence that has been patient for an age, and whose patience is ending.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eShe takes a breath.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"If we do nothing, the last Ember dies within the year. Grafvitnir breaks free. And thenГўв‚¬В¦\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eShe doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt finish.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eHaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs Decision\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs response depends on the Defence Track and the tone of the session, but the core decision is the same:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHarald is silent for a long time. When he speaks, his voice is that of a king delivering a sentence Гўв‚¬вЂќ not of hope, but of law.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"I cannot lead this mission. Hrafnborg needs a king on the walls. But I can give you what I have: supplies, maps, authority.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe looks at each of you in turn.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"YouГўв‚¬в„ўve proven yourselves. You found Kaelen. You broke the siege line. You held the wall. I trust you with what comes next Гўв‚¬вЂќ not because I have faith, but because I have no other option.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe draws a deep breath.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Go to the Emberwell. Find out what the tree needs. Do what must be done.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHis voice cracks, just once.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"And come back.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eGragnirГўв‚¬в„ўs Final Words\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf the GM wishes, Gragnir appears one last time Гўв‚¬вЂќ at the edge of the Ember Chamber, in the doorway, half in shadow. He does not enter. The Ever-EmberГўв‚¬в„ўs light seems to bend around him.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"The flame told her true.\" GragnirГўв‚¬в„ўs voice is low, rough, and carries the smell of peat-smoke. \"The Emberwell is real. The road is south, through the White Waste, to the Throat of the World.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe pauses.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"I cannot walk that road with you. Not all of it. The closer we get to the deep root, the more Grafvitnir will feel me Гўв‚¬вЂќ and I have kept my presence hidden for too long to burn that advantage now.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHis gaze moves to Kaelen. Something passes between them Гўв‚¬вЂќ old pain, old debt.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"But I will find you when it matters. I always do.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe turns to leave. Then stops.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"The shape-walker Гўв‚¬вЂќ Dreyfus Гўв‚¬вЂќ is still at HaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs side. He heard every plan you made before you left, and he has been listening to every word the King has spoken since. When you return, the hound will be there, watching. You must decide what to do about that Гўв‚¬вЂќ but do not act rashly. Guest-right binds even shape-walkers, and a cornered spy is more dangerous than a patient one.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA half-smile, ash-dry.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\"Trust is the only currency left that doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt freeze.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHe is gone. The doorway is empty. The ash-smell lingers.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003ePart 7: The Road Ahead (Act 2 Hook)\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe final scene of Act 1 sets the stage for the next chapter.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003ePreparations\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eGive the PCs a short downtime scene in Hrafnborg before departure. They can:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eResupply:\u003c/strong\u003e Harald provides cold-weather gear, rations (10 days), maps of the Interior Belt and the northern routes toward the White Waste, and a sealed letter of authority bearing the Cold Iron CrownГўв‚¬в„ўs seal.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGather information:\u003c/strong\u003e Ask NPCs about the Emberwell, the White Waste, the Throat of the World. Most people have never heard of the Emberwell specifically, but the Throat of the World is known in legend Гўв‚¬вЂќ a volcanic plateau beyond the northern glaciers where \"the roots of the world break the ice.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePersonal scenes:\u003c/strong\u003e Say goodbye to NPCs, write letters, make promises. If Lew is still in Hrafnborg, he makes a final snide comment and refuses to say anything sentimental.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRest:\u003c/strong\u003e A respite in actual beds. This may be the last time for a while.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eThe Departure\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#2a2a3a; color:#e0d8c8; padding:14px 18px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:6px; border-left:4px solid #c4a03c; font-style:italic;\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou leave Hrafnborg at dawn. The guards open the postern gate Гўв‚¬вЂќ the same one you entered through Гўв‚¬вЂќ and you slip out into the grey.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe dead are still there. But theyГўв‚¬в„ўve pulled back from the southwestern marsh. Not far. Just enough. KaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs ember-mark glows faintly, and the nearest draugr \u003cem\u003eflinch\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIt wonГўв‚¬в„ўt last. The markГўв‚¬в„ўs strength will fade as you move further from the Ever-Ember. But for now, it clears a path.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe road north stretches ahead of you. The Interior Belt. The White Waste beyond it. And somewhere, at the end of the world, the Emberwell.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBehind you, HrafnborgГўв‚¬в„ўs Ever-Ember flickers. Ahead, the wind rises.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou walk.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eOutcomes\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBy the end of Beat 9, the PCs should have:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBroken through the undead siege line to reach Hrafnborg.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWitnessed the city under siege Гўв‚¬вЂќ the human cost of the crisis.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWatched Kaelen speak to the Ever-Ember and received the full revelation: Yggdrasil is dying, Grafvitnir is gnawing at the deepest root, the Embers are failing because the tree is failing.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDefended the walls against a Wight-Lord assault Гўв‚¬вЂќ the climactic combat of Act 1.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eReceived their new mission: journey to the Emberwell to renew the spark (or discover what must be done).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSaid goodbye to Harald and (possibly) Lew.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHeard GragnirГўв‚¬в„ўs final warning about the road ahead and the shape-walker still at HaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs side.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSet out south toward the White Waste and the Throat of the World.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eWhat Act 1 Has Established\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:12px 0; color:#2a2a2a; background:#faf8f2;\"\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#e8e0d0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eElement\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 10px; text-align:left; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eStatus at Act 1 End\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Crisis\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eFully understood. Yggdrasil is dying. Grafvitnir gnaws the root. Ever-Embers are symptoms, not the disease.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Mission\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePivoted from \"find the Keeper\" to \"save the World-Tree.\" Destination: the Emberwell.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Party\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eLevel 3. Bonded through hardship. No longer volunteers Гўв‚¬вЂќ agents of the flame.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eKaelen\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eReturned. Wounded by guilt and communion. The partyГўв‚¬в„ўs connection to the Embers.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLew\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eDebt settled (mostly). May or may not be present. Favour still owed.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGragnir\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eRevealed as ancient guardian. Will not walk the full road. Appears when it matters.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDreyfus\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eExposed but still at HaraldГўв‚¬в„ўs side. GrafvitnirГўв‚¬в„ўs agent. The party knows the truth Гўв‚¬вЂќ but Dreyfus doesnГўв‚¬в„ўt know they know. A ticking bomb in the throne room.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHarald\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHolding Hrafnborg. Alone. Trusting the PCs with everything.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHrafnborg\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eBesieged but stabilised. KaelenГўв‚¬в„ўs communion bought time Гўв‚¬вЂќ not salvation.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe World\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 10px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eGetting worse. The dead rise. The cold tightens. The World-Tree screams in silence.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#2a6a2a;\"\u003eBeat 9 Гўв‚¬вЂќ Victory Point Summary\u003c/h4\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:8px 0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#c0e0c0;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eEvent\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eDifficulty\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eVP Award\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 2: Breaking the Line Montage (2 rounds)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHard\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e2/1/0 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003eCombat Complication: The Watchers\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003eModerate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003e1 VP on victory\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 5: The Breach (Boss Combat)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHard\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e2 VP on victory\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#98cc98;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eBeat Total (Mandatory)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eup to 4 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#f5f0e6; color:#2a2a2a; padding:12px 16px; margin:12px 0; border-radius:4px; border-left:4px solid #4ac84a;\"\u003e\u003ch4 style=\"margin-top:0; color:#2a6a2a;\"\u003eBeat 9 Гўв‚¬вЂќ Victory Point Summary\u003c/h4\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:8px 0; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#c0e0c0;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eEvent\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eDifficulty\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"padding:6px 8px; text-align:left;\"\u003eVP Award\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 2: Breaking the Line Montage (2 rounds)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHard\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e2/1/0 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003eCombat Complication: The Watchers\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003eModerate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#555; font-style:italic;\"\u003e1 VP on victory\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003ePart 5: The Breach (Boss Combat)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003eHard\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#2a2a2a;\"\u003e2 VP on victory\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"background:#98cc98;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eBeat Total (Mandatory)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:6px 8px; color:#1a2a1a; font-weight:bold;\"\u003eup to 4 VP\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eTransition to Act 2\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eThe road north. The White Waste. The Throat of the World.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eDreyfus sits at the KingГўв‚¬в„ўs feet. Grafvitnir knows everything. The Embers are failing.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eBut you carry the flameГўв‚¬в„ўs last direction. You carry an oath. And you carry each other.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eProceed to \u003cstrong\u003eAct 2: The White Waste Gate\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","markdown":null},"src":null,"system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"sort":90,"flags":{},"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"exportSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"draw-steel","systemVersion":"0.10.0","createdTime":0,"modifiedTime":0,"lastModifiedBy":null}}],"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"exportSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"draw-steel","systemVersion":"0.10.0","createdTime":0,"modifiedTime":0,"lastModifiedBy":null}}